title: turkey chili
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in olive oil until soft. Add ground turkey and season with salt, pepper, 1 tablespoon of cumin and chili powder. Crumble turkey as it cools. In a crock-pot, put tomatoes, beans, 2 tablespoons cumin, chili powder, salt and pepper to taste. Add a dash of hot pepper sauce or more if you want it spicier. Add turkey mixture to tomato mixture (drain fat if there is a lot of liquid). Cook on high anywhere from 6 to 8 hours, depending on how tender you want the meat.

title: granny's graham cracker cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add yolks, one at a time, and beat well.
Mix flour, baking powder and crackers (ground fine).
Add it with milk to first mixture.
Add vanilla.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in 2 layers in 350° oven.
Put in custard filling with 1/2 cup chopped walnuts, lemon rind and juice of lemon.
Frost with a butter frosting.

title: tomato macaroni bake
directions: Lightly brown, in a saucepan, onion in butter or margarine. Stir in tomato soup, water and 3/4 cup Cheddar cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Blend with cooked macaroni; pour into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup Cheddar cheese and buttered bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until nicely browned and bubbling.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tagliarini
directions: Heat oil and brown meat.
Add ingredients, except cheese, and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, about 25 minutes. Remove lid from pan and cook 10 to 15 minutes.
If Parmesan cheese is used, pour into serving dish and sprinkle with cheese.
If Cheddar cheese is used, fold carefully into the mixture and serve.

title: cheese cake
directions: Grease bottom and sides of an 8-inch spring-form pan; place on a baking sheet.
In a large mixing bowl, stir together flour, pudding mix and baking powder; add the 1/2 cup milk, margarine or butter and egg.
Beat with an electric mixer on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour batter into the prepared pan.
Slice the 2 bananas; arrange slices atop batter.
Set aside.

title: batter-dipped chicken
directions: Heat oil in deep fryer to 370°.
Combine pancake mix and milk in shallow dish.
Season with garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken pieces in batter, coat well.
Fry in batches until golden, about 1 minute.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with hot mustard or sweet and sour sauce.
Great as an appetizer.

title: barbecued chicken wings
directions: Remove small wing tips and discard.
Cut remaining wings in two pieces.
Place in baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over wings.
Bake at 350° for one hour or longer if a thicker sauce is preferred.
Serves 12.

title: lemon pudding cake(goes fast)
directions: Mix butter, flour, 3/4 cup sugar and 2 egg yolks. Add milk. Add lemon juice. Stir well.

title: pineapple surprise cake
directions: Bake as directed (use layers).
Spread 1/2 pineapple on first layer.
Mix pudding, cream cheese with milk; mix until thickened. Spread 1/2 pudding mixture over top of pineapple.
Position 2nd layer of cake on top.
Cover with rest of pineapple, then rest of pudding mixture.
Frost whole cake with Cool Whip.

title: italian chicken
directions: Let chicken soak in dressing overnight.
Preheat oven to 350° and put chicken on a cookie sheet.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
It's ready to serve with your meal.

title: classic waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle apple cubes with sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Add celery, grapes and nuts.
Fold mayonnaise into whipped cream. Gently fold into apple mixture.
Chill and serve in lettuce-lined bowls.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients with salt and pepper to your taste.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a dish.
Put in drained fruit.
Cover with 1 cup sugar, then cover with batter made of 3/4 cup sugar, flour and milk.
Mix well and pour over fruit.
(Makes a thin batter.)
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: brisket of beef
directions: Wipe brisket with wet cloth.
Place in a heavy pot with a tight-fitting lid.
Pour onion soup on brisket.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over brisket.
Cook, covered, in oven at 350° for 1 hour for each pound of brisket.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter, vanilla and coconut.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens. (Alternate method:
Microwave for 6 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.)
Remove from heat and add butter, vanilla and coconut. Pour mixture into cooled pie shell.
Top with your favorite topping.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Blend in remaining ingredients. Drop by tablespoons into hot oil at 375°.

title: chili chicken
directions: Mix chicken and tomato sauce in 4-quart Dutch oven.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in beans and corn.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low.

title: spiced tea
directions: Use 2 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: strawberry snow
directions: Prepare strawberry pudding with milk as directed on the box. Beat the egg whites until stiff and lightly fold into pudding mix. Pile into tall glasses in alternate layers with the strawberry pie filing and allow to chill.

title: sugar-free blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 12 muffin pan cups with nonstick cooking spray.
In large bowl, sift flour, baking powder, salt and sweetener.
In small bowl, beat egg, milk and margarine with fork or whisk.
Add egg mixture and blueberries to flour mixture.
Stir just until flour is moistened.
Spoon batter in cups.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until toothpick is clean.
One muffin = 1/2 bread and 1/2 fat.
Calories - 117; 2 gm fat.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and egg.
Add vanilla.
Add rest of ingredients and stir in well.
Mix in 1/2 cup nuts if desired.
Roll into small balls.
Put on cookie sheet that is greased and press with a fork in crisscross fashion.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: 24 hour vegetable salad
directions: Put in a 9 x 13-inch dish and layer in the following order. Cover and leave overnight in refrigerator.
Do not stir or mix. Lettuce, green pepper, celery, peas (break up frozen ice and peas), onion, add sugar to mayonnaise and frost salad like cake, grated cheese, bacon.

title: james' potato surprise
directions: Heat oil in pan over medium heat.
When hot, add cut potatoes, carrots and smoked sausage and onion.
Cook until carrots, onions and potatoes are tender, then add kraut.
Simmer a few minutes until kraut is warm and flavors have blended.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt margarine and add to sugar.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: toffee
directions: Combine butter, sugar and 1 cup nuts.
Boil mixture until it turns light brown and has dark brown streaks, stirring constantly. Pour onto cookie sheet and spread evenly.
Place chocolate bars on top and spread.
Sprinkle remaining nuts on top.

title: original chip cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking powder and salt.
Beat butter in mixer bowl until smooth.
Beat in sugars, vanilla, water and eggs until light and fluffy.
Blend in flour mixture.
Stir in nuts and chips.
Drop from teaspoon, 2 inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown. Makes about 8 dozen.

title: orange-date-nut cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time. Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add sifted flour in about 3 parts to the butter mixture, alternating with the buttermilk.
Beat until smooth after each addition.
Add orange rind, dates and pecans that have been floured.
Bake in tube pan 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: chicken nut puffs
directions: Combine chicken and almonds. Set aside. In a large saucepan, combine the next 7 ingredients. Bring to a boil. Add flour all at once, stirring until a smooth ball forms. Remove from heat. Let set 5 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Beat until smooth. Stir in chicken and almonds. Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheets. Bake at 450° for 12 to 14 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm. Yield: about 6 dozen.

title: marshmallow fruit dip
directions: Blend together.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Arrange fresh fruit on plate and serve with dip.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Blend in flour, onions, salt and pepper.
Cook until mixture is bubbly.
Stir in chicken broth and milk.
Heat to boiling and boil for 1 minute. Stir in chicken, peas, carrots and potatoes; set aside.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cook peppers in boiling water about 5 minutes; drain well. Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add meat and saute until brown.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: carolyn's pancakes
directions: Put eggs and sugar in a 2-quart pitcher or mixing bowl and beat lightly with rotary beater.
Blend in milk and oil.
Add flour.
Blend together and beat until batter is nearly smooth.
Do not overbeat; small lumps will break up when fried.
Pour batter on hot griddle or frying pan (about 500°).
Turn when bubbles rise to surface in center.
Serve with favorite syrup or fruit.

title: texas pie
directions: Place into baking dish in the order listed, pouring the melted margarine over the top and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: peachy crumb cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, combine dry muffin mix, 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Cut in butter, then stir in nuts.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, combine pie filling, 1/2 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, the almond extract and the drained blueberries.
Spoon the crumb topping over the peaches.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until topping is golden brown.
Serve with ice cream, if desired.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: quick ice cream
directions: Chill milk in ice cube tray until almost frozen at edges.
Put ice cold milk into cold small bowl of electric mixer.
Chill the beaters of mixer and whip the milk until fluffy (high speed).
Add sugar and Kool-Aid.
Whip until stiff.
Freeze in 1-quart ice cube tray until firm, 3 to 4 hours.
Kids really like this.
Makes 8 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant until mushy and drain.
Add all ingredients except 1/2 cup of cheese and 1/2 cup of cracker crumbs and small amount of melted margarine.
Mix well, pour into baking dish. Sprinkle with reserved cheese, crumbs and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: quick potato soup
directions: Add potatoes and onions to the boiling water.
Cover and cook for 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Mash potatoes slightly with a fork to thicken the soup a little, if desired. Add milk, margarine and seasonings.
Heat.
Makes 4 servings.

title: no-fat mock russian dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a wide mouth jar or small bowl. Mix vigorously with a fork or wire whisk until yogurt, ketchup and honey are well blended.
Chill.
Keep covered in refrigerator for storing.

title: egg custard
directions: In large bowl, combine butter, sugar and flour.
Beat eggs; pour into sugar and butter mixture.
Add milk and vanilla. Mix well.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell (9-inch).
Bake until done at 350°.

title: crabmeat hors d'oeuvres
directions: Melt butter and cheese.
Drain crab meat.
Put crab meat in saucepan and season with garlic salt.
Spread on English muffins and add garlic, parsley, salt and paprika.
Broil until brown. Cut with pizza cutter in quarters.

title: swiss chocolate cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Beat well.
Pour into 3 oiled and floured 9-inch pans and bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool thoroughly before frosting.

title: ground meat in barbecue sauce
directions: Combine first
ingredients
in jar and shake to mix. In skillet
melt margarine and add onion.
Cook until onion is transparent.
Add
ground meat and cook until meat is browned. Add salt
and pepper to taste.
Add sauce and continue cooking slowly for
minutes, uncovered.
Spoon meat and sauce onto warm buns.

title: creamy apple squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Combine first 2 ingredients; mix until crumbly. Reserve 2/3 cup for topping. Add brown sugar and cinnamon to reserved topping mix. Mix well. Set aside. Press remaining mixture onto bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan. Arrange apple slices
over base.

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: In bowl, beat eggs.
Add milk, saltines, onion, salt, sage and pepper.
Add beef and mix well.
Shape into 8-1/2 x 4-1/2 inch loaf in an ungreased shallow baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients; spread 3/4 cup over meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 60 - 65 minutes or until no pink remains.
Drain.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.
Serve with remaining sauce.
Serves 6 - 8.

title: ham-vegetable chowder
directions: Melt butter in large soup pot.
Add onion and celery.
Saute until tender.
Add flour, mix well.
Cook about 3 minutes.
Add water or stock, other vegetables and ham.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to a simmer.
Stir occasionally, about 30 minutes or until vegetables are done.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup water.
Bring soup to boil.
Add gelatin and cream cheese to hot soup.
Cook over medium heat until mixture is smooth.
Allow mixture to cool to lukewarm.
Add mayo, celery, onion and seasonings.
Let stand in refrigerator for 5 to 10 minutes until thick.
Add broken shrimp and place in well oiled mold until firm.
Serve with crackers.

title: sloppy jeans
directions: Saute hamburg and onion. Add garlic salt and oregano to taste. Add mushrooms when meat is done. Add water, if more liquid is needed.
Thicken with flour and water, if needed.
Add a few drops of Gravy Master to darken. Simmer 5 minutes. Salt and pepper to taste. Serve on buns or toast.

title: cobbler pie crust
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk and add melted butter.
Drop in with spoon.

title: banana split dessert
directions: In 9x13 pan or glass dish, cover bottom with wafer crumbs. Beat egg whites until stiff, then add sugar and cream cheese.
Mix until smooth.
Pour onto crust.
Add layer of bananas.
Add layer of pineapple.
Next add layer of cherries or strawberries.	Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts if desired.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Scoop out with spatula for best results.
Serves 12-15.

title: apple upside-down cake
directions: Cream
the
fat;
add
the
sugar,
well beaten egg and vanilla.
Sift the dry ingredients together and add alternately with the milk to the first mixture.

title: frozen salad
directions: Fold all together and freeze.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix together.
Put in 8 x 11-inch greased, floured pan. Sprinkle top with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake in a 425° oven for 20 minutes.

title: crock-pot yummy roast
directions: Mix soups and water in crock-pot. Add roast. Cook all day.

title: yuletide punch(non-alcoholic wassail)
directions: In a large saucepan, combine apple juice, cranberry juice cocktail, honey, lemon juice, lemon peel, allspice and cinnamon stick.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes. Remove and discard lemon peel, allspice and cinnamon.
Let cool slightly.
Carefully pour into a heat-proof punch bowl or slow cooker.
Garnish with slices of star fruit.

title: ranger cookies
directions: In bowl, cream shortening, oleo, vanilla and both sugars together.
In bowl, blend dry ingredients, then fold in creamed mixture.
Fold in Rice Krispies, coconut, chocolate chips and pecans.
Roll into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Press with fork.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sticky bread
directions: Thaw bread.
Cut on floured board into 12 slices.
Dip floured slices in melted butter, then sugar/cinnamon mixture. Place in buttered loaf pan to rise.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.

title: bronia's mixed beans dish(abington grange supper)
directions: Cut bacon in pieces.
Brown and add all other ingredients (including the bacon drippings), except beans.
Simmer 20 minutes. Add all the beans, including their juices.
Mix together in a 4-quart baking dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Slice of smoked kielbasa may be added in the mixture.
Serves 10 to 12 generously!

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter.
Spoon into a 2-quart baking dish.
Pour butter over the top and bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned on top.

title: maple salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Tastes great on salads!

title: noodles
directions: Mix well.
Roll out and let rest 20 minutes before cutting.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Rinse peas in hot water; drain.
Combine vegetables, nuts and bacon with sour cream.

title: pepper pups
directions: Slice wieners in bite size pieces. Melt butter with seasoning in pan. Add franks and brown.
Spear with toothpick.

title: beef bake casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni.
Drain.
Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients except onions.
Pour half of mixture into a 2-quart casserole.
Add 1/2 of French fried onions on top.
Pour remaining mixture over onions.
Cover.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: merry berry delite
directions: Break the cake into bite-size pieces.
Divide in half.
Put half of the cake in a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.

title: bacon water chestnuts
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook bacon in large skillet on medium heat until almost crisp; drain.
Wrap bacon around water chestnuts; secure with toothpicks.
Place in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over water chestnuts.
Bake 45 minutes.
Makes about 24.

title: german cheesecake
directions: Cook until thick and cool.

title: celebration frost
directions: Combine concentrate with water, nectar and lemon juice. Mix until smooth. Add sherbert just before serving. Gently add ginger ale. Serve immediately. Serves 24 (8 oz.) servings.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, 1/2 cup butter, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Stir well.
Spoon into a greased dish.
Crush cereal and stir in remaining butter.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Boil the eggplant until soft.
Cut eggplant in half; scoop out pulp and mash well.
Simmer onion in butter until tender.
Add the bread crumbs and salt and pepper to taste.
Stuff pulp mixture back into eggplant shells and bake in a hot oven 15 to 20 minutes.

title: stir-fried beef lo mein
directions: In a medium sized bowl, toss meat with soy sauce and let stand while preparing the other ingredients.
In a large heavy skillet or wok, heat 1 tablespoon oil over moderately high heat.
When oil is very hot, drain beef, saving marinade; add beef to oil.
Stir quickly for about 3 minutes, until brown.
Place a colander over the marinating bowl and pour in beef pan juices.
Wipe the skillet with a paper towel.
Heat the remaining 3 tablespoons of oil in skillet over moderate heat.
Add onion and cook, stirring frequently, until it softens.
Add cabbage and sprinkle with salt. Cook about 2 minutes.
Sprinkle sugar inside the edge of the skillet.
Stir in beef, the juices from the bowl and the chicken broth.
Cook about 1 minute.
Add spaghetti.
Stir mixture and heat for about 3 minutes.

title: rice's stuffed green peppers
directions: Prepare peppers.
Cut off tops about 1/2-inch below the stem and remove seeds.
Blanch peppers for 1 to 2 minutes in boiling water; drain.
Brown meat slightly in oil over medium heat.
Add onions and cook until vegetables are soft.
Remove from heat.
Stir in together 2/3 cup of cheese and all remaining ingredients.
Spoon mixture into peppers.
Sprinkle tops with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: congealed cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello; set in refrigerator until it is of egg white consistency.
Beat cream cheese until smooth; add milk, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in nuts.
Set aside.

title: curried cabbage
directions: Cook shredded cabbage in boiling salted water for 10 to 15 minutes.
Melt butter.
Add combined dry ingredients.
Add milk gradually.
Stir until thickened.
Pour over drained, cooked cabbage.

title: salad dressing
directions: Combine and shake well.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Great on spinach salad.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix all together (batter will be thin).
Grease and flour cookie sheet or jelly roll pan.
Spread batter to cover bottom of pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: spicy franks
directions: Microwave jelly on medium for 4 minutes.
(If using preserves, microwave for 2 minutes.)
Mix mustard into heated jelly.
Place wiener pieces in jelly mixture.
Microwave 2 minutes on Medium.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Heat milk and butter.
Mix sugar, flour, egg yolks and salt. Add to milk and butter.
Cook until thickened.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Brown in the oven.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix sugar with apples.
Let stand until sugar dissolves.
Add eggs and beat well. Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir into apple mixture.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
While cake bakes, make sauce.
Pour over cake as soon as cake comes from oven.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Soften dry yeast in warm water.
Combine milk, sugar, salt and shortening .
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 1 cup flour and beat well.
Beat in yeast and egg.
Gradually add remaining flour to form soft dough, kneading well.
Cover and let rise in warm place until dough doubles.
Turn onto floured surface and shape as desired.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes approximately 12 rolls.

title: mom's cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese and beat well with sharp Cheddar cheese. Add all ingredients, then stir in parsley and pimentos.
Form into a ball and cover with nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: hot ham sandwiches
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Spread mixed ingredients onto bun with 1 slice meat and 1 slice cheese.
Wrap in aluminum foil.
Place on cookie sheet.
Place in preheated oven for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: divinity
directions: Beat egg whites until peaks form.
Cook all ingredients, except vanilla, food coloring and walnuts.
Boil to a hard ball stage.
Add coloring and vanilla, then add to egg whites and beat on medium speed until all gloss has left.
Add walnuts, then spoon out onto waxed paper until set up.

title: dad turner's chili
directions: Brown meat and onion; add water.
Place meat, onion, tomatoes, tomato juice, green pepper, potato, 3 tablespoons chili powder, cloves and sugar in crock-pot.
Cook on high for 2 hours.
Add additional 3 tablespoons chili powder or amount desired.
Continue cooking an additional hour.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat together first 5 ingredients.
Add pecan halves.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° until set, 40 to 50 minutes.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut steak in 1-inch cubes.
Mix soy sauce, garlic and salad oil; let stand 1 hour.
Fry in very hot pan for about 5 minutes; stir occasionally.
Lower heat.
Mix cornstarch with water; stir in pan.
Add tomatoes; cover and cook 5 minutes.
Great with rice and a salad.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Generously grease bottom and sides of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Reserve 1/2 cup dry cake mix for filling.
In a large mixing bowl, combine remaining dry cake mix, margarine and 1 egg; mix until crumbly.
Press into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until light golden brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Wrap chicken in foil and bake at 425° until very tender (about 40 minutes).
Shred into small strips.
Mix with soups and sour cream.
Put into casserole dish.
Crumble Ritz crackers and mix with melted butter.
Spread over chicken mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until bubbly.

title: potato soup
directions: Bring potatoes and onion to a boil; cook until almost done, but not mushy.
Make up flour paste (1/4 to 1/2 cup flour).
Add water to make smooth paste.
Stir into potatoes.
As it thickens, add milk until the right consistency.
Add the butter; stir well. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: a peas cakes(pa dutch breakfast cakes)
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add all liquids.
Mix with spatula or fork.
Make a pattern on top and sprinkle a little sugar on pattern.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in two 8-inch pans.

title: pepper relish
directions: Cut peppers into thin strips; combine vinegar and sugar. Simmer for 15 minutes, then add peppers and onions.
Heat to almost boiling.
Pour in jars and seal.

title: homemade dressing
directions: Combine, shake and allow to sit in the refrigerator for an hour or so.
Shake before each use.

title: french onion dip
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Cover; let stand overnight. Serve with chips or vegetables.
Add 1/3 cup real bacon bits, if desired!

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs 3 minutes.
Cool by running water over eggs.
Peel and cut in half.
Take out yolk and put in small bowl.
Add mayonnaise, salt, pepper and squirt of mustard.
Place back in white of the egg and sprinkle with paprika.

title: raspberry meringue bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Cream the butter, 1/2 cup of sugar and egg yolks in food processor with metal blade or in a mixing bowl with electric mixer until well blended.
Add flour and mix until incorporated. Pat the dough into bottom of prepared pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until lightly browned.
Remove from oven (leave oven on).
Cool pastry for 5 minutes and spread with jam.

title: peas and mushrooms
directions: In large skillet, melt butter over medium-high heat.
Add onion.
Cook, stirring often, 3 minutes or until soft.
Add mushrooms.
Cook, stirring 5 minutes, or until mushrooms are tender.
Stir in peas, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring 3 to 5 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 6.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Mix well and drop by teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: five layer delight
directions: Mix 1/4 cup pecans, oleo and flour and press into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake until golden brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar after cooling.
Mix 1 carton Cool Whip and cream cheese. Spread this mixture over the pecan mixture.
Cover with chocolate pudding.
Top pudding with 2nd carton of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle remaining pecans on top.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: potato doughnuts
directions: Mash potatoes, adding milk and butter.
Add yeast, eggs, salt and flour; mix.
Add flour; let stand until bubbly.
Add enough flour to make soft dough.
Let rise until double.
Cut out with doughnut cutter.
Let rise again.
Fry in deep fat fryer, turning only once, until light golden brown.

title: grandma trey clement's carrot cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs.
Beat.
Add dry ingredients, carrots, nuts, coconut and pineapple.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Check for doneness with a toothpick.

title: granny mcmullen's potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until just done. Add boiled eggs, retaining 1 of the whites for slicing and putting on top of salad.
Add all other ingredients, with salt and pepper to taste.
Add mayonnaise until of desired consistency.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all together and chill at least 6 hours before using.

title: turkey or chicken casserole
directions: Put uncooked rice in bottom of baking dish; add a layer of broccoli, then a layer of chicken.
Pour in chicken broth.
Make a White Sauce and pour over all.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; cut into cubes. Cover with water and season with salt and pepper to taste; boil with chopped onion until tender, but firm (do not overboil).
Drain all water off with a strainer.
Stir gently the margarine and sour cream into the potatoes until margarine is melted and sour cream is well blended. Place in baking dish.
Top with grated cheese and bacon bits. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix by hand cake mix, margarine and 1 egg.
Press in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix until smooth the cream cheese, powdered sugar and 3 eggs.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and melted oleo and press in bottom and sides of pan.

title: german potato salad
directions: Combine bacon, potatoes and onion.
Add remaining ingredients to bacon drippings and heat.
Pour over potatoes.

title: best ever biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Blend in the shortening, milk and egg.
Stir to stiff dough.
Knead and roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into biscuits and bake 10 to 15 minutes in 450° oven.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix ingredients together; chill.
Serve with cut up fresh vegetables.

title: miniature peanut butter treats
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream together margarine, sugars, egg, peanut butter, vanilla and salt.
Gradually add flour and soda; mix well.
Cover and chill.
Roll into walnut-size balls; place each into miniature muffin tin.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes. Remove from oven.
Gently press one peanut butter cup into each cookie to make depression.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: salmon lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 475°. Pour Crisco pure canola oil into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch ovenproof baking dish. Add shrimp and sprinkle with garlic, salt and pepper, then toss with bread crumbs and parsley. Bake at 475° for 5 minutes. Turn shrimp gently with a slotted spatula and bake 3 to 5 minutes more or until pink and bread crumbs are brown. Serve immediately with lemon wedges and rice, if desired.

title: fruit salad
directions: Pour pudding mix in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Stir in juice from pineapple and juice from mandarin oranges to make 1 cup liquid.
Set pineapple and oranges aside.
Cook pudding mix 3 to 4 minutes on high or until mixture boils, stirring once.
Add pineapple and oranges.
Refrigerate 1 hour or until ready to serve.
Stir in bananas when ready to serve.
Keeps several days.

title: rum cake
directions: Place nuts in bottom of well-greased and floured tube or Bundt cake pan.
Mix other ingredients well.
Pour over nuts. Bake 1 hour at 300°. While cake is still warm, pour glaze over it.

title: dirty rice
directions: Brown in skillet the margarine, onion and rice.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Add onion soup, beef consomme, curry powder and mushrooms.
Bake covered for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: stir-fry over uncle ben's rice
directions: Stir-fry shrimp, red pepper and snow peas in oil for 3 1/2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and cook 2 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add oil, white and brown sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt and add to above mixture.
Stir in chopped nuts and mix.
Pour into 2 (5 x 9-inch) greased and floured pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
This bread is very moist and freezes well.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Parboil zucchini 5 to 8 minutes.
Drain and cut in half lengthways.
Hollow out, leaving 1/4-inch shell.
Chop centers. Melt butter, then combine cheese, chestnuts, bread crumbs, garlic, tomato and zucchini centers.
Cook filling until cheese starts to melt.
Fill hollow zucchini.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: deluxe chocolate marshmallow bars
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients.
Mix in nuts, spread in greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Remove from oven and place miniature marshmallows on top of cake.
Return pan to oven for an additional 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from oven and with knife dipped in water, spread marshmallows evenly.
Let cool. Combine chocolate chips, peanut butter and 3 tablespoons oleo and cook over low heat, stirring constantly until melted and well blended.
Remove from heat and add rice cereal.
Spread over cake and cool completely.
Cut into squares.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Drain string beans.
In 2-quart casserole, layer ingredients in order.
Repeat with second cans.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes in oven at 425°.
Uncover and mix.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all together very well and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually whip in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into prepared crust.
Chill 3 hours.
Top with cherry pie filing.
Just before serving, refrigerate leftovers.

title: tex mex stir-fry
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon oil. Add broccoli, carrots, pepper and celery.

Stir-fry 3 minutes. Set aside. Add oil to hot skillet; fry shrimp 3 minutes. Return veggies to skillet. Pour in fajita sauce, brown sugar, ginger and mustard. Cook 2 minutes longer, tossing to blend. In hot skillet, stir-fry rice.
Serve shrimp and veggies over rice. Sprinkle with almonds.

title: quick chicken noodle soup
directions: Fill Dutch oven pot 3/4 full with water.
Put in spices and bouillon.
Cut up and put in onion and celery.
Bring to boil. Throw in leftover chicken (if chicken breast is uncooked, put in with onion and celery) and mixed vegetables.
Let cook on medium heat 15 to 20 minutes.
Put in flavor package from 1 of the Oodles of Noodles (not noodles).
Mix cornstarch with small amount cold water in separate bowl until smooth.
Turn heat up on high to boil.
Pour in starch mixture slowly while stirring soup.
Break up noodles while still in package.
Pour into soup.
Let cook another 3 minutes.
Serve.

title: oven chicken stew
directions: Cut up fryer and place in 2 or 3-quart casserole dish.
Mix soup, potatoes and onions with 2 cups water.
Pour over chicken. Cover with aluminum fol and bake in 400° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Drain shrimp and crumble. Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Chill for several hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach, then drain (very well).
Mix ingredients putting spinach in last.
Dump ingredients into middle of bread, saving the middle pieces for dipping.

title: nancy's chicken dip
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with the can of chicken and the chopped scallion onions.
Add seasoned pepper and garlic salt to taste.
Allow to chill in the refrigerator before serving with your favorite cracker.
A great dip for tailgating or parties!

title: chess squares
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over the crust.
Bake in a preheated oven at 325° about 1 hour.

title: grilled potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
Place slices on aluminum foil coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Spray potato slices with cooking spray or may brush with cooking oil.
Sprinkle with seasoning salt and pepper.
May use any spices.
Place on grill rack over medium-hot coals; cook 10 to 15 minutes, turning once.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Reserve 1 cup dry cake mix. In a large mixing bowl, combine remaining cake mix, 1 egg and oil (mixture will be crumbly).
Press crust mixture evenly onto bottom and 3/4 of the way up the sides of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and 3 teaspoons sugar.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 400°.
Cool.

title: lime punch
directions: Let sherbet sit until soft enough to mix with a big spoon. Place in punch bowl, then add ginger ale and club soda.
Stir gently until well blended, then serve.

title: caramel chow mein candy
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter over hot water.
Add noodles and marshmallows.
Stir and drop on waxed paper.

title: dip for veggies or crackers
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients in double boiler until thick.
Mix cream cheese, pimento and onion.
Add 2 mixtures and beat. Refrigerate and it thickens.
Serve with veggies or crackers.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat and drain fat.
Combine all ingredients and simmer approximately 30 minutes.

title: broccoli egg puff
directions: Spread cooked broccoli in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add flour, salt, baking powder, cottage cheese, Mozzarella and butter.
Mix well.
Stir in bacon and pour over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Do not overcook as it will be dry.

title: vernie's date loaf
directions: Combine dates, raisins, pecans and cracker crumbs.
Melt butter and marshmallows together on medium heat.
Pour over date mixture and mix well.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool for 1 hour, then cut into squares.

title: oh!  so good broiled hamburgers
directions: Mix and spread on small open face hamburger buns.
Broil; not too close to heat until done.

title: egg drop soup(from china)
directions: Bring the broth, chicken and water chestnuts to a boil.
Mix the cornstarch and water together.
Pour into soup, stirring constantly.
Mix in the eggs until set.
Serve hot.

title: aunt millie's calico beans
directions: Brown bacon and hamburger.
Add the rest of the ingredients. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate crescent bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Separate rolls into 2 large rectangles. Place dough into 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan (or a small cookie sheet).
Gently press dough to seal perforations.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Prepare
noodles according to package directions.
Cook ground beef,
onion, and pepper.	Add drained corn and tomato paste
to ground beef mixture and allow to simmer for about 10 minutes. Place
noodles in bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.	Pour ground
beef mixture over top of noodles.
Spread mushroom soup evenly over ground beef mixture, then completely cover
mixture with sliced cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: appetizer kebabs
directions: Combine in large bowl the mushrooms, cherry tomatoes, white vinegar, oil, garlic clove, marjoram, salt, sage, pepper and dry mustard.
Cover.
Marinate 12 to 48 hours in refrigerator.
Stir occasionally.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix pecans, raisins and cherries.
Add coconut, sugar and crumbs.
Add melted butter and shape into balls.
Dip into 12 ounces chocolate morsels melted with 1/2 block paraffin in a double boiler.
Put on waxed paper until set.
Keeps for months in a tight container.
Makes approximately 90 cookies.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain off fat.
Add onions.
Cook until onions are transparent.
Add chili mix, beans, salt and tomato sauce.
Stir well.
Cook over low heat until beans are cooked.

title: angel food delight cake
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Smucker's topping together and spread between layers.
Crunch candy bars in food processor and sprinkle on top.

title: sour cream squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Cover with 1/2 of the herb stuffing mix; set aside.
Mix together the squash, carrot, onion, soup and sour cream.

title: roadside potatoes
directions: Place hash brown potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In saucepan on stove, mix half and half, butter and salt.
Pour over potatoes. Sprinkle with 1 cup Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put sliced apples in a buttered casserole dish and mix dry ingredients separately; cut butter into mixture.
Mix dry mixture into apples.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot with whipped cream.

title: shrimp etouffee and hot rice
directions: Etouffee: Saute onion, bell pepper and celery in margarine until tender.
Put shrimp in and cook for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add cream of mushroom soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes and cook for 15 to 20 minutes on low to medium heat.
Serve on hot rice.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Blend together flour, lard, salt and water and bake for pie crust.
Slice peaches into pie shell.
Cook sugar and water and cornstarch until thick.
Cool and add peach or orange gelatin. Pour mixture over sliced peaches; add whipped topping on the top. Serves 6.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown celery and onion in oleo.
Add hamburger and fry until done, stirring often.
Drain.
Heat kidney beans, tomato juice and soup.
Add hamburger mixture and chili powder.
Cook altogether well, until celery is tender.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onion with 1/2 stick butter.
Add 3 cups water and chicken bouillon cubes; boil.
Add the noodles; cook 5 minutes. Add broccoli; cook 5 minutes.
Add milk and cheese.
Don't boil again.
Easy to make and good to eat!

title: fudge brownies
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
Bake in greased and floured pan for 25 minutes at 300°.
Ice in pan with Fudge Frosting.
(I double recipe and put in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 35 minutes.)

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix well and shape into 2 balls.
Roll in 1 1/2 to 2 cups chopped pecans.
Can be frozen.

title: omelette for two
directions: Place butter in a 9-inch microproof pie plate and place in oven.
Combine eggs, water, salt and pepper; beat lightly with fork.
Pour into heated pie plate and cook for 60 seconds. Sprinkle with cheese and cook 1 1/2 minutes.
Fold and cut in half and serve immediately.

title: chicken fajitas("easy")
directions: Salt, pepper and season strips.
Fry in skillet in 2 tablespoons oil until tender.
Warm tortilla shells as per package directions.
Place strips of chicken on shells; top with choice of lettuce, tomato, onion or sour cream.

title: eggs mexicana
directions: Scramble eggs (with milk), bell pepper, onion and olives. Have ready crushed chips, cheese and salsa.
Mix with scrambled eggs 2 minutes, until blended.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with pint of sour cream.
Return to oven to warm.

title: vanilla cupcakes
directions: Mix everything together, pour batter into a pot.
Put the pot in a 400° oven for 100 minutes and then take it out when the bell rings.
Scoop them off the pan and eat them.

title: delmonico nut cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and egg yolks.
In a separate bowl, sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture gradually, alternating with buttermilk.
Fold in pecans.
Add vanilla.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into well-greased Bundt pan and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: broccoli cheese squares(spinach, too)
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Steam broccoli about 3 minutes. Cool and press dry. Beat eggs and milk until frothy.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add to egg mixture, mixing well. Fold in broccoli, cheese, margarine and onion. Spread evenly into prepared dish.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until lightly browned and set.
Let stand 5 minutes. Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
These freeze well. Yields 3 to 4 dozen.

title: lasagna in a bun
directions: Cut thin slices off tops of rolls. Hollow out centers, leaving 1/2-inch thick shells; set aside.

title: wild rice and chicken supreme
directions: Cook rice per package directions only until thawed.
Melt butter in large saucepan.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Add chicken broth and milk; heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in rice, chicken, mushrooms, green pepper, pimiento and almonds.
Turn mixture into greased 13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish (or casserole).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until mixture is bubbly.
Serves 10.

title: fruit, nut and turkey salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, yogurt, curry, salt and pepper.
Add turkey, pineapple, grapes, celery and walnuts.
Mix thoroughly and serve on lettuce.
Sprinkle with coconut if desired.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: open faced strawberry pie
directions: Mix and cook to a boil.
Remove from heat and add 3 tablespoons strawberry jello.
Slice berries into baked pie crust and pour sauce over all.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In a saucepan, cook onions in hot oil until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Use on anything you want barbecue sauce on.

title: southern banana pudding
directions: Combine pudding mix, egg yolks and milk in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat.
Bring to full boil.
Remove from heat. Arrange layer of Nilla wafers on bottom and sides of 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Add layer of banana slices and of pudding.
Continue layering, ending with pudding.
Beat egg whites and salt until foamy.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Beat to form stiff, shiny peaks. Spread lightly over pudding, sealing edges well.
Bake at 425° for 5 to 10 minutes until lightly browned.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: chocolate-pecan pie
directions: Use 1 deep or 2 shallow pie crusts (I use 2).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: bouillabaisse de marseille
directions: In a soup kettle, saute onion and garlic in olive oil until golden.
Add tomatoes, parsley, bay leaf, thyme, fennel, saffron and ground pepper.
Simmer for
a few minutes and add lobsters and fish.
Cut the fish, carefully cleaned and the lobsters, live, into 2-inch pieces.
Put the coarser fleshed fish in the kettle first, then the lobsters, then the rest of the fish.
Add the dry white wine and boiling water just to cover the fish.
Bring the liquid back to a boil and cook the bouillabaisse, covered, over very high heat for 15 minutes.
Add mussels, thoroughly scrubbed, 6 minutes before cooking time is up.
Serve in soup plates, from a tureen, with sliced French bread spread with garlic butter and toasted.
Serves 8.

title: easter breakfast bake
directions: Place cubed bread in bottom of well-greased baking dish (8 x 12-inch or 9 x 13-inch).
Top with grated cheese, sausage and mushrooms.
Beat eggs with 2 1/2 cups milk and mustard.
Pour milk mixture over bread, sausage, cheese, etc.
Refrigerate overnight (up to 2 days).
When ready to bake, dilute soup with milk and pour over mixture.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 75 minutes, until set.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: aunt mary's tamales
directions: Mix together hamburger, sausage, chili powder, cayenne and salt.
Make into small 1/2 x 2-inch servings.
Combine cornmeal and water to form a mixture that does not stick to hands.
Scoop up enough mixture to cover meat serving.
Roll in tamale papers, which have been softened in water.
Tie with string in middle. Drop into boiling water and cook for 35 minutes.
Serve with chili or alone with mustard.
Yield:
25 tamales.

title: quick hamburger
directions: Combine all ingredients, brown on both sides.
Serve on bun with mustard and ketchup.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Cut baked potatoes lengthwise and scoop out inside.
Mash and add rest of ingredients.
Whip until light and fluffy.
Pile into potato shells.
Sprinkle with paprika and a few shreds of grated cheese.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes until brown.

title: dilled green beans
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in water over medium heat.
Add onion, dill, sugar and pepper.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add beans and cook 8 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: *Can use self-rising flour but delete salt, soda, and powder.

title: mashed turnips
directions: Wash, pare and cut turnips into pieces.
Cook turnips in boiling salted water until fork-tender; drain well.
Mash turnips or put through a ricer.
Add sugar and a large pat of butter. Season to taste with salt and pepper and add a little cream.
Beat until turnips are smooth.

title: spinach balls
directions: Thaw spinach, squeezing any excess liquid from spinach.
Mix all ingredients together; chill for 2 hours.
Mold into balls the size of large walnuts.
Bake for 30 minutes at 300°.

title: cheese squares florentine
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder in a large bowl.
Add eggs, milk, butter, cheese and onion.
Squeeze excess moisture from spinach and add to cheese mixture.
Mix well.

title: baked ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Butter 4 slices of bread and put in pan, buttered side down. Sprinkle with ham and cheese.
Top with other 4 slices of bread. Pour egg, milk and mustard mixture over all and let stand 1 or more hours.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes until top is browned.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake the yellow cake on a cookie sheet.
While the cake is cooking, boil sugar and pineapple for 5 minutes.
Pour over baked cake while cake is warm.
Cool cake completely.

title: rolls
directions: Mix yeast, water, margarine, sugar and egg.
Add flour and stir well.
(Dough will be soft)
Fill muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake 15 minutes in 400° oven.
May be kept in refirgerator and used as needed.
Do not have to rise.

title: cherry salad
directions: Dissolve cherry Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water with cream cheese (I use blender).
Add 2 cups cold liquid using pineapple juice, cherry juice and water.
Add crushed pineapple, nuts and cherries.
Put in mold and refrigerate.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except flour well.
Add flour.
Cook at 350° until done.
Makes 2 loaf pans.

title: roasted garlic artichoke dip
directions: Drain the artichoke hearts pressing out any excess moisture. Coarsely chop the artichokes and place in mixing bowl.
Mince roasted garlic and add to artichokes.
Add mayonnaise and cheese. Coat with oil a 1-2 quart, refrigerate to oven safe ceramic baking dish.

title: polet etouffee(smothered chicken)
directions: Pour oil into deep pot (crock-pot) on low-medium heat.
Wash meat and put into hot oil.
Cover meat with onions, then peppers, parsley, celery, Worcestershire and bitters.
Be sure ingredients get inside chicken also.
Sprinkle Tabasco around on meat.
Add garlic, then salt.

title: ribbon cookies(rich's cookies)
directions: Cream butter and sugar, beating well.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, salt and baking powder; mix well.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Measure and place all ingredients, except chocolate chips, in mixing bowl.
Blend well with spoon.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips evenly across top of brownies. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Let cool before cutting into squares.

title: crock-pot greens and corn bread
directions: Salt and pepper the greens to taste. Cook greens down in crock-pot with bacon grease. Fix cornbread batter, then pour over greens. Cover and cook until cornbread is almost done.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Cover first 5 ingredients in salt water.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Drain off water.
Mix with the remaining ingredients.
Put in freezer cups and freeze.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Combine other ingredients except cracker crumbs.
Then mix with broccoli.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Top with cheese cracker crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: vegetable-stuffed peppers
directions: In a large bowl, combine the tomatoes, beans, rice, 1 1/2 cups of cheese, corn, onion, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder, pepper and salt; mix well. Remove and discard tops and seeds of green peppers. Fill each pepper with about 1 cup of the vegetable mixture. Place in a 5-quart slow cooker. Cover and cook on low for 8 hours. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Cover and cook 15 minutes longer or until peppers are tender and cheese is melted. Yields 6 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces. Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Roll each piece of biscuit in sugar and cinnamon.
Grease tube pan. Place biscuit around bottom of pan (evenly 3 to 4 layers).
If any sugar or cinnamon is left, pour over top of biscuit.
Pour melted margarine over top of everything.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: venison stew
directions: Soak venison overnight in milk.
Drain venison and dip in flour and Creole seasoning.
Drop in hot cooking oil and brown lightly.
Add onions and bell pepper, chopped.
Simmer, then add tomato sauce, tomatoes, carrots, potatoes and enough water to cover.
Cook slowly until potatoes are tender.
Serve over rice.

title: crabbies
directions: Cream butter, cheese spread and mayonnaise together; add seasonings and crab meat and blend well.
Spread on muffins; freeze 10 minutes.
Broil 6 to 8 inches from broiler for 5 to 8 minutes, until bubbly.
Cut each muffin into 6 wedges.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix in order and serve.

title: baked potato slims
directions: Mix water with oil and Tabasco.
Peel 4 Idaho potatoes and cut into 1/2-inch strips or use unthawed frozen French fries. Toss potatoes with Shake 'n Bake in a bag.
Place 8 to 10 strips at a time in bag and shake until evenly coated.
Place potatoes in single layer on cookie sheet lined with foil.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 to 35 minutes (20 to 25 minutes for frozen ones).

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream cheese until soft.
Add sugar, a little at a time, creaming thoroughly.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Enough for 1 loaf cake.

title: bean-macaroni soup
directions: Heat oil in 6-quart kettle.
Drain beans.
Add mushrooms and vegetables; saute 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and spices.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Cook macaroni; drain.
Add beans and water to make 4 cups cooked macaroni.
Bring to boil; cover and simmer until hot. Makes 16 servings.

title: strawberry angel food torte
directions: Mix jello
with hot water and stir to dissolve.
Chill, but do not
let
jell.
Mix pineapple, coconut, pecans, sugar and strawberries
with
jello
and let this mixture jell some. Break angel
food cake into bite sized pieces and layer in the bottom of a
large
bowl.
Next spoon jello mixture over cake and continue alternating layers until mix used.
Top with Cool Whip and chill.

title: southern dumplings
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt in a bowl.
Put softened margarine on top of dry ingredients.
Pour boiling water on top.
Mix well.	Roll into a ball like pie dough.
Put in refrigerator until needed.	Cut into diamond or squares.
Drop into boiling broth.
Cook half; cover 20 minutes.
Let stand another 20 minutes.
Before serving, use large pot and plenty of broth.
Good warmed over.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix all together and cook in double boiler until thick.
Cool slightly before putting in pie shell.
Mix 2 tablespoons sugar with beaten egg whites and spread on top and brown in a slow oven about 350°.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Put in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: brownies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat sugar into eggs. Mix in Wesson oil, chocolate and vanilla.
Add flour all at once. Mix well.
Add nuts.
Turn into oiled pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 20 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes, then turn out on rack to cool.
Cut into 16 squares.

title: cheese strata
directions: Cube bread and cheese.
Put layer of bread and cheese until you use it all.
Beat eggs; add milk and pour over cheese and bread.
Bake for 30 minutes or until bubbly in 350° oven.

title: brandied fruit
directions: Every 2 weeks add 2 cups fruit and 2 cups sugar.
Stir occasionally.

title: rhubarb jello salad
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cook until tender.
Stir in 1 package jello (any red; we like strawberry best).
Then add 1/2 cup cold water. Place in refrigerator until set.

title: tony's tiger bites
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter until mixture is smooth.
Add cereal, stirring until well coated.
Press mixture into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: apple pie toast
directions: Make a slice of toast and butter the top.
Spoon on applesauce and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Run under broiler long enough to warm applesauce.
Remove and top with a slice of cheese.
Run back under broiler long enough for cheese to melt.

title: depression dinner
directions: Mix beef, carrots, onion, potatoes, eggs, garlic, salt and pepper.
Divide and form into 14 patties.
Wrap a slice of bacon around edge of each; secure with toothpicks.
Broil or grill both sides to desired doneness.
Remove picks.
Garnish with parsley. Makes 14 servings.

title: missouri cookies(cow plops)
directions: First gather and measure all ingredients.
Mix together in large saucepan:
milk, margarine, sugar and cocoa.
Stirring constantly over medium heat, bring to a rolling boil.
Let boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and peanut butter.
Pour mixture over the oats and stir until blended.

title: heavenly christmas marmalade
directions: Soak apricots overnight in enough water to cover.
The next day cook until soft enough to crush with a spoon.
Add crushed pineapple, drained and cut up cherries, orange juice and sugar.

title: grits casserole
directions: Bring milk to boil; add grits.
Cook over medium heat until thickened (8 to 10 minutes), stirring occasionally.
Add butter, roll of cheese and salt.
Stir until melted.
Beat 2 eggs; add 1/2 cup milk and add grits mixture.
Pour into well buttered casserole. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top and bake 15 minutes more.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chips in
thick-bottomed
saucepan
over low heat. Add peanuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto brown paper.

title: party potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover.
Chill several hours to blend flavors.
Makes 4 cups.

title: sourdough calamata olive bread
directions: To Make By Hand:
Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water. After yeast mixture foams up, add other liquid ingredients, followed by olives, salt and whole wheat flour.
Mix well.
Add bread flour, mixing until stiff.
Turn out on floured board and knead in the rest of the bread flour.
Allow to rise in a warm, draft-free location until doubled in bulk, then knead again.
At the end of the dough cycle or second hand kneading, shape the dough by hand into a round loaf.
Allow to rise in a warm, draft-free location on a baking sheet sprayed with nonstick spray (or lightly oiled) until doubled in bulk.
To bake, brush the loaf with water. Slash a couple of times with a sharp knife and place in preheated 375° oven above a pan of boiling water for about 35 minutes.

title: christmas bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Butter large bowl; set aside. Butter an 8-inch round cake pan. Line inside of pan with double layer of heavy-duty foil so that foil extends 2-inches above top edge. Secure ends with paper clips. Butter inside of foil.

title: curry chicken salad with artichokes
directions: Cook chicken and cut up in bite size pieces.
Make Rice-A-Roni according to package directions and cool.
Combine chicken, rice, onions, pepper, artichoke hearts, mayonnaise, curry powder, salt and pepper.
Mix well; put in pan and refrigerate overnight to blend flavors and enhance taste.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: cranberry butter spread
directions: Whip everything together until light pink.
Add buttermilk last.
This is great on hot rolls or bread.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix by hand, cake mix, eggs, oil and sour cream.
Pour 1/2 batter into greased 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon over batter.
Spread remaining batter over this.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Mix xxx with warm water.
While cake is still hot, cover completely with xxx sugar and water mixture.

title: enchiladas de pollo
directions: Place chicken breasts in a large pot or Dutch oven.
Add water to cover onion, bay leaf, peppercorns and salt to taste.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes or until tender.
(Or do this in about 15 minutes in the microwave.)
Cool chicken in broth.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix apples and salt.
Sift flour, soda and cinnamon.
Beat eggs, sugar and Wesson oil.
Mix with flour mixture and apples. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch glass pan.

title: country corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 500°.
Melt 1/3 cup bacon in an 8-inch iron skillet until the grease is melted and skillet is hot.
Stir until all dry ingredients are blended.
Add 1 egg and 3/4 cup sweet milk.
Stir until well blended.
Add melted grease, leaving about 1/8-inch of grease in skillet.
Pour in mixture and cook for about 15 to 20 minutes until brown.

title: lime cottage cheese pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice; fill with water to 1 cup.
Bring to a boil; pour over jello.
Add marshmallows and allow to dissolve. Cool.
When it begins to set add other ingredients, folding in whipped cream.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts (salt) until tender.
Remove from broth (save broth) and let cool.
Pull chicken from bone and break into bite-size pieces.
Put chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix soup and chicken broth.
Pour over chicken.
Mix cornbread stuffing mix with melted margarine and enough broth to make crumbled mixture.
Spread over chicken mixture.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pepper steak
directions: Pound flour and salt into steak with meat mallet.
Cut into serving size pieces; brown in shortening in large skillet.
Remove meat pieces to platter.
Saute green pepper and onion.
Stir in pimento, applesauce, Worcestershire sauce and bouillon.
Add meat; cover and simmer 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve with rice or noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: honey barbecue drumettes
directions: Batter chicken in flour, salt and pepper; fry as usual.
Then mix honey and barbecue together; dip fried chicken in sauce. Layer in 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Broil in 425° oven until brown. Serves 8 people.

title: hot and spicy fried potatoes
directions: Spray nonstick skillet with Pam.
Saute potatoes and onion together until tender and golden brown.
Season with salt, black pepper and cayenne pepper to taste.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Melt Jell-O.
Add sherbet and mix well. Stir in pineapple and oranges. Chill before serving.

title: barbecue sauce for beef brisket and wild game
directions: Mix; pour over brisket or wild game.
Bake 3 hours at 350°.

title: pigeon peas and rice
directions: Fry the bacon in a skillet until crisp.
Stir-fry onion and bell pepper until done.
Add tomatoes; cover and allow to simmer for 45 minutes.
Pour 5 cups of water into cooked tomato mixture. Add remaining seasonings, along with rice; simmer until done.

title: green bean appetizers
directions: Remove crusts from bread (save crusts for bread crumb toppings).
Flatten bread with finger tips or rolling pin.
Spread generously with dip.
Lay three whole beans on edge of slice of bread, roll up and roll in melted butter.
Arrange about 1 inch apart on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 12 minutes at 400°.
Yields 8 servings.

title: mrs. montgomery's pineapple drop cookies
directions: Cream butter, honey or sugar, egg and add in salt (if desired), lemon juice, pineapple, flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake until done, 10 to 12 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: peach dumplings
directions: Sift flour.
Measure and sift with baking powder, salt and sugar. Cut in shortening and add milk. Turn into lightly floured board. Roll in sheet 1/4-inch thick.
Cut in 4-inch squares. Place 1/2 cup thinly sliced peaches in each square.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Dot with butter.
Moisten edges of dough.
Press lightly together. Place in baking pan. Bake in hot oven at 425° for about 35 minutes.

title: mango custard pie
directions: Prepare custard by mixing together ingredients; beating eggs separately and adding them last.
Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry and bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and fill with prepared custard mixture.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake for 30 minutes or until done.

title: easy skillet dinner
directions: Slice or cut up all vegetables and put in skillet with a little oil in it.
Cook slowly until all vegetables are tender or done.
Turn occasionally to keep from sticking or burning.
Use lid to steam and they will cook faster.
Use as many of each vegetable as you like.
Makes delicious summer meal served with cornbread.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Fry bacon crisp and drain on paper towel.
Then crumble. Break broccoli into small pieces.
Combine bacon, onion and broccoli.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil potato with skin on.
Peel and mash while hot.
Add butter and vanilla at once.
Add 1 pound powdered sugar gradually while potato is still hot, as long as mixture will absorb. Mixture will be stiff.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar well.
Bring to a boil the oleo, oil, cocoa and water.
Pour over sugar and flour and blend.
Add buttermilk, soda, vanilla and eggs.
Blend well.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Use large sheet cake pan.

title: four-day coconut cake
directions: For
icing,
combine sour cream, sugar and frozen coconut. Mix
and
leave covered overnight in refrigerator.
Next day, make up cake mix and bake two layers according to package directions. Split each layer, making four layers in all.
Ice with
icing mixture between layers and top, but not on sides. Seal
in covered cake container and refrigerate 4 days before serving. Cake absorbs the icing, which is slightly liquid.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Brown sausage in large pot; drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients and cook 45 minutes.
Makes a large amount and freezes well.

title: goldie's cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Drop by spoon onto baking sheet.

title: cheese delight
directions: Mix pineapple and marshmallows and let set 2 hours or until the marshmallows are softened.
Mix together until creamy, cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Whip double cream.
Mix pineapple marshmallows mixture with cheese and mayonnaise mixture.
Fold lightly until blended well, then add cherries and nutmeats. Freeze until set before using.
Freeze on quick freeze.
Don't stir.
This is delicious.

title: fresh mushroom soup
directions: Saute mushrooms in margarine until tender.
Mix in chicken broth.
Add lemon juice, Vermouth, sherry and Tabasco sauce.
Heat until warm.
Makes 5 (1-cup) servings.

title: baked brie
directions: Mix brown sugar, walnuts and brandy.
(You store this mixture in a jar for a week or so.)
Put Brie on pie plate into 500° oven for 4 to 5 minutes, until soft.
Sprinkle mixture on top of Brie and bake 2 to 3 minutes more until sugar is melted.
Serve with apple wedges, grapes or crackers.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Put flour, salt and pepper in a plastic bag with chicken. Shake to coat chicken well.
Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: In a pan, place sugar, butter, milk and cocoa.
Stir over medium heat. Boil 1 1/2 minutes. Add peanut butter, oatmeal, vanilla and raisins.
Mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper. Cool.

title: pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 420°.
In large mixing bowl, combine two cups flour, yeast, and salt.
Stir in water, egg, and oil.
Beat at low speed with mixer for 30 seconds, scraping sides of bowl.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
By hand, stir in enough flour to make a moderately stiff dough.
Put onto floured surface and knead until smooth (about 5 minutes).
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to coat dough.
Cover, and let rise until size doubles (about one hour).
Divide dough into two portions.
Place each portion on greased pizza pan.
Spread dough out to pan edges.
Top with tomato sauce and cheese, and bake 25 minutes.

title: crisp sweet slaw
directions: Mix all vegetables.
Whisk together the vinegar, apple juice, oil, Sweet 'N Low, celery seed, dry mustard, salt and pepper. Pour over vegetables; toss to coat.
Refrigerate until served. Makes 8 servings.

title: sangria for a crowd
directions: In a large kettle, combine water and sugar; heat until dissolved.
Add sliced fruits.
Let stand at room temperature at least 4 hours.

title: easy rice pudding
directions: Cook pudding as directed on package.
When done, add vanilla, cooked rice and raisins.
Cool.
Put into serving dishes and sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon.
Makes 6 1/2 cups.

title: pasta with broccoli or cauliflower
directions: Cook broccoli or cauliflower according to directions.
Drain. In large pot, melt butter.
Add mushrooms, parsley, broccoli or cauliflower, salt, pepper and half and half.
Add cooked and drained pasta.
Remove from heat.
Add the 2 cups freshly grated Parmesan cheese.
Mix until half and half has been absorbed.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender, then drain well.
Mix in diced oleo and cheese; turn into baking dish.
Top with 1/2 to 1 stick melted oleo and 1 1/2 roll package crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Recipe can be cut in half for smaller versions.
Large one good for buffet.

title: cherry glazed pork roast
directions: Place roast on rack in shallow roasting pan.
Cook uncovered in 325°
oven for 2 1/2 hours or until meat thermometer registers 170°.

title: watermelon pickles
directions: Peel rind off watermelon; leave a trace of pink on inside for color.
Cut rind into pieces.
Let stand overnight in cold water in aluminum pan.
Drain well.
Bring 4 ingredients to a boil; add watermelon rind and bring back to a boil again; set aside until next morning.
Bring mixture to a boil; set aside.
Third morning, bring to a boil; seal in hot, sterilized jars.
Hot water bath for 10 minutes.
Makes about 7 pints.

title: bread pudding
directions: In a medium bowl, mix first 6 ingredients and set aside.
In a medium pan mix next 4 ingredients and heat on top of stove until hot but do not boil.
Pour slowly into first mixture, mixing well. Then pour into a 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Place the dish into a larger pan with some water in it.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: jennifer's pinch me cake
directions: Mix together sugar, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Melt margarine. Pinch off small pieces of biscuits and dip in butter.
Dip in sugar mixture.
Layer these on a biscuit pan.
Bake according to the directions on the biscuit label or until golden brown.
Pinch off a piece and enjoy!

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook and chop chicken.
Cook Rice-A-Roni according to package directions (using oil, not butter) and cool.
Mix all ingredients with dressing and chill.
Serve on a bed of bibb lettuce.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: quick and easy cookies
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Beat eggs and add oil and vanilla.
Add this to first mixture.
Roll into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press out with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 400°.

title: three-bean casserole
directions: Drain kidney beans and string beans.
Do not drain pork and beans.
Mix
together.
Brown
bacon
and onion and add to bean mixture.
Add
rest
of ingredients and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: pie dough dumplings
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in oil.
Add water to form dough.
Roll on lightly floured board and cut into 2-inch squares. Cook in boiling chicken or beef broth for 12 minutes, uncovered.

title: fudge
directions: Boil milk, sugar and oleo 7 minutes; get rolling boil.
Stir in peanut butter and chocolate chips; add nuts and vanilla.
Makes large batch.

title: holiday frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberry sauce with juice of 1 lemon; spread mixture in an 8 x 8-inch pan, dish or tray.
Sprinkle half of the chopped pecans on top of mixture.

title: jello
directions: Drain syrup; leave slices in can.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; pour over pineapple slices.
Chill 3 hours.
To unmold, dip can in hot water.
Cut out bottom and push mold out, then slice into slices.

title: granny's coconut cake
directions: ALL INGREDIENTS MUST BE AT ROOM TEMPERATURE!!

title: blue fish imperial
directions: Bake fillets in a preheated oven at 325° for 20 minutes.
Coat with about 1/4 inch of mayonnaise and sprinkle seasoning on top to suit your taste.
Return to oven and broil for about 5 minutes or until golden brown.

title: minnie mouse's tropical treat
directions: Put 1 pineapple ring in each of 4 dessert dishes.
Place 1 scoop sherbet on top of each pineapple ring.
Sprinkle coconut over sherbet; top with cherry on each.
Serves 4.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil, eggs and sugar; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients, except apples and nuts.
Add apples and nuts last. Bake in a Bundt pan (greased and floured) at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: party mix
directions: Melt butter.
Add salt, Worcestershire sauce, pour over Rice Chex, pretzels, nuts.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Place shredded cabbage in a large, deep pot.
Combine sugar, vinegar and water in a bowl.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over cabbage.
Sprinkle salt and pepper to taste.
Add bacon grease; heat to boiling.
Cover and turn heat down to simmer. Cook on low for 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove cover and cook until liquid is cooked down.

title: macaroni and lentil soup(makrooni rahwa)
directions: Wash lentils.
Cook Cover lentils with water and bring to a boil.
Then cook for 15 mins.
Saute onion and garlic in oil until browned.
Add tomato paste, water and seasoning.
Blend well and bring to a boil.
When lentils are soft, add tomato sauce mixture and macaroni.
Bring to a boil.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Bake at 350° until heated through and top is browned; about 25 to 30 minutes.
Tip:
Can prepare the day before and refrigerate.

title: lemon flounder bake
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart saucepan over medium heat.
Cook celery, green pepper strips and onion until tender.
Stir in tomato soup and lemon juice.
Spoon 1/2 cup sauce in shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Arrange fish fillets in single layer over sauce; cover with remaining sauce.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, or until sauce is bubbling and fish flakes easily with a fork.
Garnish with celery slices, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in a casserole dish in order:
soup, broccoli (bite size pieces) and cheese.
Repeat layers until ingredients are gone.
Top with prepared Stove Top stuffing.
Bake covered approximately 30 to 45 minutes at 350° until bubbly.

title: zucchini-tomato casserole
directions: Be careful in your selection.
Do not choose too young and select only those that have been reared in a good moral atmosphere. Some keep them in a pickle, others keep them in hot water.
This only makes them sour, harsh and sometimes bitter.
Even poor selections may be made sweet, tender and good by garnishing them with patience, well sweetened smiles and flavored with kisses to taste.
Then wrap them in a mantle of charity.
Keep warm with a steady fire of domestic devotion, then serve with peaches and cream.
When thus prepared, they will keep for years.

title: delicious lemon pie
directions: Mix together and put in graham cracker crust.
Chill.
Keep refrigerated.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Place all in bowl except nuts. Microwave 1/2 power until chips melt (3 to 5 minutes). Stir in nuts. Pour into well greased 8 X 8 dish. Refrigerate until set.

title: el paso chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix soup, milk and chilies in medium saucepan and heat.
Line a greased 3-quart casserole dish with tortilla pieces and add onion, chicken, soup mixture and cheese.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix and bake in 9-inch square pan at 400° for 30 minutes, or until done.

title: glazed pineapple cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350. Drain pineapple reserving juice. Blend cream cheese, sugar, eggs, and 1/2 tsp. vanilla. Stir in 1/2 cup pineapple and pour into crust. bake 25 - 30 minutes or until center is set. Cool. Combine reserved juice with cornstarch and cook 3-4 minutes or until thickened and translucent. Stir in remaining vanilla and cool slightly. Pour over pie. Arrange remaining pineapple around edge of pie. Chill.

title: cajun chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees.

Heat chicken in 10-inch nonstick skillet over medium heat for 2 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in bell pepper and onion; cook about 4 minutes, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are slightly crisp.
Spoon into ungreased 13x9x2-inch baking dish.
Stir in tomatoes, soup and seasoning.
Stir remaining ingredients in medium bowl until blended.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: meatballs sweet and sour
directions: Combine eggs, flour, salt and pepper.
Dip walnut-sized meatballs in and brown in skillet with hot oil.
Remove meatballs. Keep warm.
Pour all but 1 tablespoon of fat.
Add pineapple (diced).
Cover and cook over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and thickens.
Add meatballs.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: snip doodle(easy coffee cake)
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in order given. Pour into small greased and floured cake pan. Sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon over top. Dot with margarine.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: chop suey casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain off grease.
Add all the ingredients except the chow mein noodles into a casserole dish.
Stir well and cover.
Place in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Remove the cover and sprinkle the chow mein noodles on top.
Bake 15 more minutes until noodles turn a golden brown.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Scrub zucchini.
Cut each lengthwise 4 times, then chop.
Chop celery and tops and onions.
Put in pot with broth.
Cook until zucchini, onions and celery are done, about 20 minutes.
Add chicken bouillon cubes, pepper and curry powder.
Put in blender and zap it.
Add sour cream, zap again.
Sprinkle with chives when served hot or cold.

title: filled cookie turnovers
directions: Mix the shortening, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Stir in cream and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients except preserves and stir well.
Chill dough for 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400°.
Roll out dough to 1/16-inch thickness.
Using a cookie cutter, cut 2 for each turnover.
On lightly greased baking sheet, place 1 piece of dough.
Place a rounded teaspoonful of preserves and top with another piece of dough.
Pinch edges.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick of margarine in pan.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 2 cups graham cracker crumbs.
Mix and spread in 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at medium temperature (350°) for 5 minutes.
(Watch; will burn easy.)
Let cool.
Combine sugar, cream cheese and remainder of margarine.
Mix well.
Pour over cooled crust.
Drain pineapple and spoon over cheese mixture.
Slice bananas and lay over pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over bananas.
Swirl with chocolate syrup.
Top with peanuts and cherries.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: chocolate chippers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat oil and sugars. Add eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Add flour and baking soda.
Mix well.
Stir in cereal and chocolate chips. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 12 to 15 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix all but chocolate chips and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt chocolate chips and pour on top of mixture.
Refrigerate until set.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine the cream cheese, pepper, onion, salt, 1 cup pecans and pineapple.
Chill.
Form mixture into a ball and roll in additional chopped pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage into large iron skillet.
Cover cabbage with water.
Add enough bacon grease to flavor.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook on medium heat.
When water cooks out, keep adding until cabbage is tender.
Then fry cabbage until slightly browned!

title: holiday fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips with condensed milk slowly.
Stir occasionally until melted and mixture begins to thicken.
Remove from heat.
Add chopped nuts and vanilla.
Blend well.
Spoon into petit fours cups and chill or chill fudge for 1 hour to thicken.
