Pour fudge in pie pan lined with whole walnuts and shape into a ring.
Chill until firm and cut into slices.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13 baking dish, place chicken parts.
Add rice. Cover with heated soup mixture.
(Heat soups, oleo, water to pour over chicken rice.)
Bake at 275° for 3 hours.
May need to add water.

title: turtle cake
directions: Make cake mix as directed.
Pour half in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes; do not overbake.
Melt caramels and margarine until smooth. Add Eagle Brand and mix well.
Pour on cake.
Pour rest of mix over caramels. Top with chips and nuts. Bake about 1/2 hour.

title: italian wedding soup
directions: Mix ground chuck, garlic, 1/2 cup water, parsley, bread crumbs, 1 onion (chopped) and 2 eggs.
Make very small meatballs!! Boil chicken, salt and onion until tender.
Remove chicken from broth.
Chill broth and chicken separately.
Skim fat from broth when cooled down.
Cut chicken into pieces.
Return broth to a boil.
Drop in meatballs and cook 15 minutes.
Add pieces of chicken and endive.
Cook 10 minutes more.
Last, mix cheese and 3 eggs; add to soup.
Cook 10 minutes more.
Enjoy!!

title: caramel icing
directions: Melt margarine (or butter). Stir in firmly packed brown sugar and a pinch of salt. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes. Add milk. Stir constantly until mixture comes to a boil. Remove from heat. Stir in gradually sifted powdered sugar. Add vanilla and mix well. If too thick, add more milk.

title: calico beans
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet and sour cabbage soup
directions: Brown beef and add salt and pepper to taste.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook 2 hours on simmer after bringing to boil or cook all day in crock-pot.

title: foiled orange roughy
directions: Place each fillet on a piece of aluminum foil.
Put potatoes into microwave-safe dish (covered) and cook on High for 3 to 5 minutes.
Then top each fillet with 1/2 of the potatoes, carrots, green beans, onion and margarine.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Fold the foil into a packet, covering all ingredients and bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Test fish with fork to make sure it is cooked thoroughly.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: In skillet, brown beef in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Set aside. In same skillet, add remaining margarine and cook mushrooms and onion until tender.
Return meat to skillet.
Add water and A.1. Heat to boil.
Reduce to low and simmer 50 to 60 minutes until tender.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve over noodles.

title: instead of frying fish(4 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 500 (no mistake).
Cut fish into serving size pieces.
Place milk in a shallow bowl.
In another shallow bowl, combine chips, parmesan cheese and thyme.
Dip fish in milk, then coat with potato chip mixture.
Sprinkle a greased 8-inch square pan with bread crumbs.
Place fish over crumbs; drizzle with butter.
Bake uncovered at 500 for 12-14 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.

title: strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Add fruit and mix well.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Spoon into pastry filled pie plate.
Dot with margarine.
Add top crust.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: mom's chili mac
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and celery together; drain grease. In a soup kettle, add together the meat, kidney beans, juice, 1/3 can of water and cooked macaroni and chili powder.
Cook, covered, on low heat until soup thickens.

title: shrimp beignets
directions: Cook shrimp; drain.
Put through meat grinder.
Set aside. Boil water.
Add butter, salt, celery salt and pepper.
When butter is melted, add flour all at once; stir well and remove from heat.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Grate onion into batter and add shrimp.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Then fry in spoonfuls in oil until golden.
Serve hot.

title: chicken and crab casserole
directions: Place chicken, crab meat and mushrooms in a casserole dish. Mix soups and add seasoning and pour over mixture in casserole dish.
Cook for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients; cut in Crisco.
Add buttermilk.
Stir 12 to 15 times; knead on a floured board and roll thick.
Cut into biscuits and place on a greased pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 450°.

title: stuffed celery stalks
directions: In small bowl, blend first 4 ingredients.
Stuff celery pieces.
Sprinkle with peanuts.
Chill.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: rainbow milk
directions: Pour 2 cups of milk in pie pan.
Drop 2 or 3 drops of food coloring anywhere in the milk.
Squeeze some detergent (1 to 2 tablespoons) in at the side.
As the detergent displaces the milk fat the colors run and swirl together.
(You can add additional color and detergent.)

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven
to
Wash
tomatoes
and cut a thin slice off top.
Scoop out pulp into a bowl.
Mix pulp, 1/2 cup bread crumbs, seasonings and green onion.
Place tomato shells in an 8-inch
square
pan
or
a pie pan. Divide pulp mixture evenly between the tomatoes, placing in hollow carefully.	Mix melted margarine
with
remaining	1/4
cup
bread crumbs and sprinkle on	top
of
tomatoes.
Bake for 25 minutes or until tomatoes
are tender, then sprinkle grated Parmesan cheese (if you like) on top of tomatoes while still hot.

title: s'mores
directions: You take the graham crackers and roast the marshmallow and put the chocolate on the graham crackers and stuff.

title: pineapple slush
directions: Freeze in metal pan.
Once starting to freeze on sides and top, remove from freezer and stir.
Return to freezer.
Mix with ginger ale or Mountain Dew.

title: crustless custard
directions: Put all ingredients into blender (except nutmeg); blend on high speed one minutes. Pour into glass or ceramic pan. Lightly sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake at 325 degrees for 50 minutes.

title: yogurt dessert
directions: Place mixed
Cool
Whip
and yogurt in baking pie shell (pastry,
graham cracker crumb or pretzel).
Top with favorite fruit (optional).

title: candy critters
directions: On wax paper-lined baking sheets, place pecans in cluster of threes, 2 inches apart; set aside.

title: cream cheese chocolate cake
directions: Make cake as shown on box.
Let cream cheese soften, then mix cream cheese and Cool Whip together.
Add your powdered sugar a little at a time.
Mix well.
Make layer cake.
Put icing and cherries between layers, then put rest of cherries on top.
Cover; keep in icebox.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets; save 1/3 cup liquid.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add beet liquid, vinegar and butter.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Add beets; heat through.
Serve hot.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Combine flour, butter and nuts.
Mix well and press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: mexican corn
directions: Mix together all ingredients except cheese.
Pour in casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lola's corn bread
directions: Drain corn into medium size bowl.
Add eggs and beat well. Then add all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 7 x 11-inch oblong pan or 1 1/2-quart baking dish sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: baked stuffed pork chops
directions: Melt butter in frying pan.
Add onion and celery.
Cook until onions are clear.
Add bread, salt, pepper and poultry seasoning. Cut hole of meat out of each pork chop.
Stuff mixture into each hole in pork chop.
Cover with 1/2 can water and cream of mushroom soup.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: christmas pie
directions: Mix fruit and rum.
Let stand while remainder of recipe is put together.
Soften gelatin in cold water.

Mix cream with 1/4 of the sugar and heat in double boiler. Stir in gelatin and stir until dissolved. Beat egg yolks and combine with hot mixture. Stir over boiling water until mixture is smooth and slightly thickened. Remove from heat and chill until thick, stirring frequently. Fold remaining 1/4 cup sugar into stiffly beaten egg whites. Fold into thickened cream mixture. Return to refrigerator and chill again until almost ready to set. Fold in candied fruit and rum mixture. Fill well chilled pie crust.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: crumb-top cake
directions: In an 8-inch pan, stir 2 cups cake mix, the egg, milk and vanilla with rubber spatula until well blended.
Scrape down sides of pan.
In small bowl, mix well remaining 1/2 cup cake mix, nuts and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over batter.
This has 259 calories.
Bake according to Snack-Cake directions.

title: grandma downes' chocolate icebox cake
directions: In a heavy saucepan, melt chocolate chips with milk and marshmallows.
Chill well.
Whip the cream and fold it into the chocolate mixture.
Split cake into 2 layers.
Spread filling between layers and over the top and sides.
Refrigerate overnight. Cut into squares for serving.

title: funnel cakes
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, heat about 3/4-inch salad oil to 325° on deep fat thermometer (or heat oil according to manufacturer's directions in deep fat fryer set at 325°).
In medium bowl, with wire whisk or fork, mix flour, milk, baking powder, almond extract, salt and egg until well blended.
Holding narrow spouted funnel (1/2-inch spout), close spout with finger; pour 1/4 cup batter into funnel.
Over hot oil, carefully remove finger to let batter run out in a stream while making a spiral about 6 inches in diameter.
Fry 3 to 5 minutes until golden brown, turning once with tongs.
Drain well on paper towels; keep warm. Repeat with remaining batter, stirring well before pouring. Sprinkle funnel cakes lightly with confectioners sugar.
Serve warm.

title: lemon pie
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick.
Add lemon juice and rind.
Add sugar, flour and salt.
Blend together and add evaporated milk and melted butter.
Beat egg whites until dry.
Fold into pie shell. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 325° for 30 minutes.

title: artichoke rice salad
directions: Cook rice as directed on package, except omit butter.
Remove from heat; turn into bowl and let stand.
Add onions, green pepper and olives to rice.
Drain artichokes, reserving the marinade. Combine marinade with curry and mayonnaise.
Mix until blended. Add dressing to rice.
Mix along with artichoke hearts.
Mix lightly.
Cover bowl.
Serve chilled or room temperature.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Moisten bread crumbs with milk.
Add ground beef, salt and pepper.
Shape into patties.
Place in baking dish.

title: prune cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add sour cream alternately with sifted dry ingredients.
Add prunes and walnuts.
Pour into angel food pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix thoroughly and let set overnight.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wipe mushrooms with damp cloth.
Remove stems; chop stems fine.
Heat 1 tablespoon of margarine in large skillet.
Saute mushroom caps (on bottom only) for 2 to 3 minutes; remove.
Arrange, rounded side down, in shallow baking pan.
Heat rest of margarine in same skillet.
Saute stems, pepper and onion until tender, about 5 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper; remove from heat.
Spoon mixture into mushroom caps.
Bake for 15 minutes, until heated through.

title: crunchy cheese ball
directions: Beat cheese and mayonnaise until creamy.
Mix in rest of ingredients (except nuts).
Cover and chill several hours.
Form into a ball and roll in chopped nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: easy vegetable soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer until pasta is tender, about 30 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Drop on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8-10 minutes or until dough springs back to touch. Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place 1/2 the beans in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover with 1/2 the mushrooms and 1/2 chopped onions.
Sprinkle with 1/2 salt and 1/2 grated cheese.
Add mushroom soup.
Repeat in this order. Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Top with French fried onions the last 5 minutes of baking.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cut all into bite size chunks. Mix and add equal amounts of juice from cans to taste. Let set one day before serving. Can add chopped banana right before serving.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix melted margarine, eggs and sugar.
Cool slightly.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla. Mix well.
Stir in chocolate bits and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a long flat casserole.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: . Pour into greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool in pan.
When cooled, blend pudding mix with milk.
Beat cream cheese into pudding; mix until smooth.
Stirring by hand, fold whipped topping into pudding-cheese mixture.
Spread pudding mixture on top of cake.
Spread drained pineapple over pudding.
Sprinkle with coconut, nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate.

title: granmas hawaiian style chicken
directions: Coat chicken parts in butter.
Put in baking pan.
Scatter green pepper, mushrooms, sweet onion and pineapple chunks over chicken.
Mix catsup, lemon juice, chili sauce, brown sugar, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce, cornstarch, salt and juice from pineapple chunks. Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: cranberry molded salad
directions: Combine water and jello.
Let cool and thicken a little.
Add cranberry sauce, apples, and celery.
Beat sugar and cheese until well blended.
Stir in whipped topping.
Put in bottom of dish. Spoon jello mixture on top of cool whip mixture and chill until set.

title: pizza pie, kroger style
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the meat, milk, bread crumbs, salt, Italian seasonings and pepper.
Press meat mixture evenly over the bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Cut 1 1/2 slices of cheese into 6 triangles; set aside.
Shred or chop remaining cheese. Combine tomato paste, green pepper, mushrooms and shredded cheese; spread over meat mixture.
Bake in a 350°
oven for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Top with cheese triangles and continue baking for 10 to 15 minutes more, or until meat is done. Allow 10 minutes for pizza to set before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: old fashioned creamy rice pudding
directions: Bring to a boil 4 cups milk, sugar and rice.
Add the rice that has been rinsed well.
Simmer slowly, covered.
Cook for about 1 hour on low heat.
Pour into a greased 9-inch casserole. Add the remaining 1 cup milk and vanilla.
(Raisins may be added if desired.)
Bake in 400° oven until the skin on the pudding is browned.
Allow to cool.

title: cake mix cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine water and yeast; dissolve. Add flour and cake mix. Stir and knead until smooth. Turn into buttered bowl.
Let rise until doubled.
Punch down and repeat.
Divide dough in 2 parts. Roll out. Spread with melted butter or oleo, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up and slice.
Dip top of cut rolls into melted oleo, then into the mixture of sugar and chopped nuts, if desired. Let rise. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until done. Glaze and serve warm.
Very good.

title: impossible chicken parmigiana pie
directions: Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Layer cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese in pie plate.
Mix chicken, 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese, garlic powder, oregano, basil and tomato paste.
Spoon over cheese.
Save rest of Mozzarella for top.

title: carrot pennies
directions: Cook carrots until tender (about 7 minutes).
Drain and cool. Divide
carrots
into
half, peppers into half portions and onions into half portion.	Place layers of carrots, layers of
onions and
layers
of peppers in a buttered baking dish. Repeat with the remaining carrots, peppers and onions.

title: fudgy buttons
directions: In a small saucepan, melt the butter; remove from heat.
Add cocoa and mix well.
Stir in sugar.
Add milk and stir until smooth.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.
Flatten tops and shape into 1-inch patties.
Yields approximately 1 1/2 dozen.

title: spicy chunk pickles
directions: Drain dill pickles and cut into chunks.
Combine in a pan sugar, cider vinegar and pickling spice.
Heat until mixture boils, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Pack pickles into jar and pour liquid over.
Cover jar and refrigerate for one week.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together, using enough broth for mixture not to be dry.
Pour into large, greased baking pan. Bake at 400° until well done, approximately 1 hour.

title: gourmet rice
directions: Saute mushrooms and small onion in butter.
Pour in casserole with beef consomme and long grain rice.
Bake at 325°, covered, for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 1/2 hour longer, stirring occasionally.

title: dirty rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: company cauliflower
directions: Separate cauliflower in medium pieces.
Cook, covered in boiling salted water until tender, about 10 to 15 minutes; drain. Meanwhile, brown mushrooms and green pepper lightly in butter and flour.
Add milk and cook, stirring constantly until thick like a gravy.
Add salt.
Place 1/2 the cauliflower in a 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with half the cheese, then half the sauce. Repeat the layers and sprinkle with paprika.
Brown lightly in moderate oven at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine melted margarine and graham cracker crumbs; pat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until set so sugar, egg and butter mixture will
spread
better.
Beat
eggs
on
high speed until light.
Add
confectioners
sugar,
soft margarine and vanilla.
Beat 5 minutes and spread over crumbs.
Chill 30 minutes; spread pineapple over cream mixture.
Arrange bananas over pineapple; cover
with
Cool
Whip. Sprinkle with pecans. Cover and chill 6 hours.
Garnish with cherries.

title: chocolate candy balls
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients and roll into balls. Freeze.
Melt the paraffin and chocolate chips in double boiler. Spear balls with toothpicks and dip in chocolate.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: clam pie
directions: Melt butter in frying pan; add clams and rest of ingredients. Simmer for 15 minutes.
Place in deep pie plate; cover with pie crust.
Bake
at 350° until golden brown.
Serves 4.

title: no crust oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife will come out clean.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add bananas and eggs.
Slowly add dry ingredients to mixture.
Stir in nuts; blend thoroughly.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain grease.
Drain water off green beans and add to hamburger. Add tomato soup (do not add water or milk to the soup).
Let that simmer while making your potatoes.
Put hamburger mixture in a casserole dish.
Spoon mashed potatoes on top and smooth evenly. Bake in a 250° oven for 15 minutes.
You may also top with 1/2 cup grated Cheddar cheese before baking. Serves 3 or 4.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Thaw bread in refrigerator overnight.
Roll dough into 24 (1 1/2-inch) balls (12 balls from each loaf of bread).
Roll each ball into a rope, 14 inches long.
Shape each rope into a pretzel by forming a knot and looping the ends through.
Place pretzels 1 inch apart on a well-greased cookie sheet.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Combine egg white and water; brush on pretzels. Sprinkle with salt if you wish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: ham yum yums
directions: Melt margarine and combine with next 4 ingredients.
Slice open rolls.
Place generous slices of ham and cheese on open rolls.
Place tops in place.
Pour margarine mixture over rolls. Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes or until warm and cheese is melted.
Cut apart and serve.
Leave in pan until ready to serve.

title: mama's refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, peppers, onions and salt together well.
Mix sugar, vinegar and celery seed together; pour over cucumber, pepper, onion and salt mixture.
Put in refrigerator in a glass jar.
Will keep for 4 to 5 weeks.

title: sauerkraut dip
directions: Mix together. Microwave until hot and cheeses are melted. Serve hot with cocktail rye bread.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each one.
Add flavoring and salt.
Add flour, a little at a time, mixing well.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken and asparagus roulades
directions: Heat oven to 370°.
Remove excess fat from chicken; flatten each chicken breast half to 1/4-inch thickness between plastic wrap or waxed paper.
Mix salt, onion powder and dill weed; sprinkle over chicken.
Place 1/4 of asparagus spears and pepper strips crosswise on large end of each chicken breast half.
Roll tightly and secure with wooden picks.
Place chicken, seam sides down in square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Cover and bake until chicken is done, about 30 minutes.
Prepare Mock Hollandaise Sauce.
Serve with chicken.
Garnish with snipped fresh dill weed, if desired.
Makes 4 servings with about 3 tablespoons sauce each.
Calories 265 and fat 10 g.

title: grandma's apple-nut squares
directions: Combine egg, sugar and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to egg mixture and blend well.
Stir in apples and nuts. Spread in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Cut in squares and serve warm with ice cream.

title: creamed potato-cauliflower soup
directions: Combine soup, milk, cauliflower and 1/2 soup can water in blender container.
Process for 1/2 minute or just until smooth in blender.
Stir in sour cream.
Pour into saucepan.
Cook until heated through.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
May chill for 4 hours or longer and serve cold.
Yields 2 to 3 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add drained pineapple, seasoned salt, bell pepper, onion and 1 cup of chopped nuts.
Save 1 cup of nuts to roll cheese ball in before refrigeration.
This makes 1 large or 2 small balls.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together with fork and shape into balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes or until done.

title: spaghetti and cheese
directions: Slice half the cheese and dice the rest.
Break spaghetti into 3 pieces and cook.
Boil together the tomatoes, onions, pepper, sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
In another pan, melt butter and mix in flour.
Add this to the tomato mixture with the diced 1/2 pack of cheese.
In casserole, put half the spaghetti and tomato mixture and half the sliced cheese.
Repeat in layers and bake at 425° until brown.
tags: pack white sharp Cracker Barrel cheese

title: apple pie squares
directions: Mix all together.
Divide in half.
Press 1/2 on bottom of large cake pan.
Spread 1 can of fruit filling over, then sprinkle the other half all over the pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ham and cheese roll
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients, mixing well.
Chill thoroughly. Shape into 8-inch roll and coat with pecans.
Chill.
Garnish with parsley and serve with crackers.

title: vegetarian no bake pizza
directions: Do not separate crescent roll mix, just spread on pan and bake lightly.
Do not overbake.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread on top of roll mix.
Shred carrots.
Add carrots and broccoli cut in small pieces on top.
Cut into bite size squares.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Drain peaches.
Keep juice until later.
Melt stick of butter in baking pan.
In mixing bowl, combine the following:
flour, sugar, baking powder and soda.
Add buttermilk and mix.

title: zucchini cheese bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle zucchini with salt and let stand for 10 minutes.
Squeeze out liquid.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix with zucchini.
Spread in 8-inch square pan that is greased.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; add all ingredients.
Put in casserole dish, covered, and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: holiday glazed yams
directions: Heat butter until melted; add other ingredients.
Simmer until all sugar is melted.
Pour over yams.
Makes enough syrup for one 9 x 13-inch pan.
Can be doubled.
Pour small pecan pieces over syrup.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(Can be prepared up to 2 days prior to baking.)

title: brownie cake
directions: Bring to a boil the oil, oleo, water and cocoa. While hot, pour over sugar and flour, which have been sifted together. Add remaining ingredients. Bake in 9 x 14-inch greased pan 20 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken parmesan(serves 4)
directions: Flatten chicken to an even thickness using palm of hand or meat mallet.
Dip chicken in egg; coat with crumbs.
In skillet over medium heat, in hot margarine, cook chicken until browned on both sides.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and parsley.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve over hot spaghetti.

title: venus de milo soup
directions: Puree basil, garlic and nuts in food processor.
Add olive oil while pureeing.
Add Parmesan and process briefly.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Makes enough for 2 pounds of pasta.
Freezes well.

title: smothered green cabbage
directions: Melt butter and bacon drippings in large saucepan or Dutch oven.
Add cabbage and stir over medium heat until cabbage is tender-crisp, about 10 minutes.
Add garlic, caraway seeds, salt and pepper.
Stir in soup; heat thoroughly and serve.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into thin slices. In a saucepan, cook onion in margarine until tender. Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and stir in milk and 1 1/2 cups of cheese. Heat to boiling and boil for 1 minute. Place potatoes in ungreased 4-quart casserole pan and pour cheese sauce over potatoes.
Cook uncovered at 350° for 1 hour. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake until melted. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Slice cake in half.
Combine Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice. Add Cool Whip and strawberries.
Fill middle of cake with this mixture, then put the top back on and frost top and sides. Refrigerate after icing.
This will stay in the refrigerator for several days in a covered container.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale and refrigerate.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: cheese roll
directions: Place the cheese on wax paper and roll with a rolling pin until flat.
Mix together the remaining ingredients on top of cheese and roll up.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serve with any type of crackers.

title: hello dolly
directions: Layer in 9 x 13-inch buttered cooking dish (as presented). Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Mash with fork after slightly cooled.
Cut in small squares.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Beat cream cheese, eggs, vanilla and brown sugar until well blended (will be slightly lumpy).
Put a vanilla wafer (round side down) in bottom of cupcake papers and fill 3/4 full with mixture. Top with cherry or nutmeat.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain off fat.
Mix uncooked rice into meat.
In a greased 2-quart casserole or 9 x 13-inch pan, place chopped cabbage.
Top with meat and rice mixture.
Mix soup and puree together.
Thin with enough water to make a pourable topping. Season with desired herbs (I use basil, oregano, pepper and garlic powder).
Pour soup mix all over the top of the casserole.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
If white rice is used, bake for 1 hour.

title: brie appetizer
directions: Trim off casing from top of Brie.
Braid or twist bread sticks around Brie.
Put brown sugar on Brie about 1/4 inch thick and sprinkle some pecans or almonds on top of brown sugar.
Glaze bread sticks with egg whites and then sprinkle some brown sugar on the bread stick ring.
Bake at the temperature and time for the bread sticks.

title: senegalese yasa
directions: Fry chicken in hot oil until crisp.
Combine separately diced onions, sliced onions, mustard, garlic, lemon juice and salt and pepper; cook 10 minutes.
Add cooked chicken pieces, crushed bouillon cube and water to make sauce.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over hot rice.

title: cream cheese clouds
directions: Separate dough into 12 biscuits; press or roll each to 1/4 inch thickness. Mix sugar and cinnamon in shallow dish. Dip cream cheese cubes in melted butter, then roll in the cinnamon sugar. Place

1 cream cheese cube in center of each dough circle; gather up sides of dough to enclose filling. Press edges of dough together to seal. Place seam sides up, in lightly greased muffin pan. Drizzle with remaining butter; sprinkle with remaining cinnamon sugar. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: baked fish
directions: Butter a 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe bowl.
Layer fillets with dots of butter between layers. Cover and microwave 15 minutes at 400 watts.
Remove cover.
Squeeze one lemon over fillets. Microwave 7 minutes more or until done, with lid off.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Mix Salad Supreme, dressing, spaghetti and vegetables.
Refrigerate.

title: biscuits and beans
directions: Brown meat; add next 4 ingredients.
Heat until bubbly.
Pour into casserole dish.
Place biscuits on top, then sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: streusel coffee cake
directions: Stir together 1 1/2 cups flour, granulated sugar and baking powder. Set aside. Combine egg, milk and oil. Add to flour mixture; mix well. Stir in raisins and chocolate chips. Turn into a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine brown sugar, 1 tablespoon flour, butter and cinnamon. Sprinkle over batter. Bake in a 375° oven about 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 1 coffee cake.

title: easy tamale pie
directions: In a heavy skillet, heat oil and cook onion until soft.
Add beef and cook until lightly browned.
Stir in all remaining ingredients, except olives and cheese, mixing well.
Add olives. Cover pie with chunks of cheese.
Cover and cook on top of stove over low heat, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: deluxe cucumber pickles
directions: I use pickling or large dill cukes.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Cook cabbage leaves in salted water a few minutes to soften. Drain.
Combine 2 tablespoons soup with remaining ingredients. Divide meat mixture into 8 balls and place one in each cabbage leaf.
Fold in sides of leaves and roll up, securing with toothpick.
Place rolls, seam side down, in skillet.
Pour remaining soup over rolls.
Cover; cook over low heat for 40 minutes, spooning sauce over rolls occasionally.

title: caramel lover's fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In heavy saucepan, combine caramels, condensed milk and 1/2 cup shortening.
Over medium heat, cook and stir until melted.
In medium bowl, combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
In large bowl beat sugar and rest of shortening until fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
In small bowl combine water, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add alternately with flour mixture, beating well. Spread half of the batter in a greased 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake 15 minutes or until center is set.
Spoon caramel mixture evenly over cake.
Spread remaining batter over caramel.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 40 minutes or until cake tests done in center.
Loosen from sides of pan while warm.
Cool completely before serving.

title: chili-cheese hominy
directions: Saute onions in butter in a large skillet for 5 minutes.
Add hominy, green chilies, sour cream, chili powder, and pepper;
add 1/2 cup cheese.
Stir well.
Pour into a lightly greased 10 x 6 x 2 baking dish; bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining 1 cup cheese over top, bake an additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Yield:
6-8 servings.

title: mother's gluck
directions: Cook hamburger and rice.
Mix together when done.
Add dash of garlic salt and season with salt and pepper.
Cook peas.
Fry altogether and serve.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix Crisco, sugar, eggs and vanilla thoroughly.
Stir
in
remaining
ingredients.
Drop
dough by teaspoon 2 inches
apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until done.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and salad dressing until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: sour cream cucumbers
directions: Thinly slice cucumber.
Sprinkle with salt.
Let stand 30 minutes, then drain.
Combine sour cream, vinegar, hot pepper sauce, chives, dill weed and pepper.
Pour over cucumber.
Chill 30 minutes.
Makes 4 or 5 servings.

title: baked pineapple filling
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs (whipped with a fork) and drained pineapple, then bread.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, uncovered.
Can eat hot or cold. Great with ham!

title: chinese nut cookies
directions: Mix together and shape into small balls.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Cover with powdered sugar while still warm.
This recipe can be doubled easily.

title: giant fruit cookie
directions: Spread cookie dough on pizza pan.
Cook at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, egg and powdered sugar.
Spread on cookie.
Chill.
Add sliced fresh fruit.
Spread with Cool Whip.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Combine ingredients in a large skillet and cook until mixture thickens.
Add 2 cups Rice Krispies and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
When cool enough to handle, shape into balls and roll in powdered sugar or coconut.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook bacon over medium-high heat in large nonstick skillet until crisp.
Remove from heat.
Remove bacon with slotted spoon and set aside.
Strain all but three tablespoons of fat from pan. To fat in skillet, add vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Mix water with cornstarch and stir into skillet.
Cook and stir over medium heat until potatoes are tender, stirring once or twice.
Add bacon, onions and parsley.
Mix gently to heat through.
Serve hot.
Makes four side dish servings.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Separate chicken from the bone. Set aside.
Cook rice as directed on package.
Cook onion, pepper and butter until tender and put into rice mixture.
Add mushroom soup and stir, then add chicken.
Put Worcestershire sauce in and stir.
Will serve 4 to 5 people.

title: maggie's macaroni
directions: Bring 2 quarts water to a boil.
Add macaroni and reduce heat to low.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Drain.
Spray frying pan with Pam. Add ground beef and chopped onion; season with fresh ground pepper.
Cook over low heat until brown.
In large casserole, place macaroni, beef and onions, tomatoes and cheese.
Stir.
Heat in microwave for 5 minutes and serve.

title: apple
directions: Beat first 8 ingredients.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.

title: skip and go naked
directions: Build in Collins glass with cubed ice.
Fill with beer.

title: fiesta southwestern salsa
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients except avocado.
Chill 4 hours or overnight.
Just before serving, toss avocado with mixture, if desired.

title: hamburger noodle bake
directions: Cook and stir hamburger and onion in 2-quart saucepan until hamburger is light brown; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, salt and garlic powder.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, 30 minutes.

title: sicilian eggplant caponata
directions: Wash eggplant; do not peel.
Cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Fry in heated oil until tender.
Take out and set aside.
Saute onion in same oil until tender.
Add garlic, celery, tomatoes and olives.
Cook slowly for 10 minutes.
Add eggplant, pine nuts and capers.
Heat vinegar and stir in sugar. Add to vegetable mixture.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cook for 5 minutes more.
Serve chilled.
Serves 6.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill in refrigerator 2 to 3 hours. Serve with ham.
Serves 18.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Wash, quarter and remove core from apples.
Place apples, celery, mayonnaise and salt in mixing bowl; mix lightly.
Chill and serve.

title: pina colada pie
directions: Layer bottoms of pie crust with drained pineapple.
Then layer with coconut cream pie filling and layer of banana cream pie filling.
Sprinkle with flaked coconut and pineapple chunks. Spread whipped cream over pies.
Chill and serve.
Serves 12 to 18 people.

title: cube steak and gravy
directions: Cook Crisco until brown and set aside.
Wash and batter chops with flour, salt and pepper mixed.
Put 1/4 cup flour in pan with Crisco.
Cook steak until brown and then add water.
Bring to a boil until thick.
Add more water if too thick.

title: the forgotten cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Add salt to egg whites and beat until stiff.
Add sugar and vanilla gradually.
Add pecans and chips. Mix all together well.
Drop by teaspoon onto foil.
Put in oven and turn oven off.
Keep in oven a minimum of 2 hours or overnight.
Then peel off of foil.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil, applesauce and milk.
Combine remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Add to applesauce mixture, mixing well.
Pour into three 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: cowboy's delight
directions: Saute onion.
Brown meat; add potatoes and cook until done.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add sour milk alternately with flour, baking powder and soda.
Add bananas and vanilla.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: ginger-sauced melon
directions: Combine wine, sugar and cloves in a small non-reactive saucepan.
Heat to boiling, simmer for 5 minutes.
Strain; add juice and ginger.
Chill.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Using a large mixing bowl, mix flour and sugar, stirring well. This is the flour mixture.

title: little debbie oatmeal creme pies
directions: In a large bowl, creme together margarine, sugar, brown sugar, molasses,

vanilla and eggs. In a separate bowl, combine the flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon. Combine the dry ingredients with the wet ingredients. Mix in the oats. Use a Tbsp. to drop dough onto an ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until cookies are just starting to darken around the edges. They will still appear to be moist in the center. Be careful not to overcook. When cooled, the cookies should be soft and chewy. While the cookies bake, prepare the filling.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Combine brown sugar, melted butter and sweet potatoes in small bowl. Beat until fluffy.
Stir soda into buttermilk. Combine all ingredients.
Stir only until moist. Turn out on floured board.
Knead slightly.
Roll out and cut into biscuits. Bake on ungreased baking sheet for about 20 minutes or until done. Makes about 18 biscuits.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti in salted water.
Fry bacon until grease is cooked out.
Fry onion in grease until light brown.
Add tomatoes and chili powder.
Add spaghetti; put in casserole dish and place pieces of cheese over top.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mom's fruit cake
directions: Combine all the nuts. Over this mixture add and mix the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Beat 3 eggs and vanilla.
Pour over first mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Walnuts may be used.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Boil chicken and take off bone.
Mix Stove Top dressing according to directions.
Put chicken, Stove Top dressing and soup in layers in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and bake until cheese melts.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be frozen.

title: kielbasa casserole
directions: Lightly grease a 2-quart baking dish. Brown and drain kielbasa in a large skillet. Stir in onion and garlic, then tomatoes. Cover and simmer over low heat 10 minutes or until onion is tender. Add remaining ingredients.
Stir to mix.
Transfer to baking dish. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes until hot and blended. Serves 4.

title: hodgepodge soup
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot (on low) and cook all day.

title: french pot roast
directions: Mix all ingredients except the roast and seasonings.
Brown the roast after seasoning with salt, pepper and garlic powder. Pour soup-wine-water-thyme
mixture over the roast. Cook covered for 3 hours at 325°. Serve with rice or baked potato.

title: boiled spice cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and boil for 3 minutes and cool.
Add baking soda and flour; bake.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook and chop vegetables.
Place in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix coconut and pecans together and put in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Melt margarine and cream cheese together. Stir in sugar.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash, cut and slice green tomatoes; coat with flour.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place tomatoes in hot cooking oil and fry one side until brown; turn and brown other side.

title: eclair cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line bottom with whole graham crackers.
Mix pudding with milk; beat 2 minutes.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour 1/2 mixture over crackers; cover with a layer of graham crackers.
Layer again pudding with crackers.
Spread softened icing on crackers.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut and serve chilled.
Travels nicely.

title: feta-stuffed chicken breasts(with sun-dried tomatoes)
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Combine olive oil, sun-dried tomatoes, garlic, oregano and pepper in small bowl (put all of these ingredients together in a food processor and chop them up to combine).
Set aside.
Place chicken breasts in roasting pan.
Slip fingers under chicken skin and loosen to form pocket.
(If using skinless chicken breasts just cut small slits in the chicken and stuff the feta cheese in.)
Spoon olive oil mixture evenly on tops of chicken.
Cover pan with heavy-duty foil.
Bake for 50 minutes. Remove foil.
Broil few minutes, uncovered, until lightly browned. Yield 6 servings.

title: chicken and vegetable bake
directions: Preparation time: 10 minutes.
Cooking time: 30 minutes.

title: pink salad
directions: Combine the pineapple (juice and all), jello and marshmallows. Heat until melted; cool.
Combine cream cheese, milk and whipped cream.
Pour into jello mixture; mix well.
Pour into mold.

title: taco soup
directions: Mix ground meat and chopped onion. Fry off and drain. Mix with all other ingredients. Simmer for about 30 minutes. Good when made that morning and let sit all day to let flavors blend. Can be served with cheese or chips.

title: lori's caramel corn
directions: Melt butter, syrup, sugar and salt.
Let boil 5 minutes, stirring regularly.
Add flavoring and soda.
Pour over popcorn in paper bag; do not stir.
Cook on High in microwave for 30 seconds. Take out; shake and microwave for an additional 30 seconds.
Stir (recommend an oven mit be worn over the hand).

title: crispy potato chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Arrange chicken in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish that has been sprayed with nonstick coating.
Mix mustard and garlic.
Spread over chicken.
Scrub potato, grate and mix well with oil.
Spread over chicken.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes, until chicken is done and potatoes are golden. Calories per serving:
Exchanges:
4 lean meat, 1/2 starch.

title: frozen fruit cup salad
directions: Boil together the sugar and water.
Add lemon juice to cooled syrup.
Mix syrup and fruit.
Freeze.
This is a very refreshing summer salad.

title: triple crown meat loaf
directions: Combine 1/3 cup crushed onion rings and brown sugar.
Put 1 tablespoon mixture in each of 8 small, well-greased ovenproof custard cups.
Top with 1/2 teaspoon mustard.
Melt butter in small saucepan.
Remove from heat and stir in flour to form a smooth paste.
Add catsup; stir to blend.
Combine hamburger, egg, catsup mixture and remaining crushed onions.
Mix thoroughly.
Press 1/3 cup meat into custard cup.
Place 1/2 slice cheese on top of meat. Add more meat on top of cheese and seal edges.
Place custard cups on cookie sheet.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes, until done.
Drain any accumulated grease.
Run knife around edge of custard cup and invert onto platter.
Make sure you scrape bottom of custard cup to get glaze out.
Spread on meat loaf.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix sugars, Crisco and egg.
Add flour.
Mix well.
Add enough water to moisten (approximately 2 tablespoons), then add chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: nuns farts
directions: Mix well.
Roll the dough and butter it.
Put a good layer of brown sugar.
Roll in jellyroll fashion and cut 1/2 inch thick. Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.

title: moravian sugar cake
directions: Soak yeast in the water and 1 teaspoon sugar and set aside. Cream 1 cup sugar, margarine and salt together.
Add eggs, then hot mashed potatoes.
Mix. Add yeast, water and sugar mixture.
Stir in all of flour.
Let stand in warm place overnight or until it rises.

title: delicious cracker dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve on Ritz or Townhouse crackers.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix and blend as you would for any quick bread recipe.
Grease and flour 2 large loaf pans, bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: robyn's chili dip
directions: Heat first 3 ingredients until cream cheese is melted.
Serve with chips and enjoy.

title: cedric's casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add beef, heating through, but not browning it.
Add salt and pepper.
Spread 3 cups cabbage in 2-quart baking dish.
Cover with meat mixture, then top with 3 more cups of cabbage.
Pour tomato soup, undiluted, over top. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add pumpkin, milk and beaten eggs.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lela callis thompson's gingersnaps
directions: Set oven for moderate, 350°.
Mix and sift first 5 ingredients.
Sift again twice; return to sifter.
Beat shortening until creamy.
Add 1 cup sugar gradually, continuing to beat. Beat in egg and molasses.
Sift about 1/4 of the flour mixture over the molasses mixture; stir to blend well.
Repeat until all flour mixture is added.
Form teaspoon of dough into small balls by rolling lightly between palms of hands.
Then coat with the extra sugar and place about 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake approximately 12 minutes or until tops are slightly rounded and crackly.
Cool on racks.
Makes about 5 to 6 dozen cookies.

title: breakfast biscuits
directions: Crumble sausage and brown with onion.
Drain on paper towels. Combine biscuit mix, water and soup until moistened.
Add sausage. Using a heaping tablespoon, drop batter on lightly greased baking sheet 2-inches apart.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until slightly brown.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: barbara's dip
directions: Mix dry package dip mix, mayonnaise, milk and cream cheese. Add cheese. If mixture is too thick, add more milk to desired consistency. Refrigerate for several hours or overnight. Serve with crackers.

title: pralines
directions: Do not double recipe.

title: lasagna with a twist
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add sauce and seasonings; simmer 5 minutes over low heat.
Combine meat sauce with cooked pasta. Combine the cheeses thoroughly.
Place 1/2 the pasta mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Evenly top with cheese mixture and remaining pasta.
Bake 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: cranberry salad(lo-cal)
directions: Drain crushed pineapple, reserving 3/4 cup juice. Set aside. Combine gelatin and boiling water in a bowl. Stir until gelatin dissolves. Stir in reserved pineapple juice and cranberry sauce. Cover and chill 45 minutes. Fold in drained pineapple, apple, celery and walnuts. Spoon gelatin into a 1-quart serving bowl. Cover and chill 4 hours or until firm.

title: special k bars
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil; remove from heat and add peanut butter and Special K.
Mix well.
Butter hands lightly and press mixture firmly into large buttered cookie sheet.
Melt chips and spread over top for frosting.
Yields 24 bars.

title: busy day bake
directions: Season liver with salt and pepper; coat with flour.
In large skillet, brown quickly in hot
oil,
about	1
minute on each side.
Place in greased
baking
dish.
Add seasoning and tomatoes; cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and bake for 10 to 15 minutes
longer to thicken gravy.
Serve on rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Combine
margarine,
brown
sugar
and	corn syrup in a large saucepan;
bring
to a boil.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally,
so
it doesn't scorch.
Remove from heat. Add baking
soda;
mixture will foam.
Pour over popped corn; mix well.
Pour
into
unbuttered
large pan (a roaster works well); place
in
a 200° oven for 1 hour, stirring about every 15 minutes.
Store in covered container.

title: super beefy enchiladas
directions: Combine beef, 1/2 cup cheese and onion.
Set aside.
Combine soups and enchilada sauce.
Dip tortillas in hot oil to soften a few seconds on each side. Top each tortilla with 1 heaping tablespoonful of meat mixture.
Roll up.
Place seam side down in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over and top with remaining cheese. Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: packet dinner
directions: Spray foil pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Arrange bologna, potatoes, beans and pepper in sprayed pan.	Pour melted margarine over mixture; toss to coat.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and pepper.
Cook 20-25 minutes on covered grill or until vegetables are tender, stirring frequently.

title: chocolate critters
directions: In saucepan, mix chocolate chips, margarine, milk and salt. Stir until all is creamy.
Bring to a slow boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and pecans; stir well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let stand until cool.

title: onion blossom
directions: Peel onion, leaving root end intact.
Cut onion vertically into quarters, cutting to within 1/2 inch of root.
Cut each quarter vertically into thirds.
Place onion in boiling water 1 minute.
Remove and place in ice water 5 minutes.
Loosen petals if necessary.
Drain onion, cut side down.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream the sugar and oil.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir flour, baking soda and salt together.
Mix cocoa and food coloring and add vinegar.
Add to creamed mixture.
Beat hard and add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and beat until blended.
Pour in 3 prepared layer pans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: 14 karat cake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add remaining
ingredients,
including coconut, if desired.
Grease and flour three 9-inch pans, bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool completely before frosting.

title: strawberry satin pie
directions: Add powdered sugar, vanilla and almond extract to cream cheese.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Fold in whipped cream. Spread evenly over bottom of pie shell.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Drain cucumber well, pressing between layers of paper towels. Stir together cucumber and next 4 ingredients.
Spread mixture evenly over half of bread slices.
Top with remaining bread slices.
Trim crust from sandwiches, and cut in half diagonally. Garnish, if desired.
Store sandwiches in an airtight container. Yield 16 sandwiches.

title: seafood newburg
directions: Simmer haddock and drain.
Saute scallops in a piece of butter.
If large scallops, cut into bite size pieces.
Combine all seafood with soup and pour into a casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbling or about 30 minutes.
Serve in cooked patty shells.
If made ahead of time, it will be more flavorful. Can make it the day before, refrigerate and bake it just before serving.

title: apricot salad with topping
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice for topping.
Combine apricot nectar and water in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add gelatin; stir to dissolve.
Stir in pineapple, marshmallows and bananas. Pour into shallow 2-quart dish.
Chill until firm.
Cover with topping.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta; drain, then mix together lemon juice, olive oil and Accent and stir into pasta.
Let set while cutting up fine the onions, bell pepper, celery, olives and pimento.
Add a big dab of Miracle Whip.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix everything together and store in a tight container.

title: ting-a-lings
directions: Melt the chips in the top of a double boiler and add the noodles and the peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
They are ready to eat as soon as they firm up.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: bacon cheese appetizers
directions: Slice bacon into halves. Cut cheese into cubes. Sprinkle with cayenne pepper. Wrap with bacon; fasten with toothpicks. Place on baking sheet. Broil 2 to 3 minutes; turn and broil 3 minutes until cheese melts and bacon is crisp. Garnish with tomatoes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into a buttered casserole.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350° and stir; then bake for 30 to 40 minutes longer.

title: sunshine cake(grandmother hasselo)
directions: Beat whites stiff, add cream of tartar.
Slowly add sugar.
Add yolks beaten light.
Fold in flour.
Bake in tube pan about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: norwegian rye bread
directions: Measure water, molasses, shortening, sugars and salt into a big bowl.
Heat until shortening is melted and mixture is warm. Stir in yeast and rye flour; beat.
Stir in as much white flour as possible and then with your hands work in rest.
Knead until smooth (I don't use quite as much flour).
Let rise until double in bulk.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Makes 5 loaves.

title: (hot) german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes.
Cool slightly, peel and cut in 1/8-inch slices to make about 4 cups.
Cut bacon in small pieces and fry until crisp.
Drain on paper towel and set aside.
Reserve bacon grease. Stir flour, sugar and seasonings into bacon grease until smooth. Cook until bubbly.
Add water and vinegar to flour mixture.
Cook until mixture boils and thickens.
Add potatoes and bacon; stir gently so potatoes hold their shape.
Cover casserole and let stand until ready to serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cool summer sandwich
directions: Cut one ice cream sandwich in half. Place one whole and one half sandwich along a short side of an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Arrange 8 sandwiches in opposite direction in the pan. Spread with half of the whipped topping. Spoon fudge topping by teaspoonfuls onto whipped topping. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup peanuts. Repeat layers with remaining ice cream sandwiches, whipped topping and peanuts (pan will be full). Cover and freeze for up to 2 months. Remove from the freezer 20 minutes before serving. Cut into squares. Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: granny smith apple dumplings
directions: First, roll biscuits out as thin as possible.
Now wrap each apple quarter with dough and place seam-side down in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Next, melt the butter and add brown and white sugar, cinnamon, lemon juice and water.
Bring to a boil and pour the liquid over the top of the dumplings until nearly covered. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, until slightly brown on top. Serve warm with cream.
Makes 28 dumplings.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Brown sausage and ground chuck in separate pans. Drain in colander to remove grease. Break up cheese. Return meats to big skillet over low heat. Add cheese and stir until all cheese is melted. Add seasonings; blend well. Spread mixture onto bread; place on cookie sheet and freeze. Then put into freezer bags. When ready to use, bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°, until crispy.

title: taffy apples(candy apples)
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine sugar, syrup and cinnamon with 1 cup cold water.
Over medium heat, stir constantly just until sugar and candies are dissolved (do not boil).
Add food coloring and cinnamon. Stir to mix well.
Bring syrup to boiling.
Continue cooking without stirring, to 300° on candy thermometer.
Wash apples and dry well.
Remove stem and insert skewers part-way in stem end, far enough to hold apple firmly.
Remove syrup from heat.
Working quickly, dip each apple into syrup. Coat completely.
Place skewer end up on well greased cookie sheets, to let taffy harden.
Let stand at room temperature until serving. Makes 6 medium apples or 8 small apples.

title: soft bread sticks
directions: Sprinkle yeast over very warm water in a 1-cup measure.
Very warm water feels comfortably warm when dropped on wrist.
Stir in 1 teaspoon of the honey.
Let stand until bubbly, about 10 minutes. Mix butter, salt, boiling water and remaining honey in a large bowl, cool to lukewarm.
Beat egg in small cup, reserve 1 tablespoon for brushing sticks.
Stir remaining egg into butter mixture.
Stir in yeast until blended.
Add 2 cups of the flour; gradually stir in enough extra flour to make a soft dough.
Do not knead.
Divide dough into 12 equal parts.
Roll each on floured surface to make an even stick 12 inches long.
Place on greased cookie sheets about 2 inches apart.
Mix reserved egg with 1/2 teaspoon water, brush on sticks and sprinkle on seed or salt.
Let stand, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Remove to wire rack.
Serve warm.
For shorter sticks, divide dough into 24 parts.

title: chinese hamburger
directions: Cook beef until crumbly.
Drain off grease.
Add onion, celery, soups, can of water, pepper, soy sauce and rice.
Stir. Put on lid and cook on low until rice is done, about 30 minutes. Serve over Chinese noodles, if desired.

title: cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cream butter with brown sugar in small bowl. Add flour and walnuts.
Mix well. Put aside 1 cup of the mix for topping. Press the rest evenly into the bottom of an 8-inch square pan. Bake for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat
oven to 375°.
Beat together margarine and sugars until light
and
fluffy.
Beat
in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking
soda,
salt and spices.
Add to margarine mixture,
mixing well.
Stir in oats and pecans.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful
onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes for a
chewy
cookie or
10 to 11 minutes for a crisp cookie. Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.

title: congealed salad
directions: Use the juice of the pineapple and add enough water to make 4 cups of liquid.
Bring to a boil, adding marshmallows.
Dissolve Jell-O in mixture.
Set in refrigerator until it begins to thicken, then add remaining ingredients.
Pour into favorite mold. Chill and serve on lettuce.

title: colorado ranger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs.
Add flour, baking powder, soda and salt and work in oats, Rice Krispies, coconut and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly until mixture is a stiff dough.
Mold into small balls and press down on greased cookie sheets with fork. Bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: vegetable sandwich spread
directions: Soften cream cheese, then add all other ingredients. Mix well. Spread on whole wheat bread.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix sugar, butter and eggs.
Add flour and salt.
Mix soda with milk.
Gradually add milk and bananas to sugar mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Makes 1 large loaf.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and bake at 350° for about 25 or 30 minutes.
Bring to boil about 2 minutes the sugar, oleo and milk. Take off heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour over cake while hot.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Fry hamburg until crumbly; drain off fat.
Combine soup and milk.
Alternate layers of crushed potato chips, hamburg, soup mixture and beans or peas.
Top with crushed chips.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: favorite vegetable soup
directions: In a 3-quart pan, combine diced onion, instant chicken broth and garlic cloves; cook on medium until onion is translucent, stirring.
Add green beans, carrots, sliced celery, chopped tomatoes, chopped fresh parsley, basil leaves and pepper; stir in well.
Cover; cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, for 10 minutes.
Add water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium. Cover; cook until vegetables are soft, approximately 20 minutes. Makes 7 to 8 servings.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix well into little balls.

title: ham stuffed cherry tomatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients, saving parsley for later.
Blend well.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
With sharp small knife, cut tops from tomatoes and scoop insides out.
Spoon mixture into each, mounding slightly.
Garnish with parsley.
Party Day: Prepare in morning and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: snowball
directions: Add gelatin to the cold water.
Stir in hot water.
After dissolved, add salt, sugar, orange juice and lemon juice.
Place in refrigerator and partially set (or freezer for about 40 minutes).
Combine beaten cream or Cool Whip with gelatin mixture. Either bake angel cake the day before or buy one all made at store.
Cut off all the brown edges (some like it left on).
Break into small bite-size pieces.
Use largest size Pyrex or stainless steel bowl and line with strips of waxed paper.
Add a small layer of cake pieces.
Add layer of gelatin.
Alternate with cake and gelatin.
Make sure you end with a layer of gelatin.
Place in refrigerator until set (best overnight).

title: cheese bars
directions: Mix together cake mix, 1 egg and margarine like cookie dough. Press into a greased 13 x 19-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until puffy.
Mix cheese, 3 eggs and sugar on medium speed.
Add nuts. Pour over cake.
Bake until golden brown, approximately 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then pour into a graham cracker pie shell.
Let cool in refrigerator, then serve.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream first four wet ingredients, then add rest.
Roll in balls, then in sugar.
Place balls on nonstick cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: amaretto punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in boiling water (1-quart).
Stir in remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Divide mixture into pint size freezer bags and put into freezer.
Remove bags as needed and let stand at room temperature until slushy.
Yields about 6 quarts.

title: fruited chocolate trifle
directions: Cut cake into 1 inch cubes; set aside.
In small bowl, combine milk and pudding mix; beat a low speed 1 to 2 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes to thicken.
fold 1 1/2 cups of the whipped cream into pudding.
Spoon about 1/3 of the pudding mixture into bottom of 2 1/2-quart straight-sided glass serving bowl.
Add 1/3 of the fruits and 1/3 of the cake cubes.
Repeat layers two more times.
Pipe or dollop remaining whipped cream over top layer of cake cubes.
Garnish with sliced almonds and strawberries.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Beat together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift together, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to sugar mixture.
Beat well.
Add chocolate syrup and mix.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 13 inch pan about 35 minutes or until done.

title: bacon spaghetti
directions: Put butter on the macaroni, then you put water on it.
Boil it on the stove for a little bit long.
Put cheese and butter and water on it after you boil it.
Then it's done.
That's the way you do it.

title: breaded chicken with lemon juice
directions: Wash chicken pieces, dredge in flour, dip in egg-water, coat thoroughly with bread crumbs.
In frypan heat oil and butter to medium heat.
Carefully place chicken in pan, turning when brown. Cook until juices run clear.
Serve hot with a few drops of lemon juice sprinkled on top.
Try lemon juice on the vegetables also.

title: black walnut pie
directions: Bake in 9-inch unbaked pastry shell.
Beat eggs with sugar, pinch of salt, corn syrup and melted butter.
Add black walnuts. Pour in shell and bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: italian chicken
directions: The day before you are going to serve it, lay chicken in a baking dish and pour entire bottle of dressing on top of chicken. Cover with foil and let set in refrigerator overnight.
Drain extra dressing before cooking and put to side.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Add dressing to chicken while cooking as desired.

title: 4-h club punch
directions: Boil water and sugar 1 minute.
Cool.
Mix with tea and juices and add flavoring.
If desired, add food coloring.

title: string beans and potatoes(great on a cold winter night)
directions: Snap beans (remove ends).
Cut potatoes in chunks.
Cook beans and potatoes in two pans.
Do not let beans or potatoes overcook. Also, cook light tomato sauce.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Combine sugar, shortening, cocoa and milk in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Add salt, vanilla, nuts and oatmeal.
Stir.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Cool and eat.

title: vegetable mix
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut the onion, bell pepper and zucchini into chunks; place in a large bowl.
Add the garlic, corn and mushrooms.
Coat vegetables with olive oil.
Stir in the herbs and salt.
Mix well.
Place vegetables in a large baking dish and bake until tender, about 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: 10-layer salad
directions: Cover with foil and refrigerate several hours before serving. Will keep for 4 days.
Make this recipe in a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish or suitable container.

title: orange pop ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into ice cream freezer.
Freeze according to directions.

title: no measure garlic bread
directions: Cut bread in half lengthwise.
Spread each half generously with butter.
Generously sprinkle garlic bread sprinkle, then Parmesan cheese over butter.
Place each half in preheated broiler of oven until browned, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Cut in pieces and serve.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: In large saucepan, combine green peppers, jalapeno peppers, sugar and vinegar.
Heat to boiling.
Boil 1 minute, stirring to prevent boiling over.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pectin, mixing well.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Skim off white film which forms on top.
Mix in food coloring.
Strain if you prefer a clear jelly. Pour into hot sterilized 8 ounces jars.
Top with sterilized 2-part lids and tighten bands.
Cool on racks.
Makes six 8 ounce jars.
Makes appetizers by spreading cream cheese on Ritz crackers and topping with a bit of jelly.

title: parmesan-bacon sticks
directions: Wrap bacon strips around breadsticks; roll in cheese and place on baking sheets. Bake at 250° for 1 hour. Serve immediately. Yield: 2 1/2 dozen.

title: creme de menthe pie
directions: Reserve 1/4 cup crumbs for top.
Mix remaining crumbs with melted butter and press into spring-form pan.
Add creme de menthe to Fluff, mixing well.
Whip cream and fold into Fluff mixture. Put into pan.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Freeze at least 4 hours. Remove 20 minutes before serving.

title: vegetable and chip dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Layer potatoes, onion, salt and pepper.
Top with chops or boneless chops.
Over this, pour soup and water.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.	Cook ahead and heat at mealtime.

title: nestle holiday fudge
directions: Combine butter, evaporated milk, sugar and salt in medium heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, morsels, nuts and vanilla.
Stir vigorously for 1 minute, or until marshmallows are melted.
Pour into foil lined 8-inch square baking pan; chill until firm.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces.

title: spicy beef dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: tuna-cauliflower casserole
directions: Mix soup, tuna, onion and green pepper and mix with cauliflower.
Pour into buttered 1 qt. casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cauliflower, red salmon and cream of celery soup is also very good.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Place all ingredients, except vanilla, in top of double boiler (not over heat).
Beat 1 minute with electric mixer on medium speed.
Place over boiling water and cook, beating constantly, for 7 minutes or until frosting holds stiff peaks.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Continue beating until spreading consistency.

title: sweet oil dressing
directions: This is a good snack for everyone.
We use this when we travel or just fun
time snacking.
You can use 1 to 3 cups of any of these items listed:

title: japanese chicken and pea pods
directions: Mix ingredients (can be leftovers) together in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5, depending on appetite.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in oil.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Add noodles, soups and celery.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter
directions: Get the jelly that's in the refrigerator and the peanut butter from the cabinet.
Use white bread.
Put peanut butter on one bread and jelly on the other bread and eat it in the kitchen.

title: baked pork chops
directions: In a large skillet, brown pork chops in butter.
Place 1/2 of the pork chops in an oven-safe casserole dish.
Cover with 1/2 of the cream of mushroom soup and 1/2 of the onion.
Repeat with remaining pork chops, soup and onion.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: three-two-one dip(ready in 15 minutes or less)
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the cream cheese, soup and pepperoni. Cook and stir over medium-low heat until cheese is melted. Serve warm with assorted crackers.

title: south of the border chicken
directions: Simmer the chicken in a little salted water until tender. Cut into strips and set aside. Meanwhile, brush each tortilla with the oil and cut into 1-inch pieces. Set aside.

title: polynesian turkey salad
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a large bowl and mix well. Combine mayo, lemon juice, curry powder and then stir into turkey mixture. Add oranges and toss gently. Cover and chill. Serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Better if chilled overnight.

title: quick dinner
directions: Heat soup.
Do not add water to soup.
Cook noodles.
Place noodles on long deep plate.
Pour soup over noodles.
Serve with biscuits and a side salad.
Service for 4.

title: strawberry fig pie
directions: Mix Jello, sugar, flour, tapioca and figs in a bowl and let stand for a while. Place in an unbaked pie crust, put pats of butter on top. Mix the 3 tablespoons of butter and flour until crumbly and sprinkle on top. Bake in 350° oven until golden brown.

title: tuna ball
directions: Blend all ingredients by hand or mixer.
Chill 1/2 hour.
Take out and shape into 1 or 2 balls.
Roll in nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: snowball dates
directions: Mix butter, egg, nuts, sugar, Karo syrup and dates.
Cook for 8 minutes, stirring all the time.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper to cool.
Shape in little balls.
Roll in coconut.
Store in tight container.

title: family steak
directions: Brown pieces of meat in oil in large skillet.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Put in 9 x 13 pan.
Add package of dry onion soup mix; sprinkle over top.
Mix can of soup and water; pour over top.
Simmer for 1 hour in oven at 350°.
Use broth to make gravy.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mule ear stir-fry or prickly pear cactus(tohono o'odham)
directions: This recipe is revised for more modern taste.
Nobody is sure what was originally used.
Each family had their own taste.

title: jwiebel kucken(onion pie)
directions: Slice onions and separate into rings.
Fry to a light brown. Place in an unbaked pie shell.
Add caraway seed to the shell. Mix milk, sour cream salt and eggs; pour over onions.
Mix sour cream and flour; add to mixture.
Pour into unbaked crust; place bacon slices on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: In medium bowl, mix ground chuck with beaten egg and 1/2 can of tomato sauce.
Add saltines, green pepper, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Put meat mixture in loaf pan and press to form loaf.
Put remaining tomato sauce on top of meat loaf.
Cover meat loaf with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour and fifteen minutes.

title: chocolate peanut butter chip fudge
directions: Line 8-inch square pan with foil.
In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate chips with milk, vanilla and salt.
Blend well.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter chips.
Stir only to spread the chips out.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Keep corn and peanuts in 250° oven.
I use a metal dishpan. Combine all ingredients except vanilla.
Cook over medium heat to hard cracked stage (pour strands of hot syrup in glass of cold water to check).
Add vanilla and peanuts to syrup.
Pour syrup over corn and mix quickly.
Pour on foil sprayed with Pam.
Spread and make into large pieces with 2 buttered forks.
Store in airtight container.

title: broiled fish
directions: Melt butter; add lemon juice and mustard.
Spread over bottom of a foil pan.
Oil outside of fillets and sprinkle with salt and pepper and parsley flakes.
Place foil pan on cooking grid to preheat, then turn to low.
Place fillets in pan.
Cook with lid on for 5 minutes.
Turn fillets and close lid again.
Done in 3 to 5 minutes.

title: almond cookies
directions: Place sugar, shortening and egg in mixing bowl and mix very well with wooden spoon.
Add flour, salt and baking soda to the shortening mixture.
Mix well and add almond extract.
Makes small balls out of the dough, using a small scoop such as a melon baller or your hands.
Put the balls on ungreased cookie sheets, about 2 inches apart.
Flatten the dough by pressing gently with two fingers.
Put a few drops of red food coloring in a measuring cup, dip end of a chopstick in it and place a red dot in the center of each cookie.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Beat butter until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar, flour and vanilla. Mix in nuts.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.
Roll in confectioners sugar while hot and again while cool.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to package directions, using two 8-inch pans.
When cake is cool, split the 2 layers into 4.

title: pizza crust
directions: Mix and let stand 15 minutes.
Then mix enough flour to make soft dough, about 2 1/2 cups or more.
Spread on greased cookie sheet.
Add ingredients over crust for pizza.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook slowly for 10 minutes.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Remove skin and bones from chicken breasts, then halve lengthwise.
Place each piece of chicken, boned side up, between two pieces of plastic wrap, and pound lightly to 1/4-inch thickness.
Sprinkle lightly with onion salt.
Place 1 to 2 tablespoons of cranberry sauce in the center of each flattened breast, then roll and secure with a toothpick, if necessary. Brush outside with melted butter or margarine.

title: pineapple nut cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening; add eggs.
Stir in pineapple and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and soda; mix well.

title: ginger and peach chicken
directions: Precook and drain pea pods and set aside.
Remove the bones and skin from the chicken breasts and set aside.
Drain and slice water chestnuts and set aside.
Spray a large skillet with nonstick spray coating.
Preheat skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken.
Cook over medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender and no longer pink.
Turn to brown evenly.
Remove from skillet, keep warm.

title: flaming cherries jubilee
directions: Drain cherries reserving syrup.
In Corning Ware dish, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Blend well.
Add cherry syrup and mix well. Put dish on stove and stir until cherry juice mixture thickens and bubbles.
Add cherries.
Turn heat off.

title: tired mama cake
directions: In 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, place cherry pie filling in bottom of pan.
Put crushed pineapple on top of cherry pie filling.
Next sprinkle coconut and nuts over pie filling, then spread the box of yellow cake mix over top.
Cut into small pieces the 2 sticks of butter, and place on top of mix.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, add melted oleo, cocoa and sugar.
Mix together.
Beat in eggs; add salt, Carnation milk and nuts.
Pour in 3 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate cookie cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar. Combine oleo, shortening, cocoa and cold water. Bring this to a boil; pour into the flour-sugar mixture; mix well. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into a greased cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Use pan size 10 x 15-inch approximately and 1 inch sides.

title: scrumptious coconut cake
directions: Bake yellow cake as directed on box in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool.
Using toothpick or fork, punch holes in cake.
Heat pineapple and sugar in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, heating until sugar melts.
Spread over cake.
Prepare vanilla pudding as directed on box and spread over cake, pouring to the edges.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, spread Cool Whip over cake and sprinkle with coconut.

title: igloos or snowballs
directions: Mix ingredients (except cookies).
Spread mixture between three cookies, sticking them together like sandwiches.
After fixing all cookies, let sit in refrigerator overnight or for at least 6 hours. A few hours before serving, cover with whipped cream or Dream Whip. Sprinkle with coconut.
May top each with a cherry.

title: red snapper delight
directions: Steam red snappers and bone them.
Surround them by steamed potatoes.
Trim with cold pineapple rings, tinted green with coloring.
Serve with lemon slices and a rich Hollandaise sauce.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Crush berries.
Mix with water, cornstarch and 1/2 cup sugar. Cook until thickened.
Pour over remaining berries in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, flour and milk.
Pour over berries.
Cook 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove and dot with butter.
Cook another 5 to 10 minutes.

title: paz's catfish with topping
directions: Rinse and pat dry the fillets.
Sprinkle with 3/4 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon black pepper.
Set aside.
Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish lightly and spread spinach over bottom.
Put on the rest of the salt and pepper.
