Spread Parmesan cheese over spinach. Melt 4 tablespoons butter; stir in lemon juice and garlic powder. Brush catfish fillets lightly with this mixture and place fillets on spinach.
Keep the rest of butter mixture.

title: batter and flour mixture for large amount deep-fried chicken
directions: Beat eggs and add milk.
Mix flour, salt, pepper (enough to taste in the flour mixture) and meat tenderizer.
You may also add Cajun spice, if you desire.
Heat oil in deep fryer to 250° or 275°.
Dip chicken in egg and milk mixture and then in flour mixture.
Deep fry for 20 minutes; drain on paper towels and serve.

title: pineapple-carrot bread
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and oil and beat until fluffy.
Add all other ingredients and bake in greased and floured bread pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: spiced chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly oil an 11 x 7-inch baking dish. Combine pepper, salt, allspice, ginger, nutmeg and cloves.
Set aside.
Remove wings tip section and discard or save for soup. Cut remaining pieces of wing apart at the joint.
Place wing pieces in a single layer in oiled baking dish.
Sprinkle with spice mixture.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Turn each piece over and sprinkle with remaining spice mixture.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes. Serve hot or cold.
Makes 96 hors d'oeuvres.

title: chili dip
directions: Brown and drain meat, onion and bell pepper.
Add tomatoes and cheese.
Serve with favorite chips or vegetables.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, then add egg, buttermilk and water. Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and drain.
Combine soup and margarine in saucepan on low heat for 10 minutes.
Put layer of broccoli in baking dish.
Top with 1/2 soup mixture, 1/2 cheese, then another layer of broccoli and the remaining soup and cheese. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Add onion rings and brown slightly.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Combine cake mix, eggs and water in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pan.
Combine granulated sugar, brown sugar and cocoa in small bowl.
Sprinkle over batter.
Pour boiling water over all. Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped topping.

title: linguini salad
directions: Cook and drain linguini.
Prepare other ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix all together except Italian dressing.
Add linguini to mixture.
Pour over Italian dressing and mix well.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Serves 12 or more.
Serve and enjoy.

title: carrot walnut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray 1 loaf pan with Baker's Joy. In mixing bowl, combine flour, nuts, sugars, baking powder, cinnamon and salt. Mix until well blended. Stir in remaining ingredients just until moistened. Pour in pan. Bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pineapple congealed salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese, vinegar, pineapple and nuts in one bowl.
In another bowl, dissolve Jell-O and marshmallows in boiling water.
Place both bowls in refrigerator until set.
Mix the two together in a shallow bowl and return to the refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream softened butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Sift flour, soda and spices together.
Rinse raisins and drain.
Combine with chopped nuts in a separate bowl.
Add approximately 1/8 cup of flour and spice mixture to nuts and raisins.
Mix well.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix the cake mix according to box and bake.
Mix the Eagle Brand milk and the cream of coconut.
Punch holes in the cake and pour Eagle Brand mixture over cake while it is still hot.
Use all of the mixture.
Let it cool.

title: egg brunch
directions: Place bread cubes in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cheese over bread.
Beat eggs with milk, add salt and mustard; pour over bread and cheese.
Add peppers, mushrooms and onions, if desired.
Cover and refrigerate at least 6 hours or overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Brown ground chuck with sliced onions. Add can tomatoes, tomato paste, potatoes, carrots and celery. Add water and bring to boil, then simmer 1 to 2 hours (until vegetables are tender).

title: pork-n-bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Stir in next five ingredients, heat until bubbly.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Cut biscuits in halves to form around the side of the casserole dish.
Place cut side down.
Sprinkle the grated cheese in the middle.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°, or until biscuits are done.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: corn pone pie
directions: Brown meat and onions in shortening, add seasoning and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add kidney beans and corn.
Pour mixture into a 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Top with cornmeal batter.
Bake at 450 degrees for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Stew and bone chicken; reserve 2 cups of broth.
Cut chicken into pieces and place in bottom of baking dish.
Pour drained mixed vegetables over chicken.
Melt oleo; pour over chicken and vegetables.
Sift together dry ingredients (flour, salt, pepper and baking powder).
Add milk; mix well.
Pour over chicken and vegetables.
Heat soup and broth to boiling point.
Pour over ingredients in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple cake with cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix sugar, flour, baking soda and walnuts in a bowl.
Make a well and add 2 eggs (beaten), 1 can pineapple (including juice) and vanilla (1 teaspoon).
Mix with a spoon just to blend.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Let cool.

title: tar heel pie
directions: Pour warm margarine over chocolate chips and stir until melted.
Blend all remaining ingredients.
Stir into chocolate mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until firm.

title: apple pecan cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until frothy. Add sugar, salt, oil, vanilla, lemon juice and rind.
Beat until well blended.
Sift flour, soda and spice together.
Add gradually to egg mixture until well blended.
Stir in apples and pecans. Grease and flour angel food cake pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in
a
1 quart casserole.
Mix lemon juice and water and sprinkle over apples, coating each piece so they will not turn brown.
Mix cinnamon and sugar and sprinkle over apples. Make topping.

title: water chestnuts appetizers
directions: Wrap each chestnut with bacon and secure with toothpick. Brown in 400° oven 20 to 30 minutes or until bacon is crisp. Remove from grease and place in another pan. Bring remaining ingredients to boil. Dip chestnuts and return to hot oven until bubbly.

title: creamy chicken-cheese bake
directions: Place chicken in flat rectangular baking dish, top with cheese.
Mix soup and milk and pour over cheese.
Top with stuffing mix.
Melt butter (oleo) and pour in over stuffing.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: lime punch
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup warm water.
Squeeze lemons and bring to boil in enough water to cover.
Mix and add sugar.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: egg in a glass
directions: Boil egg for 9 minutes.
Break bread apart and put into glass. Add butter.
While eggs are still hot, break open and put into glass.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: beef and vegetable grill
directions: Sprinkle roast with salt; place on a large double sheet of heavy foil.
Pour barbecue sauce over meat.
Place onions and carrots on top of roast and potatoes around edges.
Wrap securely, using double folds.
Place on grill, meat side down; roast over hot coals for 1 1/4 hours.
Replenish coals if necessary.
Turn package over and cook 45 minutes or until meat is tender and vegetables are cooked through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate chip zucchini cake
directions: Cream butter and oil. Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk. Sift dry ingredients together and add to liquids.
Stir in the zucchini. Spoon into a floured 13 x 9 inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes. Test with a toothpick.

title: dessert ice cream sandwiches
directions: Mix together all the ingredients except the ice cream.
Line an ice cube tray or loaf pan with waxed paper.
(An 8 x 8-inch square pan can be used if recipe is doubled.) Press half of the mixture into the tray. Add the ice cream.
Cover with remaining crumb mixture. Store in the freezing unit of refrigerator until serving time.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground meat and drain. Stir in tomato sauce and mixed vegetables.
Place in casserole dish. Spread onion rings over top of meat mixture.
Mix potatoes according to package directions. Spread evenly over top. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: layered chicken salad
directions: Spread lettuce evenly in 4-quart dish. Add celery, water chestnuts, onion and chicken in layers. Pat peas dry and arrange on top layer.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown ground beef, bacon, onion and garlic.
Drain.
Mix and combine with remaining ingredients and bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes or use a slow cooker set on high for 3 to 4 hours.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Bake in a greased and floured pan at 350° until done.

title: banana fruit loaf
directions: Beat eggs, bananas, vanilla, spices and honey together.
Stir together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add flour mixture to banana mixture; beat until smooth.
Fold in raisins and apples.
Spoon into a nonstick pan sprayed with cooking spray. Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Mix melted butter and sugar until creamy, then add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients in heavy kettle until onions are slightly brown.
Stir in the flour; cook 1 minute.
Add the beef broth, beef consomme, pepper and water.
Reduce heat; simmer for 30 minutes.
Add the Port wine and Burgundy, then ladle over slices of toasted French bread and pass the Parmesan cheese. Makes 3 quarts.

title: miniature ham and cheese rolls
directions: Split each package of rolls into 2 layers.
Do not separate into rolls.
Place ham and cheese between layers in foil trays. Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour over bread.
Let stand, uncovered, until margarine sets.
Bake, covered with foil, at 350° for 15 minutes.
May be chilled for 24 hours or frozen before baking.

title: arby's sauce(a copykat recipe)
directions: Mix corn starch and water, set aside.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Combine in blender the first six ingredients and blend until smooth and creamy.
Fold in the remaining ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: honey-orange chicken
directions: In large skillet, brown chicken in butter on both sides.
Add orange juice, honey, onion, pepper and season with salt to taste. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until tender.
Remove chicken from pan and arrange over rice on platter.
Keep warm.
Stir wine into flour and blend well.
Add to pan drippings and cook, stirring, until thickened.
Add orange peel and sections and heat through.
Spoon over chicken.
Garnish with orange slices.
Yields 6 servings.

title: lazy pierogi
directions: Steam cabbage until tender.
Drain.
Saute onion in butter until clear.
Add drained cabbage and saute about 5 minutes more. Add salt and pepper.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Gently stir in 1 cup blueberries.
Fill muffin cups half full. Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: sweet dinner rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown sausage in skillet.
Add onion and apple and saute.
Drain well.
Mix sausage mixture with remaining ingredients in a medium bowl.
Pour into greased and floured casserole.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: "yummy" pumpkin pie cake
directions: Beat together pumpkin, eggs, sugar, milk, cinnamon and nutmeg. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan, ungreased.
Sprinkle with yellow cake mix over pumpkin mixture and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for an hour or longer.
Test with toothpick when it comes out clean.
Serves 15.

title: creamy onion gravy
directions: In 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, melt butter; stir in flour until smooth.
Cook 2 minutes or until lightly browned, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir milk and water into saucepan until smooth; stir in soup mix.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to low; simmer, uncovered, 8 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 2 cups.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine dry ingredients; add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Beat on medium for 2 minutes.
Stir in boiling water.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes in greased pan.

title: southern chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together except cornflake crumbs and margarine.
Place in casserole.
Combine cornflake crumbs and margarine and place on top.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Clean shrimp, wash, cook and cut up.
Mix all ingredients together, put in refrigerator until time to be served and place on lettuce.
Top with an olive.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Coat with mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Place into greased tube pan, sprinkling pecans between layers.

title: apple salad
directions: Cook pineapple, flour and sugar until thick.
Add chopped apples.
Stir and sprinkle top with nuts.
Then top with Cool Whip.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix flour, butter, 2 tablespoons powdered sugar and nuts together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Cool 15 minutes.

title: shipwreck
directions: Mix all together.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: moist lemon cake
directions: Mix together cake mix and pudding.
In large bowl, beat eggs good.
Add corn oil and water to eggs.
Stir in dry ingredients. Beat 4 minutes.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan (grease and flour pan). Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
When done and while hot, punch holes in cake and glaze.

title: banana punch
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Let stand to cool.
Mix bananas and lemon juice in bowl.
Combine syrup and banana mixture into punch bowl.
Add concentrated orange juice and pineapple juice. Mix well.
Add sherbet at serving time.
Yields 30 servings.

title: choco peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat brown sugar, peanut butter and margarine until fluffy.
Blend in water, egg and vanilla and add combined oats, flour and baking soda.
Mix well.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Using bottom of glass dipped in sugar, press into 1/4-inch thick circles.
Bake for 5 to 8 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Melt chocolate pieces as package directs; stir in vegetable shortening, mixing until smooth.
Top each cookie with 1/2 teaspoon melted chocolate.
Chill until set.
Store tightly.
Cover.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: lasagne noodles with ravioli filling
directions: Mix ingredients, except noodles and sauce.
No boil lasagne noodles may be used.
Follow directions on box for baking in a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Bring to boil the white vinegar, salad oil and sugar. Add celery seed. While liquid is still hot, pour over the cabbage mixture. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Toss next morning. Will keep in refrigerator until used up.

title: double decker pastry
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
The dough will be very rich.
Roll out dough to fit bottom of a cookie sheet with sides.
Roll dough about two times as thick as pie dough.
Sprinkle on nut mixture to cover first layer of dough.
Roll out another piece of dough and cover nut mixture.
Spread filling of your choice on second layer of dough.
Cover with lattice topping.
Sprinkle some of the nut mixture on top,
Bake at 350 for 25-30 minutes or until nicely browned to a golden color.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: sweet & sour chicken
directions: Combine ingredients and pour over chicken. Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: bobbi's pie crust(this is enough crust for 2 double crusted pies)
directions: Mix the flour, Crisco, sugar and salt with fork.
Beat the vinegar, egg and water in separate dish.
Combine all of the ingredients and mix until moist.
With hands, mold dough into 4 balls.
Chill at least 15 minutes before using.
This dough can be frozen or keeps very well in refrigerator in tight container.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook onions in margarine until soft, do not brown.
Add soups and water.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Use 3/4-inch slice of French bread, dried in oven, for each serving.
Place bread in soup bowl.
Fill with soup.
Place slice of Provolone, Natural or Swiss cheese on top.
Broil 3 to 4 minutes or until cheese melts. Yields 6 servings.

title: hamburger corn casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Put into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: house punch
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly, adding 7-Up last.
Chill and serve.
This can be mixed in advance and made into slush.
Makes approximately 20 servings.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add flour and eggs; beat well.
Add buttermilk and lemon juice.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Use a 1-quart casserole dish.
Drain artichokes and smash with back of fork into casserole dish.
Add all other ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Mix well. Top with bread crumbs and bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Serve with plain or garlic bagel chips.

title: chocolate pocket cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix sugars, shortening, peanut butter and egg.
Stir in flour.
Chill dough.
Mold dough around each chocolate square.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Bake about 10 minutes or until light golden brown.
Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: cranberry-pear chicken
directions: Trim and discard visible fat from chicken.
In a large nonstick skillet, over medium-high heat, heat 1 1/2 teaspoons oil. Sprinkle chicken breasts lightly with salt and pepper.
Brown about 2 minutes pre side.
Remove from pan and reserve.
Add remaining oil to skillet and cook onions until softened, about 4 minutes.
Add pears, cranberries, cinnamon and ginger.
Stir to combine well.
Place chicken on top of fruit and onions.
Cover and simmer 10 to 12 minutes until cooked through.
Serve with brown, wild rice.

title: mile high pie
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, nuts and melted oleo.
Stir and spread on cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Stir several times.
Sprinkle 2/3 crumbs in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Save the rest for topping.
Combine and beat 20 minutes the strawberries, sugar, lemon juice, salt and egg whites.
Fold in Cool Whip. Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Freeze.
Serve frozen.
Keep frozen.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all together in a large jar.
Use 1 or 2 teaspoons to a cup of hot water.

title: corn salad
directions: Toss gently.
Refrigerate overnight to allow flavors to blend.
Serve.

title: drunken beef
directions: Take rump roast.
Rub with pepper and oregano.
Put in open pan for 1 hour.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next day, slice thin and add onion soup, beer and bourbon.
Cover and bake at 325° for 4 hours.
Serve on hard rolls.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream together with electric mixer, shortening, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Roll into balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll balls in 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon, mixed.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet.
Remove to cool on cooling rack.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Dissolve Jell-O, sugar and salt in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries and stir until thawed.
Chill until thick.
Prepare Dream Whip as directed, and fold into thickened Jell-O mixture. Break cake into small pieces in bottom of 2 (8 1/2 x 12-inch) Pyrex.
Pour Jell-O mixture over cake.
Refrigerate until set.

title: stuffed dates
directions: Slowly add 4 cups sugar to milk, blending well.
Mix in salt and extracts.
Sprinkle remaining sugar on a board and knead fondant until smooth and creamy, working in sugar.
Wrap in foil and keep in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Stuff the dates and top with walnut or pecan halves.
Makes 7 to 8 dozen dates.

title: lo-cal pina colada squares
directions: Mix gelatin, Sweet 'N Low and pineapple juice in pan.
Heat just to boil.
Stir in ice milk and extract.
Pour into 8-inch square pan.
Chill.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Chill for at least 2 hours. Serve with fresh vegetables, such as carrots, cauliflower and celery.

title: swiss 'n chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except walnuts. Spoon into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with walnuts, if desired. Bake for 40 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Serves 6.

title: my favorite squash casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Melt margarine and mix with bread crumbs.
Cover bottom of casserole dish with 1/2 of bread crumbs.
Pour mixed ingredients over them and then cover the top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Place sugar and flour in a bowl and mix well.
Bring margarine, butter, cocoa and water to a rapid boil.
Remove from heat and pour over sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Add vanilla, soda, buttermilk and eggs.
Beat well with an electric mixer.
Pour in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Combine butter and sugar; cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and sour cream, mixing well.
Combine next 5 ingredients. Add to batter and mix well.
Pour batter into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon; mix well.
Sprinkle evenly over batter.
Cover and chill overnight.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until cake tests done.
Makes 15 servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour (30 minutes covered and 30 minutes uncovered).

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a saucepan, mix water, tomato paste, onion, garlic, bell pepper, mushrooms and oregano.
Cook about 30 minutes over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Peel eggplant; slice lengthwise.
Brown and drain ground meat.

title: potato cheddar soup
directions: 1. Mix crumbled bacon and croutons. Set aside in soup kettle.
2. Saute onions and garlic in butter.
3. Add chicken broth, potatoes, parsley, salt, and pepper.
Simmer 20-30 minutes until tender. Remove from heat.
4. Process or blend until smooth. Add cheddar, warm
gently. Serve with bacon crouton mix.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream together shortening and sugar.
Add egg and mix well; stir in molasses.
Sift together dry ingredients and combine with molasses mixture.
Chill thoroughly.
Roll dough into balls 1-inch in diameter; roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Store in covered container with a slice of bread to keep softened (a slice of apple will also work).
Leave bread slice out if hard cookies are desired.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain and chop.
Mix all ingredients, except butter and dressing.
Pour into greased dish.
Melt butter and stir in dressing.
Place on top of mixture.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli and ham
directions: Combine macaroni, cheese, ham and broccoli.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch and water until thick and clear.
Remove from heat and stir in Jell-O and strawberries; let cool.
Mix together Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar.
Add milk if too thick.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour and mix thoroughly.
Put dough in refrigerator for a couple of hours (cover bowl with Reynolds Wrap).
Roll dough thin.
Brush with beaten egg.
Decorate with colored sugar or sprinkles.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until set.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Beat shortening at medium speed with electric mixer until soft and creamy; gradually add brown sugar, beating well.
Add egg and molasses, mixing well.
Combine flour and next 5 ingredients; add to shortening mixture, mixing well.
Cover; chill 2 hours.

title: zippy horseradish dip for veggies
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients and chill.
Serve as dip for fresh vegetables such as broccoli, cauliflower, cherry tomatoes, mushrooms, carrots, green pepper and squash.

title: cherry limeade
directions: Mix limeade and soda together. Add juice from cherries. Squeeze in juice from lime. Mix well. Garnish with cherries.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Saute onion, garlic, butter and ground beef.
Add cream of mushroom soup, tomato paste and green chillies and cook.
Place 1/2 package of tortilla chips in a greased baking dish.
Pour meat mixture over chips.
Top with remaining tortilla chips.
Sprinkle top with 3 cups grated cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Serve with sour cream.

title: english trifle
directions: Line dish with ladyfingers.
Mix jello in separate dish. Pour over ladyfingers.
Place peaches on top.
Let set.
Make instant pudding, pour over jello and let set.
Layer with Cool Whip.

title: chow mein hot dish
directions: Mix all together.
Put in a casserole.
Bake, covered, for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: soy sauce marinade
directions: Combine ingredients.
Use to marinate beef, pork or chicken before grilling or broiling.
Can also be used for marinating stir-fry meats.
Marinate 8 hours or overnight for best results.

title: chicken enchilada ring
directions: Separate crescent rolls and spread on round pizza pan to make a circle. Mix remaining ingredients and spoon onto each crescent strip. Roll crescent up and form a ring. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: tortilla chip dip
directions: Brown ground beef, sausage and onion.
Drain.
Mix all together in crock-pot and let simmer.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni as directed.
Add chicken, mushrooms, soy sauce and sour cream.
Blend well.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease 3 loaf pans.
Evenly divide mixture and place in loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini stew
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients in oil until almost tender.
Add tomato sauce, water, parsley, basil, oregano, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Add zucchini and cook this together until the zucchini is done.

title: ham and cheese calzones
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

Mix first four ingredients; set aside. Press biscuits flat to approximately 5-inch diameter circles. On each of the five flattened biscuits put dollop of ham mixture. Place another flattened biscuit over the mound and seal the edges. Repeat for the rest of the remaining biscuits.
Brush with egg and bake until golden, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: turkey chop suey
directions: Drain vegetables, reserving liquid.
In large saucepan, saute onion
in a tablespoon of butter until translucent.
Add bouillon, water,
soy
and
Worcestershire sauces and turkey. Combine cornstarch	with
1/4 cup water until mixed well.
Add to
turkey mixture.
Stir
until
thickened.
Add vegetables. Heat until warmed through.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: lemon marinade for fish or meat
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour over fish or meat, cover and chill for at least 3 hours, turning at least twice.

title: 7 layer dip
directions: Spread bean dip in shallow, 2-quart pan or dish.
Arrange avocado over bean dip.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and garlic salt in a small bowl.
Combine sour cream and taco mix; spread over avocado.
Top with a layer of tomatoes and black olives.
Sprinkle with cheese and onions.
Serve with unsalted chips.
Yields 6 cups.

title: chocolate chow mein noodle treats
directions: Melt first 2 ingredients together slowly in double boiler.
Mix in salted cocktail peanuts and chow mein noodles.
Shape to desired size and cool.
Freezes very well.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Cut up food cake in small squares.
Mix sour cream, milk, powdered sugar, and cool whip.
Combine strawberries and glaze together.
Layer cake first, then add a layer of sour cream mix, then layer of strawberry and glaze mix.
Repeat.
Letting top layer be strawberry and glaze mix, in a trifle bowl.

title: nacho dip
directions: Put ingredients in crock-pot on low setting for 3 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: sauce for grilling
directions: Just mix with an electric mixer until well-blended.
Brush on meat while grilling.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook ground beef or chicken. Set aside.
Mix together tomatoes, sauce and Mexicorn.
Spread on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan 6 corn tortillas.
Put on layer of beef or chicken, then layer of tomatoes and corn, then layer of cheese.
Layer 6 tortillas, etc., until all layers are on.
Last layer on top is cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until cheese is brown at 350°.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand.
Roll into balls.
Roll balls in melted chocolate.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in a large container.
For each cup of hot chocolate, use 1/3 cup of mix in cup.
Add boiling water.

title: mushroom spread
directions: Cook and stir mushrooms and onion in skillet over medium heat until all liquid is absorbed. Put mushroom-onion mixture, cream cheese, salt and basil in blender. Cover and blend on high speed, occasionally scraping sides of container, about 2 minutes. Add parsley and cover; blend 30 seconds longer. Cover and chill 3 hours. Serve with round buttery crackers.

title: meat sauce
directions: Mix well and marinate beef or chicken 4 to 8 hours before cooking.

title: glazed ham
directions: Combine ingredients.
Brush mixture on ham frequently during last hour of baking.
Makes 1 cup of liquid, enough for a 10 to 15 pound ham.
Also good on roast chicken or turkey.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Blend mushroom soup with 1 can of water, stirring until smooth.
Spread Stove Top stuffing in greased casserole.
Add onion flakes, garlic salt and soy sauce to soup mixture.
Place pork chops on stuffing and pour soup mixture to cover.
Bake, covered, for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: blushing pickled eggs
directions: Put eggs in a quart jar.
Mix together beet juice, vinegar, bay leaf, cloves, salt and garlic.
Heat, but do not boil.
Add to eggs in jar.
Store in refrigerator at least 24 hours.

title: cheryl's stuffed mushrooms
directions: Prepare mushrooms by washing and removing stems.
Stems are not needed.
Place mushroom tops in boiling water and boil for 7 minutes or until tender.
Remove from water carefully and place on cookie tray that has been sprayed with Pam.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Mix well; shape into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press each ball with fork to about 1/4 inch each.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Prebake the pie shell for 10 minutes.
Beat the egg yolks in a bowl until foamy.
Add the condensed milk to the yolks and beat them together.
Stir in the Key lime juice and put the filling aside.
Beat the egg whites, gradually adding the sugar and cream of tartar, until peaks form.
Add about a quarter of it to the filling.
Add the filling to the prebaked pie shell.
Top with the meringue, taking care to seal the meringue to the pie crust.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until meringue is golden brown. Let cool for a couple of hours before refrigerating.

title: sugar-free coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: easy dip
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate for a couple of hours.

title: eggplant istanbul
directions: Put all of above ingredients into a saucepan and simmer 15 minutes.
Add
salt
to
taste.
Serve with lemon wedges or spoon over
fluffy steamed rice; add an extra squeeze of lemon juice.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Cream sugar, oil, eggs and pumpkin, then add remaining ingredients.
Beat and pour into greased 10 x 13-inch cookie pan. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool before frosting.

title: reta's chocolate pudding
directions: Mix and add to 2 cups milk that has been heated.
Cook until thick, then add butter and vanilla.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Fry hamburger and onion until color changes.
Cook noodles. Mix rest of ingredients together.
Put grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: blueberry nut crunch
directions: Grease baking dish.
Pour pineapple into pan; top with blueberries.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup of sugar, dry cake mix and then nuts.
Drizzle melted margarine over top and sprinkle with remaining sugar.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except tortillas and cheese.
Place a layer of tortillas, torn into pieces, in a casserole dish.
Layer with all ingredients, ending with cheese.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 30 - 45 minutes.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar, eggs, salt, vanilla, milk and flour.
Beat after each addition.
Gently add chips.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour in mix.
Bake 30 minutes or until light brown.
Cool and cut.

title: vegetable beef and biscuit casserole
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, cook beef until browned, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix well with beater.
Pour in unbaked pie shell at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
When cool, spread Cool Whip on top.

title: tortilla strips
directions: Cut tortillas into 1/2-inch strips.
Set aside.
Combine salt, cumin and red pepper.
Place in a shaker.
In a large saucepan or deep-fat fryer, heat about 1 1/2 inches of shortening.
Fry small batches of tortilla strips in hot oil for 1/2 to 1 1/2 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove strips and drain on paper towels. Immediately shake some of the seasoning mixture over hot strips. Store tightly covered.

title: orange mousse
directions: Mix sugar, water and jello together until well mixed and dissolved.
Add sour cream and beat until cream is mixed well. Add pineapple and oranges.
Mix all together.
Let set for 4 to 5 hours.

title: chicken and asparagus
directions: First rub chicken breasts with olive oil to keep meat moist. In a baking dish, lay chicken breasts flat and not overlapping into pan.
Spread a thin layer of sour cream over chicken.
Lay asparagus spears on top.
Shake on Mrs.
Dash seasoning.

title: slow-pot chicken barbecue
directions: Cut up chicken; add other ingredients in crock-pot and cook for 5 1/2 hours or until chicken is done.
Also may be cooked in slow oven.

title: mustard fried catfish
directions: Marinate catfish filets with mustard on each side. Sprinkle with Old Bay seasoning and then apply seafood breader. Fry until golden brown on each side.

title: garlic bread
directions: Split loaf in half. Spread margarine on each half. Combine garlic powder and Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle bread halves.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.

title: shish kabob marinade
directions: For use with 2 pounds of meat.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Remove bones and skin from salmon and separate into flakes. Melt oil in frying pan.
Add onion and cook until yellow, then add bread crumbs, salt and pepper; brown lightly.
Put salmon liquor into cup and add enough milk to make one cup.
Combine salmon, crumbs and liquor.
Add lemon juice, rind, parsley and egg; blend, being careful not to mash salmon.
Pour into greased 8-inch casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.
Very good with peas.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and Cool Whip together.
Put in 1 inch balls, roll in powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: homemade drop noodles
directions: Mix all ingredients, using enough water to make a sticky dough.
Drop pinches of dough (about 1/2 teaspoon per pinch) into boiling, salted water.
When noodles come to the top, boil for 5 more minutes; drain.
Serve with soup.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt butter and Velveeta cheese in microwave.
Stir in sugar, cocoa, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Spread in greased pan and refrigerate.

title: dee dee's butterscotch brownies
directions: Cook butter and brown sugar over low heat until bubbly.
Cool. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in baking dish.
Cover top with bacon slices.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Pour boiling water over Jell-O, marshmallows, lemon juice and salt.
Let set in refrigerator until it starts thickening.
Whip cream with the sugar, stir remaining ingredients into Jell-O mixture adding the whipped cream last.

title: morning blaster or anytime protein shake
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Makes about a 12 ounce glassful.

title: egg strata
directions: Butter 18 x 26 inch pan. Butter sliced bread. Place bread slices buttered side up in pan. Put sausage on top of bread. Put cheese on top of sausage. Add another layer of bread. Mix milk and eggs together. Pour on top of mixture in pan. Let sit overnight. Bake at 350 degrees for 40 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean. Serve about 75 peoples.

title: tasty chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (except potato chips) and pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with additional almonds and the crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: mini morsel shortbread squares
directions: In large mixer bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Gradually beat in flour.
Stir in 1 cup morsels.
Press onto bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 33 minutes or just until top begins to brown. Immediately sprinkle with remaining morsels.
Let stand for 5 minutes or until soft; spread.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Cool on wire racks.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on bottom of pizza pan to form crust. Spread hash browns and Cheddar cheese on crust.
Mix eggs, milk, salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Pour over pizza.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: julie's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together oleo and sugars.
Add eggs, vanilla and soda; mix well.
Mix in flour; stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light golden brown.
Allow to cool for about 2 minutes on cookie sheet before removing cookies to cooling rack.

title: meat and corn casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper until tender.
Cook noodles until tender; drain.
Add all ingredients to meat mixture.
In a baking dish, alternate layers of noodles and meat; top with cheese.
Bake at 375° until cheese melts.

title: bread pudding
directions: Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set pan in larger pan that has a little water in it.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until set.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Spray crock-pot (inside) with Pam nonstick spray.
Mix together soups and pour over chicken.
Brown chicken breasts.
Put 3 chicken breasts in crock-pot.
Put half of soup mixture over chicken and sprinkle dried onion flakes and garlic powder to taste on top of soup mixture.
Repeat process with rest of chicken and ingredients.

title: meat balls and rice
directions: Blend ground chuck, Lipton onion soup, egg and bread.
Brown golf ball size meat balls in skillet.
Blend large tomato sauce and Lipton onion soup package.
Pour tomato blend over browned meat balls; turn on low and simmer until meat is cooked through and sauce thickened.
Prepare rice (2 cups) according to box directions. Place in large dish.
Pour meat balls and sauce over rice.

title: golden chicken lasagna
directions: Arrange 1/2 of the noodles in a 13 x 9-inch greased baking dish.
Mix cottage cheese and egg together.
Add mushrooms to this mixture.
Spread this mixture over the noodles.
Top with chicken. Mix soup, milk and basil together.
Spread 1/2 of this mixture over the chicken.
Sprinkle half of the two cheeses on this. Repeat noodles, sauce and cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: fried ice cream
directions: Scoop ice cream into balls, about 1/2 cup sized balls. Place onto a baking sheet. Freeze until hard. In a shallow dish, combine corn flakes and cinnamon. In another dish, beat egg whites until foamy. Roll ice cream in egg whites, then in corn flake mixture. Freeze again for 3 hours. In a deep-fryer or in a saucepan, using a slotted spoon, put balls in oil for about 2 to 3 minutes. At the same time, fry the tortillas until crispy, then sprinkle cinnamon and sugar on them. Then place ice cream balls on tortilla and serve with Cool Whip and chocolate syrup or whatever you
like. A real crowd pleaser.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together well.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
May be frozen.

title: vegetable lo mein
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Meanwhile, in a cup, combine chicken broth, soy sauce and cornstarch until smooth; set aside.
In a wok or large saucepan, heat oil until hot.
Add mushrooms, celery and red peppers; cook and stir until celery is almost crisp-tender, about 3 minutes.
Stir in bean sprouts, scallions, snow peas and cornstarch mixture.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and boils, about 1 minute.
Drain spaghetti; toss with vegetables. Serve hot.
Makes 4 portions.

title: garlic-cheese souffle
directions: Place garlic, thyme, bay leaf, olive oil and water in a small heavy saucepan.
Simmer, uncovered, over low heat for 30 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix all the ingredients into a dough; add 1 cup currants, rinsed and drained, and work into dough.
Roll out on a floured board; cut into 2 1/2 or 3 inch circles.
Fry on lightly greased electric frypan or griddle at 350°.
Fry until cookies puff up and look shiny, then turn over and cook until finished.

title: five minute fudge
directions: Mix milk, sugar, and salt together in sauce pan.
Heat to boiling (medium heat) Cook for 5 minutes.
Stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients stir until marshmallows melt.
Pour into buttered pan.
Let cool and then cut.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Mix flour and sugar in top of double boiler. Add beaten egg, stirring to make smooth. Combine pineapple and lemon juices. Add to egg mixture. Cook over hot water until thickened and smooth, stirring constantly. Cool. Stir in whipped cream just before serving.

title: ranch style steaks
directions: Mix salad dressing, water and olive oil.
Grill 1 1/2 pounds flank steaks for 4 minutes on one side.
Brush top with half the mixture.
Grill 3 minutes longer.
Turn and grill 4 minutes.
Brush on remaining mixture.
Grill 3 minutes longer.
Grill 3 to 5 minutes more.
Slice diagonally.
Serves 4.

title: hershey brownie
directions: Bake 350- 30 minutes; cool.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Bake potatoes and set aside.
Mix all ingredients together in saucepan.
Cook on low to medium heat.
Thicken with about 2 tablespoons of flour.
Mix flour with a little water before before putting in pan with cooked ingredients.
Stir often.

title: donna's white fudge
directions: In heavy sauce pan combine butter, milk sugar.
On medium heat bring to a boil and boil for 3 1/2 minutes add chips, vanilla. take off heat.
Right away add marshmallow cream beat with mixer till well mixed add nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13 buttered pan.
Let cool cut and enjoy.

title: anise cookies
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly.
Add sugar gradually, continuing to beat until light in color.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Blend into egg mixture.
Mix in anise seed.
Drop from a teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Let cookies dry on sheet 12 hours.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: angel fluff
directions: Mix all together.
Refrigerate at least an hour before serving.

title: mincemeat cake
directions: Combine mincemeat, water, sugar and shortening in a saucepan. Bring to boil and cook 3 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Remove from heat and cool thoroughly.
In a large bowl, sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to cold mincemeat mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Bake in 9 or 10-inch tube pan for 55 to 60 minutes. Cool 4 to 6 hours before cutting.
Remove from pan 1 hour after cooking.

title: kathie's brie and bread
directions: Scoop out the insides of a round loaf of rye bread.
Cube Brie cheese and sprinkle it with 2 tablespoons each of dill and garlic. Put the cubed Brie on the inside of the loaf and place the top back on the loaf.
Wrap in aluminum foil and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Arrange on platter and dip in.

title: pink and pretty parfait
directions: To sweeten rice, add 2 tablespoons of sugar to the water in which the rice is cooked. Chill.

title: beef stew
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and dredge meat. Brown meat pieces on all sides in hot shortening. Place in Dutch oven; browned meat, soup, water, onion and basil. Cover and bake at 375 degrees for 1 hour. Add vegetables and water. Cover and return to oven for another hour or until vegetables are tender.

title: pretzel salad(yield: 12 servings)
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and confectioners sugar together.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Cream together sugar and cream cheese.
Add Cool Whip.
Spread mixture on cooled pretzel crust.
Mix jello with boiling water and strawberries.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Strawberries will thaw and cause jello to set.
Pour over cheese mixture and chill.

title: chicken pockets
directions: Mix the chicken, cream cheese and milk together in a large bowl (hands work best); set aside.
Take the rolls out of the can and separate.
Taking 2 at a time, pinch 2 triangles of dough together to form a rectangle.
Separate chicken evenly onto rectangles.
Take corners of each rectangle and fold into ball. Dip ball into melted butter and then into crouton crumbs.
Place balls on a greased cookie sheet and place in preheated 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes, until dough has risen and browned.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns and vegetables.
Toss together with tuna. Mix potato soup, sour cream and onion together and stir into vegetables.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Mix crushed Corn Chex with melted butter in Ziploc bag and shake to mix.
Sprinkle on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet and drain.
Mix beans, tomatoes, seasonings and browned ground beef in a large pot.
Bring to a boil.
Cut heat to simmer for 35 minutes, stirring often.
When mixture is almost done, add cabbage and cook for 10 minutes or until cabbage is done.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine the first seven ingredients until blended.
Stir in eggs well, but do not beat.
Fold in pecans.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 375° for approximately 50 minutes to 1 hour, until set in the middle and golden brown.
Watch the crust carefully and cover lightly with aluminum foil if it browns before the filling sets.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookie dough and pat into pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Beat the cream cheese and Cool Whip together.
Spread on cookie.
Arrange fruit on top of cream cheese mixture.

title: tossed salad dressing
directions: Blend well and pour over tossed salad.

title: saucy asparagus
directions: In 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, combine soup and milk. Heat to boiling, stirring often.
Add asparagus.
Cover and cook over low heat 10 minutes, or until asparagus is tender, stirring occasionally.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.
Serves 8.

title: jiffy salmon patties
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Reserve 1/3 cup of the liquid. Combine
salmon
with
chopped green onions, parsley and bread crumbs.
Add
the
beaten
eggs,
mustard, lemon juice and the remaining liquid.
Shape into patties and fry over medium heat until lightly brown on both sides.	Makes 12 patties.

title: arroz con gandules(rice and beans)
directions: In medium pot, boil 3 cups of water and oil. When boiling, add all ingredients and lower flame to minimum. When water is dissolved, stir. Leave for 2 to 5 minutes. Serve hot.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Combine milk and butter in a saucepan and bring to boiling point.
In a separate bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, flour and vanilla.
Combine milk mixture and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick sticky rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Separate biscuits, cut in half and roll into balls; set aside.
Melt butter and set aside.
Combine in a bowl brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans; mix well.
Dip biscuit balls first in melted butter and then in sugar mixture.
Arrange in a greased round cake pan, leaving space between each ball for spreading.
Combine remaining sugar mixture with melted butter and mix well.
Spoon over the biscuit ball.
Drizzle over top of that the dark corn syrup.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Invert onto a plate and serve warm.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix and chill ingredients.
Serve in a bowl and pass mayonnaise dressing.
Leftovers come in handy in making this salad.

title: top of the stove cookies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, cocoa (if desired) and milk.
Boil 2 minutes, then add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix thoroughly and spoon out.

title: red raspberry brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place water in a small saucepan and heat to simmer.
Remove from heat.
Add red raspberry herb tea bags, submerging bags completely.
Set aside to cool; then remove tea bags squeezing liquid from bags.
Place chocolate and butter in top portion of double boiler and heat over approximately 2 inches of water.
Heating on low, let chocolate and butter melt, mixing until well blended.

title: chocolate banana bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together all-purpose and whole wheat flours, baking powder, soda and salt; set aside.
In a small mixer bowl, beat sugar and margarine with electric mixture until light, scraping sides of bowl often.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each addition.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Add flour mixture and banana alternately to sugar mixture, beating until smooth after each addition.
Fold in coconut and chocolate pieces.

title: strawberry cake 2
directions: Let strawberries thaw to room temperature.
Mix into bowl the cake mix, jello mix, Wesson oil, 1/2 cup of strawberry juice from frozen strawberries, self-rising flour and eggs.
Blend well.
In a separate bowl, mix together 1 cup strawberries, pecans and coconut.
Mix well, then add 1/2 of mixture into cake batter and reserve other 1/2 for frosting.
Bake cake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: angel food torte
directions: In a bowl, combine milk, pudding mix and pineapple; mix well. Fold in the whipped topping.
Cut cake horizontally into three layers.
Place the bottom layer on a serving plate; spread with 1 1/3 cups pineapple mixture.
Repeat.
Place top layer on cake; spread with remaining pineapple mixture.
Sprinkle with coconut and garnish with cherries. Yield: 12 servings.

title: hot chili dip
directions: Melt the cheese, chili and sour cream.
Mix thoroughly.
Bring to a simmer.
Serve in a chafing dish to keep warm.

title: perfect pie meringue
directions: In deep bowl, beat egg whites with vanilla and cream of tartar until soft peaks form.
Do not overbeat egg whites before adding sugar or meringue will leak, making top of pie filling moist and slippery.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff, glossy peak forms and sugar dissolves.
Rub some meringue between your fingers; you shouldn't feel any sugar granules.
Spread meringue over hot filling.
To prevent meringue from shrinking while baking, seal to edges of pastry.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until meringue is golden.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix the eggs, sugar, oil, pumpkin and flour.
Mix baking powder, cinnamon, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: aunt dennie's kibbie
directions: Soak wheat in a large bowl covered with water (about 15 minutes).
Then drain and press water out by grabbing handfuls of wheat and squeezing excess water out.
Set aside.

title: bonny's chicken salad
directions: Cook and dice chicken breasts in food processor until fine. Pulp onion in food processor.
Add celery; again, pulp in food processor.
Squeeze lemon over chicken.
Add remaining ingredients and serve on croissants.

title: crab salad
directions: Break crab meat up into chunks.
Add seasonings and vegetables and mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate in covered dish overnight for added flavor.

title: sally lunn bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix well 1 cup flour, sugar, yeast and salt; set aside. Heat milk, water and butter over low heat until very warm (120° to 130°). Gradually beat liquid mixture into flour mixture. Beat at medium speed 2 minutes.

Add eggs and 1 cup flour. Beat at high speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally. Stir in enough remaining flour to make a stiff batter; cover. Let rise about 1 hour until doubled. Stir down; spoon into well greased and floured 9-inch tube pan. Cover. Let rise about 45 minutes until doubled. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until top is golden. Turn out on rack. Serve warm or cold. Best served warm with butter and/or marmalade. Leftovers are great toasted and buttered.

title: green salad
directions: In small bowl, mix lime jello with 1 1/2 cups water; stir until jello dissolves. In separated small bowl, combine next 3 ingredients; set aside. In small saucepan, combine 1/2 cup water, marshmallows and reserved pineapple juice; cook over low heat until marshmallows melt. Put jello in refrigerator to thicken; when it is thickened, fold other ingredients into jello. Pour into bowl and let congeal.

title: frosty strawberry squares
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, walnuts and butter (with pastry blender). Spread mixture evenly in shallow baking pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spread 2/3 of this crumb mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: green beans with mushrooms
directions: Place water, salt and green beans in a saucepan; cover and bring to a boil over high heat.
Clean mushrooms and set aside. Slice the mushrooms; add to green beans when the water begins to boil.
Cover and cook over direct heat until beans and mushrooms are tender.
Remove from heat; drain and add butter.
Cooking time is 8 to 10 minutes.

title: soy chicken
directions: Cut up chicken in bite size pieces.
Shake in a bag of flour. Fry in deep fat fryer.
While chicken is frying, mix together soy and sugar.
Add a pinch of salt and monosodium glutamate.
Add slices of ginger root and sesame oil for added flavor.
Cook the sauce over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Set it on warm heat.
As you fry the chicken, immediately set it in the sauce, making sure it is well coated.
Let it drain on a cookie rack with a cookie sheet underneath to catch the drippings.
Keep it in the oven until you are ready to eat it.
Happy dining!

title: soft baked custard
directions: Scald milk.
Beat together eggs, sugar and salt.
Add hot milk slowly to mixture.
Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg. Place baking dish in pan of hot water and bake until a silver knife comes out clean.

title: glazed onions
directions: Cut whole onions in half and place in casserole dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spread 1 teaspoon of butter and 1 teaspoon of honey over onions.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: grilled pork chops
directions: Rub chops with salt and pepper.
Soak in vinegar overnight. Turn the next day.
Grill over charcoal and baste with barbecue sauce.
Yield: Your choice.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Place bread on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with ham or bacon, then cheese.
Set aside.
Combine eggs, mustard, milk, salt and pepper; beat well.
Pour over ingredients in pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, mix crushed corn flakes and melted butter; sprinkle over top of souffle.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all together and cover with slices of onion and bacon. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in casserole dish until onion and bacon are done and dish is done around edges.

title: suzie's overnight coffeecake* * * * *
directions: Eunie is a high school friend from Iowa who has published two cookbooks and is working on a third.
I tried to call her three times to get permission to use this recipe.
She's a great gal so I'm sure she won't mind.
Suzy is the owner of a bed and breakfast inn here in Salado, TX.

title: kart wheels
directions: Heat the oven to 375°.
Mix flour, margarine, sugar, baking powder and just enough milk until dough forms.
(If dough seems dry, mix in more milk, 1 teaspoon at a time.) Divide dough into 6 equal parts.
Shape each part into a ball.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet; flatten slightly.
Make an indentation, 1 3/4-inches in diameter and about 3/4-inch deep in center of each flattened ball.
Fill each indention with about 2 tablespoons jam.
Bake until the edges begin to brown, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 6 Kart Wheels.

title: arthur treachers fish
directions: Soak fish in just enough buttermilk to cover.
Refrigerate in covered container with 1 lemon sliced over it for 2 to 3 hours to remove fishy taste.
Heat 1 1/2 pints oil in heavy 2 1/2-quart saucepan.
Drain off milk.
Cut fillets in half and dredge in white flour.

title: biscuit-topped chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in a Dutch oven.
Cover with water and 1 teaspoon salt.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes or until tender.
(Can cook chicken in pressure cooker for about 20 minutes.)
Drain chicken, reserving 2 3/4 cups broth. Set chicken aside.
Add remaining 7 ingredients and 1/2 teaspoon salt to broth and cook 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: pinto bean cake
directions: Cream oleo, sugar, egg and pinto beans.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake 1 hour in greased tube pan at 350° or until done.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bacon.
Put bacon on top and bake in slow oven one hour.
This may be seasoned with hot pepper, if liked.

title: whole wheat biscuits
directions: Cut
margarine into flour, baking powder and salt until margarine is
in mostly pea-sized pieces.
Make well in center and add eggs and 1/2 cup milk.
Beat eggs and milk with a fork until smooth.
Then
continue
stirring
with fork, gradually incorporating flour mixture until moistened.
Add more milk if necessary.
Knead
dough
just
enough
to
bring it together. Roll out
dough
on
floured
board to 1/2-inch thick. Fold in thirds.
Repeat
rolling
and folding.
Roll again to 1/2-inch and cut in rounds.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 500° for 10 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Prepare cookie dough as directed and spread on a pizza pan. Bake as directed.
Cream sugar, vanilla and cheese together. Spread on top of cooled cookie.
Garnish with selected fruits.

title: cherry banana bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar in large bowl until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add bananas and vanilla; beat well.
Combine 1 cup flour, salt and soda.
Add flour mixture to batter; blend well.
Combine pecans and raisins with remaining flour.
Blend pecan mixture and cherries into batter.
Pour into waxed paper-lined loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: beef and gravy
directions: Saute onion in skillet in butter until brown. Place onion in slow cooker, but reserve drippings. Brown roast in skillet in drippings. Add meat to slow cooker, again reserving drippings. Combine salt, pepper, water, bouillon and flour. Add to meat drippings. Cook until thickened. Pour over meat. Cover. Cook on low 6 to 8 hours. Serve over noodles.

title: kool-aid pie
directions: Blend all 3 ingredients. Pour into graham cracker crust. Chill 2 hours or more before serving.

title: tuna potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water for 10 minutes; drain.
Blend flour into butter in double boiler.
Stir in mustard, milk and seasonings.
Cook until smooth and thick, stirring frequently. Layer potatoes, tuna and onions in greased 2-quart casserole, alternating all 3 ingredients.
Pour sauce over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: summer cooler
directions: In a juice extractor, first put through orange, then lime and peach.
Mix well.
Add mineral water; mix.
Serve over crushed ice.
Makes 1 serving.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Sprinkle bread cubes over sausage.
Beat eggs, mustard, milk and salt.
Pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, top with cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: mango vinaigrette(tropical sauce)
directions: Place the mango in the blender or food processor.
Add the honey.
Slowly while you process, add the vinegar.
Add the olive oil.
Add salt, pepper and optional herbs.
Blend thoroughly. Check for seasoning.
Use over salad, chicken breasts or slices of pork tenderloin.

title: grandma's biscuit pie
directions: Soak biscuits in water.
Combine biscuits, eggs, vanilla, nutmeg and sugar; mix well.
Pour into a small square cake pan. Cook for 35 minutes; let brown.

title: oat pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Heat skillet and fry.

title: oatmeal apple crumble
directions: Mix together 1/2 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon flour, salt, cinnamon and apples.
Place into a greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Mix the butter, remaining flour, brown sugar, baking powder and oatmeal into a crumbly mixture; sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes, until topping is browned and apples are tender.

title: sausage dressing
directions: Bake cornbread, let cool and crumble into a large bowl. Crumble sausage into frying pan.
Cook sausage with chopped celery and onions until pink color leaves sausage and celery and onions are tender.
Let cool.
Add remaining ingredients, mix well, using enough broth so dressing will not be dry.
Let set for at least 30 minutes, stirring occasionally, add more broth if needed.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake at 375° until brown, about 1 hour.

title: deep fried mushrooms
directions: In small
bowl,
mix
together beaten egg and milk; set aside. On a plate put flour, salt and pepper.
Wash and slice mushrooms. First,
dip
mushrooms
in egg mixture and then in flour mixture. Drop
in
hot
oil
and
fry 3 to 4 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: bacon and water chestnut appetizer
directions: Cut water chestnuts in 1/2.
Wrap each with 1/3 strip of bacon. Serve with wooden toothpick.
Bake in large shallow dish for 35 minutes at 350°.
Drain all grease.
Combine sugar and ketchup and pour over chestnuts and bacon.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 300°.

title: sauce for fresh fruit
directions: Cook the above ingredients until thickens.
Cool.
Add 2 beaten eggs and cook for 1 minute or until bubbly.
Cool slightly; pour over fresh fruit.

title: german style chicken
directions: Layer chicken, skin side down, in a greased 9 x 13 dish and sprinkle with the salt and pepper.
Cover layer evenly with the drained sauerkraut.
Cover with the 4 slices of swiss cheese. Spread the salad dressing evenly over the top.
Cover the dish with aluminum foil and bake at 325 F for 1 1/2 hrs.
Remove from oven, drain excess juices, brown top quickly under broiler if needed.
Garnish with parsley.

title: hot crab appetizer
directions: Combine together cream cheese and milk.
Add crabmeat, onion, horseradish, salt and pepper.
Blend well.
Spoon into ovenproof dish.
Sprinkle with 1/3 cup toasted almonds.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve with saltines.
Serves 4.
Enjoy!

title: pizza pasta salad
directions: Prepare pasta according to package.
Drain and place in a large mixing bowl.
Cut each pepperoni; slice into 4 pieces and slice the provolone cheese into slices the size of match sticks. Add Provolone cheese and pepperoni to pasta bowl.
Add cherry tomatoes, Parmesan cheese, Italian dressing, Italian seasoning, minced garlic and water.

title: lemon chicken in a crock-pot
directions: Cut up chickens.
Use only breasts, legs, thighs and wings. Combine salt and flour; coat chicken thoroughly.
Then brown the chicken in hot oil; drain.
Place chicken in crock-pot.
Combine lemonade concentrate, brown sugar, vinegar and catsup.
Pour over chicken.
Place cover on crock-pot and cook on high heat setting for 3 to 4 hours.
Remove chicken and pour the liquid into a saucepan.
Return chicken to crock-pot and cover to retain heat. Skim excess fat from liquid.
Blend cold water into cornstarch and then stir into hot liquid.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Serve chicken with gravy over hot, cooked rice.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Roll out crescent rolls onto ungreased pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Whip together remaining ingredients.
Put cream cheese mixture on top of cooled rolls.
Top with veggies (broccoli, cauliflower, shredded carrots, alfalfa sprouts).

title: hamburger and vegetable casserole
directions: Brown ground beef until crumbly and no longer pink; drain fat.
Mix beef with the remaining ingredients.
Spoon into baking dish and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: frozen almond dessert
directions: Melt ice cream and blend in almond extract.
Mix crumbs and pecans; pour 1/2 the mixture into an extra large Pyrex dish.
Pour the melted ice cream mixture over the crumb mixture and put remaining crumbs over the top.
Freeze and cut in squares to serve.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain off the grease.
Put back into skillet and add the onions and green pepper; cook for about 5 minutes.
Add the tomato juice, then the tomato paste.
Stir well; add the sugar and cook about 15 minutes or so.
Makes 4 servings.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Cut off tips of chicken wings.
Cut wings apart at joint. Marinate overnight or at least 1/2 day.
Place wings on cookie sheet or shallow pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.
Should be moist and juicy; baste if too dry.

title: strawberry freezer jam
directions: Mix strawberries and sugar in large bowl; let stand 10 minutes.
Stir lemon juice and Certo together and pour into berries and sugar.
Stir 3 minutes.
Pour immediately into freezer jars or cartons.
Allow to set at room temperature for 24 hours. Store in freezer.

title: brownies
directions: In saucepan, melt oleo, sugar and cocoa.
Mix well and add flour, salt and eggs.
Mix well and bake in greased pan for 20 minutes at 325°.

title: old fashion fruitcake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix brown sugar, butter, eggs and flour together.

title: instant tea mix
directions: Mix all together and use 2 teaspoons to 1 cup hot water.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except the pecans.
Make into a large ball and roll in the pecans.
Chill, wrapped in wax paper for several hours.

title: beer cheese
directions: Grate cheese and garlic in a food processor, add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Mix until creamy and spreadable.
Serve with crackers.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; cream.
Add bananas. Add flour, salt, baking soda and vanilla with buttermilk.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add nuts prior to putting batter into pan.

title: angel delight
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add ice cream and strawberries. Stir until ice cream melts.
Chill until thickened, approximately 20 minutes.
Spread strawberry mixture between layers of cake. Chill 4 hours.
Before serving, frost with whipped topping.

title: lemon chicken
directions: In a skillet, cook chicken, onion, carrot and garlic in butter until chicken is lightly browned, about 5 minutes.
In a bowl, combine the cornstarch and broth.
Stir in lemon juice, peel, salt and rice.
Add to skillet; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Add broccoli and parsley.
Cover; simmer for 5 to 10 minutes, or until rice is tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: breakfast drink for two
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend on high speed until smooth.

title: apricot cake
directions: Blend all ingredients with mixer until smooth.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar and beat well until light in color.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add flavoring and beat again.
Sift flour and baking powder together 3 times.
Add milk, starting and ending with flour.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 80 minute at 325° or until done.

title: tate's own reese's cup fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, cocoa and salt in heavy saucepan.
Cook on medium heat until mixture forms a solid ball when dropped into saucer of cold water.
Take off the stove and add peanut butter, stirring until completely
dissolved.
Pour into buttered pan and let cool.

title: easy cherry chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Stir in cake mix (dry), cherry pie filling and oil until blended.
Spread in pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
(Surface of cake will be lumpy.)
Cool completely. Prepare pudding as directed for pie.
Let stand about 5 minutes or until thickened.
Spread over cake.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: chocolate chip plus cookies
directions: Cream the margarine, shortening, sugars, vanilla and eggs. Add flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Stir in oats, chips and coconut.
Chill 3 to 4 hours before cooking.
Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 12 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 dozen cookies.

title: fresh peach cake
directions: Cream butter with brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg.
Sift flour with soda and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beating until smooth after each addition.
Gently blend in peaches.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: bonita's chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in baking dish sprayed with nonstick spray. Top with Swiss cheese.
Combine milk and soup.
Spoon over chicken.
Sprinkle with dry stuffing mix.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes, depending on amount.
Prepare corn bread to your specifications.
Use broth from your meat. Mix giblets and saute vegetables.
Break up corn bread; mix in broth, vegetables and seasonings.
If baked with meat it will take a little longer.
If croutons are used, use sparingly.

title: pecan pie(1 pie crust)
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add beaten eggs, Karo, vanilla, melted margarine and pecans.
Cook at 400° for 10 minutes, then turn to 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Take pineapple juice and add vanilla pudding and Tang.
Mix with fruit.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Combine all in a punch bowl.
Garnish with sliced oranges, lemons and limes.
Serve.

title: chopped broccoli casserole
directions: Mix mayonnaise and eggs; add to broccoli, cheese and onion. Sprinkle stuffing over and dot with oleo.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: veggie stew
directions: Mix everything in a large ovenproof casserole.
Sprinkle tapioca on top.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 325°.
Stir before serving over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: lasagna
directions: Alternate meat, sauce and cottage cheese with noodles and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 15 minutes until cheese melts.
Works well in crock-pot.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Boil squash, about 8 minutes or until tender; drain well, then mash.
Stir in margarine, milk and crackers plus cheese and eggs. Season with salt and pepper.
Transfer mixture to buttered 3-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: the lady's cheesy mac
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: orange fruit cake
directions: Cut up all fruit and nuts.
Mix together.
Add no liquid.
Add eggs and cake mix.
Mix well with hands.
Bake in tube pan for 2 1/2 hours on 250°.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Place chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch ungreased baking dish. Combine cranberry sauce, onion soup and French dressing.
Mix well and pour over chicken.
Marinate overnight.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover and continue baking an additional 25 minutes or until tender.

title: baked green beans
directions: Cook beans by package directions and drain.
Combine soup, mushrooms and cheese spread.
Toss beans with the soup-cheese mixture and place in a 6-cup casserole dish.
Top with French fried onions and crumbled bacon.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: gourmet chicken breasts wrapped in phyllo dough
directions: Combine the mayonnaise, onion, lemon juice and garlic.
Thaw the phyllo sheets according to package directions.
Brush a sheet of phyllo dough with melted butter.
Place a second sheet on top of first and brush with butter.
Place chicken breast in 1 corner of dough and cover with about 1 tablespoon of mayonnaise mixture. Roll up and fold into bundle.
Brush with butter.
Repeat with balance of chicken breasts.
Sprinkle chicken phyllo with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake on cookie sheet, uncovered, at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes until nicely browned.

title: sweet-sour chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish (clean up is easier if you line the dish with foil).
Mix the salad dressing, preserves, onion soup mix and water.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour covered.
Uncover and continue baking for half hour.
Before serving garnish with pineapple and green pepper.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Beat eggs; add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla; cream together.
Mix in flour, add nuts. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets; reserve beet liquid to measure 2/3 cup (if needed, add water).
In small saucepan, stir together flour, sugar, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in beet liquid and vinegar to flour mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil for 1 minute.
Stir in sliced beets and heat through.

title: chocolate chip cottage pudding
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Stir in chips.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes in an 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Serve warm with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Spray or grease pan.
Serves 6 to 9.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine berries and sugar; set aside.
Mix jello in hot water. Add pineapple syrup.
Chill until almost set.
Add cranberry mixture, nuts and celery.
Chill until firm.

title: carolina coffee cake
directions: Melt butter.
Mix all other ingredients.
Roll biscuits in melted butter, then roll in the other ingredients.
Put sideways in a Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
The biscuits will be all together to form a cake.

title: chicken noodle soup with vegetables
directions: Heat all ingredients, except noodles, to boiling in Dutch oven; reduce heat. Cover and simmer until chicken is done, about 45 minutes. Skim fat. Remove chicken from broth. Cool slightly. Cook noodles as package directs. Remove chicken bones; shred chicken into pieces. Add chicken and noodles to broth. Heat through.

title: ricotta puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients except powdered sugar.
Add a tablespoon of mixture to hot oil one tablespoon at a time.
Balls will form puffs.
Turn them in oil.
Remove; drain on paper towels. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: bacon wrapped water chestnuts
directions: Wrap each chestnut with 1/2 piece bacon skewer with toothpick. Bake at 350° for approximately 1/2 hour.
Drain grease.
Combine catsup and sugars.
Pour over chestnuts and bake another 1/2 hour.

title: lois h's baked carrots
directions: Cook carrots until just slightly done, about 8 minutes.
Saute onions in the 3 tablespoons butter.
Mix together all but the croutons and stick of butter.
Place in buttered or sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt the stick of butter.
Toss in the croutons. Sprinkle over the carrots.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: orange-pecan bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Sift first 6 ingredients into mixing bowl.
Stir in pecans and orange peel. Combine orange juice, egg and vegetable oil in large cup measure and beat until thoroughly blended.
Add dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Pour batter into loaf pan and bake 60 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes. Remove and cool completely on wire rack.

title: tamale pie
directions: Remove paper wrapper from tamales and cut into bite size pieces.
Place corn, chili and tamales in baking dish. Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Stir.
Sprinkle tortilla chips and cheese over all. Bake another 10 minutes. Garnish with lettuce and ripe olives.

title: sour cream noodles
directions: Boil noodles with a few bouillon cubes.
Drain.
Add butter, sour cream and more bouillon for flavor and poppy seeds if desired.
Mix.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Melt margarine in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spoon graham crumbs into margarine and mix well.
Flatten crumbs to form crust.
Pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with chocolate chips, coconut and nuts and press down firmly.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool and cut into bars.
Store, loosely covered, at room temperature.

title: cheese cake
directions: Crush crackers and make a regular graham cracker crust, mixing crumbs and margarine.
Place in baking dish, 15 x 9 1/2 or 2-inch or smaller for thicker cake (13 x 9 1/2-inch).
Mix cream cheese, eggs, 1 cup sugar, vanilla and lemon juice.
Pour over graham cracker crust and bake 35 minutes in 325° oven.
Cool to warm to lukewarm.

title: swiss steak
directions: Pound flour, salt, and pepper into steak.
Cut into serving size pieces.
Brown meat on both sides in oil with onion.
Add soup diluted with water.
Simmer slowly for 2 hours or more, until tender.
You can also put the oven on low.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine strawberries and sugar.
Set aside.
Mix water and cornstarch; bring to boil.
Mix strawberry Jell-O into boiling water and cornstarch mixture.
Add strawberries.
While mixture is still hot, pour into pie shells.
Refrigerate.
When set, cover with Cool Whip.
Makes 2 pies.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Place meat and soup bone in large pot with salt, peas, barley and water.
Bring to a boil.
