Add all of the remaining ingredients.
Continue cooking on low heat.
Season to taste. Remove meat when done and reheat.
Cook approximately 4 hours.

title: date filled bars
directions: Combine dates, 1/4 cup sugar and water in small saucepan. Cook 5 minutes, until mixture boils and thickens.
Remove from heat; add extract.
Cool.
Combine remaining ingredients in separate bowl along with remaining 1/2 cup sugar.
Sprinkle half of mixture in bottom of 8-inch baking pan.
Cover with date mixture.
Cover with other half of oatmeal mixture.
Press down slightly.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cut while warm.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Chill.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: "best yet" chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Stir in remaining ingredients ("smashing" tomatoes!).
Simmer 20 minutes.
Best served next day.

title: perfect pickled peaches
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, and spices in a heavy saucepan and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered for 5 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill for at least 1 hour to blend flavors well.

title: poor man's ham salad
directions: Place all ingredients in bowl for mixing.
Add mayonnaise last.
Mix together and place on bread of your choice.

title: stove top stuffing
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Add enough hot water to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Combine stuffing and season mix and chicken broth.
Mix all ingredients and bake for 20 minutes. Garnish with pineapple around it.
Bake at 350°.
Serve.

title: havasu potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl.
Place in buttered casserole dish.

title: amazing low carb salmon patties(this recipe makes four good sized patties.)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat about 2 tablespoons butter in a large skillet to medium temperature.
Make mixture into patties.
Drop patties onto butter in skillet.
Make sure to keep lots of butter in skillet; add more if necessary.
Don't flip patties until they are nice and brown on first side or they will fall apart.
Carefully flip them with a large spatula.
Continue to fry until nice and dark golden brown. Remove patties to a serving plate.
Pour the Special Sauce over the patties (see following).

title: mexican cheesy bean casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Put back in pan and add tomatoes, chilies and beans (drained).
Add salt and pepper and chili powder.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Layer bottom of casserole dish with Doritos, then meat and top with cheese.
Place in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes at 350°.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Slice Twinkies lengthwise.
Layer 9 x 13-inch pan with halved Twinkies, creme side up.
Pour and spread both cartons of strawberries over Twinkies.
Top with vanilla pudding.
Top with Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: monkey paw(bread)
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugar.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Dip biscuit pieces into cinnamon and sugar.
Layer biscuits and nuts in well-greased Bundt pan.
Heat oleo and brown sugar until syrupy.
Pour over biscuits.
Put into cold oven.
Turn oven to 350°.
Bake 35 minutes.
Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes; turn onto plate.

title: lazy man's beef stew
directions: Grease large casserole dish.
Put into it beef, carrots, potatoes, tomato soup, bay leaf, onions and the wine or water. Cover and bake in 275° oven for 4 hours.
Remove from oven and stir (may need a little more water).
Add frozen peas and the mushrooms.
Cover again and cook 1 hour longer.
Serves 6.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add persimmon pulp and milk, then add eggs and butter.
Pour into greased pan and bake 1 hour in 325° oven.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Mix meat and onion.
Brown lightly in skillet.
Remove meat and onion from heat and drain.
Mix sauces and soup.

title: awesome zucchini bake
directions: Slice zucchini in circles.
Coat in flour and salt and pepper.
Fry in a small amount of oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Layer zucchini, sauce, olives, mushrooms, and cheese in a 13 x 9 baking dish.
Place in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until cheese bubbles.
Serve with tossed salad and breadsticks.
Serves 6.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Spread chopped onion over butter; spread rice over onion.
Melt bouillon cubes in 2 cups boiling water.
Pour over ingredients.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: asparagus canapes
directions: Cut crust from bread.
Roll bread thin with rolling pin. Spread with mixture of cheese, mayo and egg.
Place 1 stalk of asparagus at end of each slice of bread.
Roll up and cut into 3 pieces.
Dip each in melted butter.
Freeze until ready to serve. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° until brown (around 15 minutes).

title: amish bread
directions: Pour hot water over the 2 Tbsp. sugar, salt and butter.
Cool to lukewarm (butter should be melted).
Dissolve yeast in the 1/2 c. lukewarm water mixed with 1 Tbsp. sugar.
When the yeast is working and the liquids have cooled, combine them.
Add flour until a stiff dough forms, mixing well after each addition.
Knead stiff dough 8 - 10 minutes, adding the rest of the flour as needed.
Dough should be smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl and let stand for 25 minutes.
Punch down and let rise for 15 minutes.
Punch down and let rise for 15 minutes three more times. Form three round loaves and put on cookie sheet(s).
Slash tops every inch before rising.

Let rise and brush with a mixed egg yolk and milk before baking at 350 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes. This bread takes a little extra time but is well worth the effort. The rising/punching down gives the loaves a wonderful texture not found in most homemade breads.
This is a great bread to serve with a hot bowl of homemade soup.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken , bone and
cut in bite size pieces.
Cook broccoli, until just
tender.
Place
broccoli
in
bottom
of buttered 9 x
13-inch
casserole.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry and cheese together well.
Add chicken to mixture and put over broccoli.
Cover
with
buttered bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mandarin mousse mold
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl for 2 minutes until completely dissolved. Stir in cold water. Place mandarin oranges in 6-cup mold. Spoon 2 cups gelatin mixture into mold over oranges. Refrigerate about 30 minutes or until set, but not firm (should stick to finger).

title: meatballs and noodles
directions: Mix and shape into 24 (1 1/2-inch) balls.
Brown slowly in 2 tablespoons oil, shaking often.
Add broth, mushrooms and onion. Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Blend cream and flour.
Stir into broth.
Cook and stir until thick.
Serve over warm noodles.

title: best ever chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix the last 3 ingredients together; set aside.
Beat margarine and Crisco together.
Add eggs; beat.
Add sugars and beat.
Add vanilla and beat until all ingredients are smooth, then add dry ingredients.
Mix.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a preheated 375° oven.

title: garden-vegetable pasta
directions: Cook pasta in a large pot of boiling water.
About 5 minutes before the pasta is done, stir in the bag of frozen vegetables. While they cook, in a large serving bowl, mix sour cream and party-dip mix.
Drain pasta and vegetables well, then add to the sour cream mixture and toss to mix and coat.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4.

title: no sugar chocolate pecan cookies
directions: Combine baking mix, pudding mixes and Sugar Twin. Mix well. Stir in butter, vanilla, mayonnaise and pecans. Knead until well mixed. Shape into small balls. Place on greased cookie sheet and flatten. Bake at 350° for 16 minutes or until firm. Cool. Store in airtight container.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Sprinkle 1 heaping tablespoonful salt over cucumbers, onions and green peppers and place in refrigerator for 3 to 3 1/2 hours. Stir occasionally.
Drain completely.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Let stand at room temperature until dissolved.
Store in refrigerator, covered.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: *Can use chocolate or strawberry cake mix.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks and mash with a fork.
Then blend in mayonnaise, mustard, lemon juice, salt, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Use 1 tablespoon to each half.

title: easy popcorn syrup
directions: Mix all ingredients, except soda.
Bring to boil over medium heat in heavy pan; boil hard for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add soda; mix well and pour over 6 quarts popped corn.
Mold into balls, or allow to cool and break into pieces.

title: date cookies
directions: Chop dates and nuts.
Cook sugar, milk and oleo until soft boil stage.
Add dates; cook until stiff.
Add nuts.
When slightly firm, spread on damp cloth and roll up.
Cut into small slices when cold.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Pour milk over crumbled bread. Add meat, egg and seasonings. Mix well. Form into walnut-sized balls. Brown in shortening. Shake pan to help balls retain shape. Place in saucepan.

title: holiday munch mix
directions: Place butter in a large microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on High 1 minute or until melted.
Stir in dressing mix.
Mix well. Add pretzel bits and cereals.
Mix well.
Microwave on High 4 to 6 minutes.
Stir every 2 minutes.
Add nuts; mix well.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: nut cake(100 year old family recipe)
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.	Cream butter and sugar. Add all other ingredients; add	dry.
Mix
well.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, then bake at 300° an additional hour.

title: quick and easy blackberry cobbler
directions: Butter oblong baking pan.
Place a few butter patties on bottom of pan.
Mix first 4 ingredients well, then pour into pan. Mix next 3 ingredients thoroughly in bowl.
Spoon mixture on top of batter in oblong pan.
Bake at 375° for approximately 45 minutes or until top of crust is golden brown.

title: emily's easy punch
directions: Dilute lemonade as directed on can.
Add 7-Up and sherbet.

title: one step rolls
directions: Mix together and turn out on floured board.
Add flour as needed for kneading.
Knead and cut out as biscuits.
Put in greased pan, cover with waxed paper.
Let rise for about 2 hours. Cook in 425° oven until done.

title: cranberry applesauce mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce and stir until melted.
Add applesauce.
Add 1 cup cold water. Stir.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: sweet snack mix
directions: In large bowl combine cereal, pretzels and nuts-set aside. In microwave safe bowl heat chips at 70 percent power for one minute. Stir. Microwave 30 seconds longer. Stir until smooth. Immediately pour chips over cereal mixture and toss evenly to coat. Spread on waxed paper lined baking sheet. Cook and break into pieces.

title: mother's butter cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Put wax paper on bottom and grease and flour.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter, adding sugar and creaming well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately, ending with flour.
Beat well.
Add salt, baking powder and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into pan and bake for 1 1/4 hours or until golden brown.
Let cool on rack in pan about 10 minutes, then turn out on rack to cool.
This cake is excellent for birthday cakes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well and form in 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and chill.
Combine next 4 ingredients and cook until thick.
Cool and spread over Jell-O.
Prepare Dream Whip as directed on box.
Whip in cream cheese.
Spread over Jell-O.
Top with nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: vega-burger soup
directions: Cook hamburger until well done.
Strain off excess grease. Put hamburger in a large pot.
Add vegetables, tomato soup and 2 cans of water.
Cook over medium-low heat for 1/2 hour.
Serve with hot rolls or cornbread.

title: baked scrambled eggs(with bacon, cheese and chives)
directions: Whisk eggs and egg whites in large bowl until frothy.
Add milk, bread, salt and pepper to taste and mix well.
Let stand 20 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Stir all ingredients together. Preheat oven to 450°. Spoon batter into muffin pans. Bake until brown on top.

title: aunt eva mae's blondies
directions: Mix flour, soda, baking powder and salt together.
Beat egg; add to mixture.
Mix in sugar, margarine or butter, nuts and vanilla.
Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour batter into pan. Sprinkle with 1/2 package semi-sweet chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spaghetti with four cheeses
directions: Prepare spaghetti as label directs; drain well in colander and keep hot.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers in thin rounds, also cut onions and peppers in very thin slices. Mix with 1/2 c. salt and a qt. of cracked ice. Let stand for 3 hours in a covered stone crock, weighing down the pickles. Drain. Mix turmeric, ground cloves, celery seed, sugar, white vinegar together and pour the mixture over the pickles. Bring to the boiling point in an enamel or aluminum kettle. Pour into jars. Makes 8 pints or 3 quarts.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Let sit for at least 2 hours.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sugar pie crust
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour and confectioners sugar. Cut in butter and blend to a pie dough consistency.
Press the dough evenly into an 8 or 9-inch pie plate.
Prick dough all over bottom with the tines of a fork.
Bake for 20 minutes, until lightly browned.
Remove and let cool.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a greased casserole dish at 400° for 25 minutes or until set.

title: taquitos
directions: Scramble eggs in sausage drippings after sausage is cooked. Then add the sausage and cheese to eggs.
Put mixture on a flour tortilla and add picante sauce, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Use large skillet or Dutch oven.
Brown flour in oil.
Add onion, green pepper, celery, stewed tomatoes, tomato sauce and all other ingredients, except for mushrooms.
Bring to simmer for 20 minutes.
Add shrimp and mushrooms.
Simmer for another 20 minutes.
Serve over steamed white rice.
Garnish with minced green onion.

title: apple dip
directions: Combine all ingredients until well blended.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan, set aside.
In small glass measure, combine with milk, the almond and vanilla extracts; set aside.
In a large bowl mix with electric mixer on high speed, cream butter with sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, alternately add one fourth flour with one third milk mixture, then add butter mixture; place in prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 40 minutes, or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool cake on wire rack for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool thoroughly.
Serve plain or sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
Makes 20 servings.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken with celery, salt and pepper.
Debone chicken and place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour melted oleo over chicken.
If using vegetables, add them now.
Mix flour and milk with wire beater and pour over chicken.
Heat chicken broth and add cream of chicken soup.
Mix with wire beater.
Pour over flour mixture.
Bake at 400° until slightly brown (about 25 to 30 minutes).
If overcooked it is too dry.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Sift together and set aside flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Blend together shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour mixture and mix well.
Add rolled oats, vanilla and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Yield:
11 dozen.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Prick potatoes before microwaving.
Microwave on High 12 to 20 minutes per 3 to 4 potatoes.
Slice the top from each potato. With a teaspoon, remove center of potatoes to mixing bowl, leaving shells intact.
For each potato, add to mixing bowl 2 tablespoons butter, sour cream, 1/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Mix with electric mixer until smooth.
Divide potato mixture evenly among shells, mounding if necessary.
Sprinkle with chives, if desired.
Place potatoes on plate suitable for microwave oven. Microwave 1 minute per potato.

title: pumpkin bread or cake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together, then add last ones and mix well.
For bread, bake in 3 loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour. Test for doneness.
For cake, bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 25 minutes. Test for doneness.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.
Serve with love.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate together Cheddar cheese and small onion.
Mix in cream cheese, sauce and salt.
Roll in pecans.
Sprinkle with paprika. Shape into ball.

title: st. patrick's day salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in water; let stand until slightly congealed.
Add marshmallows, pecans, pineapple and fold in whipped cream.
Add cake broken in small pieces.
Cut off all brown crust of cake.

title: zucchini casserole(super tasting)
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients well. Add other ingredients in the order listed, mixing well after each addition. Pour into a buttered pie pan (9-inch or so). Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, until firm. Serve warm. Yields 8 to 10 pieces.

title: easy holiday squares
directions: Gradually add sugar to butter in large bowl.
Cream on medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
At low speed add flour and lemon juice.
Pour batter into greased jelly roll pan.
Mark off 20 squares.
Place heaping teaspoonful of filling in center of squares.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool; sift confectioners sugar on top.
Cut into squares.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cut chicken in bite-size pieces.
Mix other ingredients with 1/2 of the bag of Doritos.
Pour into casserole dish and bake for 20 to 30 minutes
in 350° oven.
Put remaining chips on top and bake 5 minutes more.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: First thaw out frozen broccoli and Cheez Whiz 2 hours before cooking.
In a large bowl, stir well together the chopped broccoli, mushroom soup, Cheez Whiz, chopped onions, chopped celery and Minute rice (uncooked).
Grease casserole dish and pour in mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites to which flavoring has been added.
Slowly add sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Combine cracker crumbs and pecans. Fold into stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into a lightly greased 9-inch pastry pan.
Bake in a preheated 300° oven for 45 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: spinach salad
directions: Chill all ingredients.
Mix spinach, water chesnuts.
Just prior to serving, add remaining ingredients and dressing.

title: chicken tortilla bake
directions: In a bowl, combine the chicken, chiles, broth, soups and onion; set aside.
Warm tortillas in microwave according to package directions.
Layer half of the tortillas on the bottom of a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish or pan, cutting to fit pan if desired.
Top with half of the chicken mixture and half of the cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease. Mix the taco seasoning with the hamburger. Mix the softened cream cheese and sour cream together and place in the bottom of a casserole dish. Place a layer of seasoned ground beef on top of that. Next, put a layer of salsa and then place the shredded Cheddar cheese on top. Repeat, if desired.

title: mountain high cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into 3 layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: turkey swedish meatballs
directions: Combine onion, garlic and water in casserole.
Microwave, covered, on High for 1 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes, until onion is tender.
Add turkey, crumbs, egg, milk and pepper.
Blend well. Roll into 1-inch balls, place in casserole, cover with waxed paper, then cook on High for 6 to 8 minutes.
Remove from casserole.
Add margarine to casserole, melt on High for 30 to 60 seconds.
Blend flour and mace with butter.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook on High for 3 to 5 minutes, until thickened.
Stir occasionally.
Add wine and meat balls, stir, then cook on High 2 to 4 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cindy's surprise
directions: Chunk kolbasi. Place in crock-pot. Add carrots, sliced onions, mushrooms and potatoes. Salt and pepper to taste. Place stick of butter on top. Cover and cook all day.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until light and creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Add sugar, almond extract and vanilla.
Beat until smooth, thick and lemon colored, about 5 to 8 minutes.
Scrape outer edge of bowl.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
When cool, spoon cherry pie filling on top.
(May use blueberries, strawberries or whatever.)

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: In mixing bowl, combine sweet potato, sugar, buttermilk and margarine.
Mix with an electric mixer on low speed until smooth. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Form into a ball and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray a baking sheet with Pam.
Roll dough on floured surface to 1/4 to 1/2-inch.
Cut into 16 biscuits and place on prepared baking sheet.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes until lightly browned.

title: layered fruit salad
directions: Rinse grapes.
Cut in half and remove seeds.
Place in bottom of glass serving bowl.
Peel and slice bananas.
Place over grapes.
Drain peaches well.
Cut into smaller pieces.
Distribute on top of bananas.
Carefully rinse raspberries.
Sprinkle on top of peaches.
Peel oranges.
Remove the white skin.
Slice and cut into smaller pieces.
Place on top of raspberries.
Peel and slice kiwi.
Garnish salad.
Pour orange juice over top of salad and sprinkle with powdered sugar, if used.
Keep salad refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: pasta salad
directions: Toss cooked pasta with assortment of vegetables.
Add salad dressing.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place rice in saucepan and barely cover with water.
Cook on low heat until water is absorbed. Pour rice in baking dish.
Place chicken pieces on top of rice. Mix well the soups and water.
Pour over chicken and sprinkle onion soup mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix 3/4 cup of sugar and water in saucepan over medium heat just until mixture reaches a boil and sugar is dissolved.
Using mixer, whip into the dry milk until smooth.
Chill until cold. Make crust using melted low-fat margarine, sugar and crumbs. Press into an 8-inch pie pan.
Chill while making filling.

title: pecan turtles
directions: Melt caramels and milk.
Remove from heat and add 2 cups pecans.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam and drop candy on cookie sheet about the size of half dollars.
Freeze for an hour or until hard.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip turtles in chocolate mixture and place on waxed paper lined cookie sheet.

title: fresh pineapple compote
directions: Drain the lychees, reserving one-half cup of the syrup.
Mix the reserved syrup with the lime juice.
Cut the lychees into halves; toss with pineapple and orange sections.
Pour the syrup mixture over the fruit; cover and refrigerate.
Serves four to six.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove chicken from bones and cut into small pieces.
Add noodles to broth and cook per directions on package.
Add chicken to broth and noodles.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: strawberry cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with mixer until well blended.
Add egg and blend again.
Pour into graham cracker crust and refrigerate for 3 hours or until firm.
Top with strawberries before serving.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash; salt and pepper to taste.
Drain and mash squash; add onion, margarine, 12 saltine crackers (crumbled), 1/2 of the cheese and sour cream.
Pour into casserole dish.
Crumble remaining saltines and sprinkle on top.
Cover with the remaining cheese and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: old-fashioned salmon cakes
directions: Mix together well and form into patties like hamburger.
Fry in hot skillet.

title: fruit 'n easy
directions: Layer baking pan with pie filling, then 1/2 box cake mix sprinkled on top.
Melt 1/2 stick butter and pour on top.
Mix brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Sprinkle on top.
Microwave for 5 minutes.

title: jello surprise
directions: Add boiling water to gelatin and stir well.
Add pineapple juice and water.
Cool to syrupy and add remaining ingredients. Put in flat dish or individual servings.
Chill.
May be cut in squares to serve.

title: holiday cake
directions: First, she says, you mix the heart, love, kindness and generosity, then add happiness, sugar, laughter, faith, prayers and patience.
And do not freeze.
It lasts forever.

title: simple brisket
directions: Mix cola, chili sauce and onion soup mix.
Place brisket, fat side up, in a Dutch oven or 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour liquid mixture over brisket and cover tightly with lid or aluminum foil.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes per pound, about 3 hours or until tender.
Trim off fat after cooking.
For working moms or dads, cook all day at 220°.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fresh apple dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix dry cake mix, margarine, brown sugar and cinnamon until crumbly.
Reserve 2/3 cup.
Press remaining crumbly mixture in bottom of ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch rectangular pan.
Arrange apple slices on mixture in pan.
Beat sour cream and egg until blended; spread over mixture.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbly mixture.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Cool.
Serves 16.

title: carp patties
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into patties.
Use 2 cups buttermilk and 1 1/2 cups self-rising flour.
Mix together to make a batter.
Dip in carp cakes and fry to golden brown.

title: pumpkin fruit cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs, beating light and fluffy.
Blend in pumpkin.
Sift together dry ingredients to mixture, stirring until thoroughly blended.
Fold in nuts, raisins, cherries and pineapple candies.
Spoon evenly into greased floured bread loaf pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: wet burrito enchiladas
directions: Mix hamburger and onion and cook until done. Drain well.
Add spaghetti sauce, salsa, liquid pepper and seasonings and heat to bubbly hot.
Place portion of meat sauce and refried beans on tortilla.
Roll and tuck ends under.
Place in greased pan with seam down.
Pour remaining sauce over tortillas and over with plenty of grated cheese.
Bake until cheese is bubbly and hot.

title: apple-cheese
directions: Core and cut crisp tart red apples into wedges. Dip in fruit juice to prevent discoloration. Spread with Roquefort cheese, softened with cream, and spear each wedge with a toothpick. Arrange sections close together in a circle around a whole red apple.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: *Can substitute scallops, shrimp or sausage for clams.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Bake pastry shells at 350° and set aside.
Combine eggs and next 5 ingredients in a medium bowl.
Stir well.
Spoon mixture evenly into pastry shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Garnish, if desired.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Mix flour and milk; add hot chicken broth, thyme, oregano
or marjoram, Accent and pepper.
Brown pork sausage, mashing as it fries.
Remove from fat.
Saute in fat the onions and mushrooms. Drain 2 cups wild rice.
Combine all and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Add salt to taste.

title: gumbo
directions: Chop garlic, onions, parsley and celery.
Heat bacon drippings over low heat.
Add flour gradually.
Cook and stir until roux is dark brown.
Add chopped vegetables.
Stir until wilted.
Add chicken broth and Ro-Tel.

title: jerusalem artichoke soup
directions: Peel artichokes and chop coarsely.
Place artichokes, onions, bouillon cubes and water in a large pan.
Bring to boil; lower heat.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Rub through a sieve or grind in a food mill.
Serve hot.

title: easy chicken cordon bleu
directions: Skin, bone and cut chicken breasts in half.
Layer the ham and cheese on the chicken, roll up and place in a greased baking dish, with the open side down.
Cover with the undiluted soup and salt and pepper lightly.
Cover the dish and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake for an additional 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in 1/2 water recommended on package and taste of garlic salt for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Place in casserole.
Add soup. Fold in egg, grate cheese over broccoli.
Tear bread over cheese and dot with butter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cut chicken fine.
Saute onions and celery until tender.
Mix all ingredients together (except spaghetti) with one or more cups chicken broth.
Cook on top of stove very slowly for 1 hour.
Add spaghetti and 1/2 of grated cheese.
Cook in oven for 30 to 40 minutes longer.
Sprinkle rest of cheese on top before removing from oven.
Serve hot.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Beat eggs until thick.
Gradually add sugar and oil; beat until thoroughly blended.
Add flour, salt, baking powder and vanilla; beat until mixed.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Spread half of batter in greased and lightly floured angel food cake pan or Bundt cake pan.
Combine cinnamon and brown sugar; sprinkle half of this mixture over batter.
Spoon in remaining batter.
Top with remaining cinnamon-brown sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except flour, together thoroughly.
Work the flour into the mixture with your hands.
Fill a cookie press with cup of the dough at a time.
Form cookies onto an ungreased baking sheet in the form of an S, rosettes, bars or other desired shapes.
Bake at 400° until set, but not brown, for about 7 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat butter and water until it boils.
Add flour all at once. Stir vigorously until mixture no longer sticks to the side of pan. Cool slightly.
Add eggs one at a time beating after each addition.
Drop by tablespoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes and reduce heat to 325° for 20 minutes.
Punch hole in them and insert lemon pudding that was made by directions on Jell-O pie and pudding mix.

title: peaches and cream cheesecake
directions: Combine flour, salt, egg, baking powder and pudding; beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased pie pan.
Drain peaches, reserving syrup.
Place peaches over batter.
Combine cream cheese, 3 tablespoons peach syrup and 1/2 cup sugar; beat for 2 minutes. Spoon to 1 inch of edge of batter.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until crust is browned.

title: cookie jar gingersnaps
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Form into 1-inch balls and roll in additional confectioners sugar.
Cover with waxed paper and chill overnight.

title: chocolate oatmeal bars
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream together the butter and brown sugar. Add corn syrup and vanilla; stir in oats; press into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10-12 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine peach pie filling, strawberries, pineapple tidbits and bananas. Chill and serve. Top with Cool Whip for creamier taste.

title: pepperoni pizza dip
directions: In small mixer bowl, beat together cream cheese, sour cream, oregano, garlic powder and red pepper.
Spread evenly in a 9 or 10-inch quiche dish or pie plate.
Spread pizza sauce over top. Sprinkle with pepperoni, green onion and green pepper.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Top with cheese; bake 5 minutes more or until cheese is melted and mixture is heated through.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: pear honey
directions: Put pears in a heavy kettle or canner with tight-fitting lid. Pour sugar and pineapple over pears and set overnight to form juice.
Bring to a slow boil and cook for 3 hours.
Don't open lid or stir during the entire cooking period.
Put through strainer. Put back in kettle and bring to boil, then put in jars.

title: pickle relish
directions: Chop cukes, celery, onions and pepper in blender.
Let stand 6 to 8 hours in salt water; drain for 10 minutes before ready to use.
Mix vinegar, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed; bring to boil.
Add vegetable mixture; return to boil.
Get lids and jars ready to can.
Use water bath to seal.

title: simon and garfunkel chicken
directions: Flatten chicken between wax paper; spread with 1/2 butter. Season with salt and pepper.
Place one slice cheese on each chicken breast.
Roll up and fasten ends with toothpicks.
Coat lightly with flour, then dip in egg.
Roll in bread crumbs.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat sugar and oil until mixed well.
Add eggs.
Mix flour, salt and soda.
Stir in fruit cocktail.
Beat and pour in tube pan. Sprinkle with coconut on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: deviled crabs
directions: Cook crabmeat, milk, margarine and cornstarch until like mayonnaise.
Add salt and pepper to taste, mustard and vinegar. Pour into well-greased baking dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and paprika on top.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring until just blended.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour batter into a well-greased Bundt pan or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.
Serve warm or cool.
Good with or without glaze.

title: prize winning prune bread
directions: Put together as a cake.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Very good spread with butter or cream cheese!

title: oatmeal filled cookies
directions: Mix with hands.
Put about 1 tablespoon of dough for each cookie on ungreased cookie sheet, use fingers to flatten out dough.
Cook at 350° until golden brown (about 10 minutes).
Let cookies cool before removing.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger.
Combine hamburger and potatoes in pan with 6 to 8 cups water.
Add salt and pepper to cook (boil) until potatoes are almost tender.
Add celery, corn, onion and garlic powder.
Cook over medium heat until done.

title: candied yams
directions: Place half of the sweet potatoes in a 1 1/2-quart greased casserole dish.
Top with half of the pineapple.
Repeat layers with remaining sweet potatoes and pineapple.
Combine Sweet 'N Low (brown), butter and salt; crumble over top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese bombay
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and make into ball.
Place in a rimmed serving dish and chill.
Mix chutney and onions; pour over cheese ball.
Sprinkle peanuts and bacon on top.
Serve with crackers.

title: hot clam spread
directions: Combine first two ingredients in a small pan and simmer until soft (about 3 minutes).
Combine remaining ingredients in a bowl. Add pan mixture to bowl and combine well.
Spread mixture into a lightly greased quiche dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 20 minutes.
Uncover and continue to bake for 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir in butter, Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper and egg until thoroughly mixed. Spread evenly in pan.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle graham crackers to make crust.
Layer coconut flakes, chocolate chips and pecans. Pour milk over layers in a grid-like fashion covering the top layer.
You will probably have milk left over.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut bars.

title: pot roast in foil
directions: Place meat in center of piece of foil.
Salt, pepper and slice onion on top.
Fold foil.
Place seam side up in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: italian meatloaf
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Thoroughly mix together chuck and ham.
Add tomatoes, crumbs, and 8 oz. steak sauce.
Mix thoroughly. Shape into two large loaves.
You may place loaves in bread pans or place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Drain fat and reduce heat to 325.
Bake for one hour, draining fat off every 20 minutes.
Moisten with juice if the loaves begin to look too dry. Mix together ketchup and 8 ounces steak sauce and 1/4 cup brown sugar.
Pour over loaves and bake 20 minutes longer.
Let stand 15 minutes before slicing.
Recipe may be halved.

title: tortellini pesto soup
directions: Combine onion and soup broth.
Bring to a boil; gradually stir in tortellini.
Reduce heat to medium heat and cook 3 minutes. Gradually stir in pea pods.
Cook 3 minutes longer.
Stir in pesto sauce.
Serve.

title: cajun beans and rice
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in 1-quart microwaveable casserole dish.
Microwave on High 4 to 6 minutes or until heated through. Stir in 1/4 cup bacon. Top with remaining bacon.
If desired, garnish with sliced green onions.
Makes 4 servings.

title: italian soup
directions: In large saucepan, cook sausage and separate meat.
Add vegetables, garlic and oregano.
Add remaining ingredients, except tortellini; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer until done. Stir occasionally.
Cook tortellini; add to soup when ready to serve.
Makes 8 cups.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients except for gallon milk.
Pour into ice cream freezer and finish filling with gallon milk.
Stir well.
It improves the flavor of the ice cream if you let mixture mellow in the refrigerator for 3 to 4 hours.

title: fresh fruit pie
directions: In covered blender, blend 1 cup of fruit at high speed for 30 seconds.
In 2-quart saucepan, mix cornstarch and water until smooth.
Add mashed fruit, corn syrup and lemon juice.
Stirring constantly bring to boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute.
Turn into bowl; cover surface with waxed paper.
Cool 1 hour.
Fold in remaining fruit.
Spread cream onto bottom and sides of pie crust. Fill with fruit mixture.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Serves 6 to 8.
(Whipped cream may be used as topping instead of spreading on bottom of crust.)

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Line bottom of pan with asparagus.
Cover with grated cheese, then soup and about 5 slices of butter.
Place boiled egg slices between layers.
Cover with crumbled crackers.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: toffee bars
directions: Roll out crescent rolls on a jelly roll cookie sheet.
Melt butter and brown sugar until smooth.
Pour over dough.
Sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips over butter mixture.
Bake at 375° for 14 to 18 minutes.

title: cow pies
directions: In a double boiler over simmering water, melt chocolate chips and shortening, stirring until smooth. Remove from heat, stir in raisins and nuts. Drop by tbsp
onto waxed paper. Chill until ready to serve.

title: cream of zucchini soup
directions: Cook scallions slowly in butter until tender, but not browned. Add zucchini slices, broth, vinegar and herbs.
Bring to a boil, then stir in farina.
Simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.
Put in blender; thin with more liquid, if necessary.
Season.
Add 1/2 cup sour cream.
Chill.
Serve with dollop of sour cream and parsley.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Fill the filter-lined basket of a large automatic percolator with the brown sugar, cloves, allspice and cinnamon sticks. Prepare as you would coffee according to directions, but substitute cider for water.
Yields 16 to 20 servings.

title: chili sauce
directions: *Or use 4 tablespoons of pickling spice.

title: crispix snack
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients together.
Add cereal.
Gently mix with confectioners sugar.

title: beef porcupines
directions: Combine rice and vermicelli with ground beef and egg.
Shape into small meatballs (about 20).
Brown on all sides in skillet.

title: fudge pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate and margarine.
Add other ingredients to melted mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 35 to 40 minutes or until pie appears set.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: penuche
directions: In a pot, combine sugar, brown sugar, milk and salt.
Cook slowly until sugar dissolves and mixture forms soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Drizzle butter over top; do not combine.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Blend in vanilla and peanuts.
Place mixture in a greased pan; let stand until firm.
Yields 1 1/2 pounds.

title: gawumke(cabbage rolls)
directions: Mix together all ingredients except the cabbage.
Boil cabbage to soften the leaves.
Cut leaves off the core.
Thin out the thick part of the cabbage leaf near the core.
Scoop some of the mixture into the cabbage leaves and roll tight, tucking in the ends.
Repeat until mixture is gone.
Spray baking dish and place rolls in dish.
Pour sauce over rolls.

title: potato balls (rellenos de papa)(puerto rican dish)
directions: Boil potatoes until soft; drain.
Add butter, whip well.
Add egg, salt, cornstarch and cool.
Divide into 12 parts.
Make a potato ball and roll in cornstarch.
Make a hole in center of ball and put in filling.
Roll again in cornstarch and fry until brown (10 minutes).
Add all other ingredients, heat medium.
Mix well. Turn to low heat, cover and cook for 30 minutes.
For pork:
Saute in tried out salt pork and cook for 1 hour.
Potatoes can be filled with Cheddar cheese.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Cook chicken in boiling water until done.
Drain and save water.
Chop chicken into small pieces.
Add spaghetti to the chicken water and cook until done. In another pan, melt butter, saute celery and onions.
Stir in pimentos.
Add chicken, soup, milk, Velveeta, salt and pepper. Drain spaghetti and add to chicken mixture.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cheddar cheese on top.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Serves 8-10 people.

title: sausage lentil soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown and crumble the sausage.
Drain fat. Add the next 9 ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or until lentils and vegetables are tender.
Stir in mustard.
Remove bay leaf before serving.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: mexican spaghetti
directions: Boil spaghetti until tender; drain.
Add chili and corn to browned beef.
In 9 x 12-inch pan, layer beef mixture and spaghetti.
Top with undiluted cheese soup and grated cheese. Bake 20 minutes in 375° oven.

title: bath salts
directions: Mix ingredients together; store in bathroom.
Fill tub with hot water and 1/2 cup bath salts.
Set timer for 45 minutes and read or browse through magazines.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Mix together lemon jello and water.
Cool and let partially set.
Mix together sugar and cream cheese; add whipped Pet milk. Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill.

title: garden pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain, but do not rinse.
Put pasta back into the kettle. While the pasta is hot, toss with the vegetables.
Cover for 3 to 5 minutes.
Vegetables will lightly steam in pasta.
Place pasta in a large bowl.
Top with 3/4 of the dressing and lightly toss. Chill several hours or overnight.
If pasta is dry, add remaining dressing along with meat, cheese, olives and parsley or basil, if desired.
Chill until ready to serve.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 10-inch tube pan.
In a small bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Sift flour, spices, soda and salt together.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well.
Add buttermilk alternately with flour mixture.
Add jam and vanilla.
Beat just until well mixed.
Carefully fold in egg whites.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 30 minutes, then increase oven temperature to 350° and bake for 55 minutes more.
Frost with Caramel Icing. Makes 16 servings.

title: neptune casserole
directions: Saute celery, onion, pepper in margarine.
Mix with other ingredients.
Put in greased 11 x 7 inch casserole dish.
Cover and bake 40 minutes at 325°.
Uncover and add some grated cheese on top.
Bake another 5 to 10 minutes.
Serves 8. (A Hilton head specialty.)

title: blanche's chicken casserole
directions: Mix well and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until browned.

title: glazed almonds
directions: Heat sugar and butter until melted.
Add almonds and cook until golden brown.
Pour on foil; spread thin.
Sprinkle lightly with salt.
